column12: COVER OF A CUP
column13: 본 고안은 통상의 휴대용 컵에 끼워지는 컵 뚜껑에 관한 것으로서, 본체와 여기에 얹혀져서 끼워지는 뚜껑으로 되어있는 것이다. 뚜껑은 그 저면에 형성되어있는 걸림편이 본체의 상부원통부 내면에 돌설되어있는 평면테두리에 걸린체로 회전될 수 있으며 본체와 뚜껑에 형성시킨 절결부를 일치시키거나 불일치시켜서 음료를 취출하거나 밀폐시킬수 있도록 된 것이다. 본 고안은 뚜껑의 양측에 2개의 절결부가 있으므로 컵을 잡은체로 오른손잡이나 왼손잡이 모두가 편리하게 사용할 수 있으며 불사용시에는 음료를 외부공기로부터 차단시킨체로 위생적으로 안전하게 보관할 수 있게 한것임.

column13: PURPOSE: A donation method through online game play and a system thereof are provided to integrate the online game play of a user and a donation activity using a donation point obtained in a game, thereby promoting active participation of users. column12: Method of preparing organically modified aluminosilcates sol-gel films
column13: An organically modified sol-gel method of preparing substantially crack-free aluminosilicates films is provided. Chelated aluminum alkoxide and polydimethylsiloxane are mixed in a 1:1 ratio by weight in a solvent and refluxed at approximately the boiling temperature of the solvent to produce a sol-gel liquid including polymerized aluminosilicates. The sol-gel liquid is cooled to room temperature. Additional solvent is added to the sol-gel liquid to reduce its viscosity. A substrate is coated with the reduced viscosity sol-gel liquid. The coating of sol-gel liquid on the substrate is dried to produce an organically modified aluminosilicates sol-gel film. The sol-gel film is heated, to enhance polymerization of the sol-gel film and to evaporate residual solvent, and then cooled.

column13: A clothes drying machine having a temperature sensor that may be easily repaired or replaced. The clothes drying machine includes a housing forming an external appearance of the clothes drying machine, a drying tub rotatably mounted in the housing, a hot air introducing duct to introduce hot air into the drying tub, a hot air discharging duct to discharge the hot air out of the drying tub, and a temperature sensor mounted at the front part of the hot air discharging duct to detect the temperature of the hot air passing through the hot air discharging duct. The temperature sensor is mounted at the front part of the hot air discharging duct so that an operator has easy access to the temperature sensor. Consequently, repair or replacement of the temperature sensor may be easily and conveniently performed.

column12: Power supply voltage and temperature-independent RC oscillator using controllable schmitt trigger
column13: A power supply voltage-independent and temperature-independent RC oscillator using a controllable Schmitt trigger comprises a transition voltage generator circuit, a Schmitt trigger circuit, an RC delay circuit, and a quantizer. The transition voltage generator circuit generates a high transition voltage and a low transition voltage. The high and low transition voltages are proportional to a power supply voltage. The Schmitt trigger circuit generates an output voltage having a first level when an input voltage becomes greater than the high transition voltage and having a second level when the input voltage becomes less than the low transition voltage. The RC delay circuit comprises a resistor and a capacitor and generates the input voltage in response to the output voltage. The quantizer quantizes the input voltage to output a square-wave oscillation signal. Accordingly, an oscillation signal having a stable oscillation frequency unaffected by the external conditions can be obtained.

column12: TEST SOCKET

The test socket comprises: a support sheet, made of an insulating material, which has a penetration hole in every position corresponding to the terminal of the tested device; an insertion unit including a first conductive unit which is arranged a plurality of conductive particles inside an insulating and elastic material in a thickness direction, and is arranged inside the penetration hole of the support sheet, and an elastic and insulating unit, made of an insulating and elastic material to surround the first conductive unit, which is arranged between the first conductive unit and an inner wall of the penetration hole; and an anisotropic sheet including a second conductive unit which is arranged on the lower part of the first conductive unit and in which a plurality of second conductive particles inside the insulating and elastic material is arranged in a thickness direction, and an insulating support unit which is arranged on the lower part of the support sheet to support and insulate the second conductive.

column12: CLAYMORE MINE WITH PHOTOELECTRIC CONVERSION TRIGGER
column13: Provided is a claymore with a photoelectric conversion type percussion device, comprising a transmitter photoelectric adapter (50) receiving power generated by a percussion device (30) and supplying the received power to a laser diode or a light emitting diode (LED), connected to a covered electric wire (41) formed by covering a copper or tin leading wire of a hybrid cable (40) as described hereinafter, and including a transmitter photoelectric element (LD) modularized by coupling a light emitting source (51) and one end (52) of an optical cable (42); the hybrid cable (40) including an optical cable (42) connected to the transmitter photoelectric adapter (50) to transmit light and the covered electric wire (41); a receiver photoelectric adapter (60), to which the other end (62) of the optical cable (42) and a photodiode (PD) conducted when light is irradiated thereto are coupled, and to which the hybrid cable (40) is connected, outputting electric power to an electric donator (20); the electric donator (20) operated by power output from the receiver photoelectric adapter (60); and an explosion unit (10) in which charged gunpowder is exploded according to an operation of the electric donator (20). Introduction of electric power noise is fundamentally blocked, and when electric power noise is introduced, the electric power noise can be safely released to the earth.

column12: METHOD/APPARATUS FOR TRAINING ABSOLUTE PITCH, ELECTRONIC MUSICAL INSTRUMENT, AND SOUND SOURCE PROCESSING APPARATUS
column13: The embodiments of the present invention relate to a method/apparatus for training an absolute pitch, to an electronic musical instrument, and to a sound source processing apparatus. According to one embodiment of the present invention, an absolute pitch training apparatus is provided, comprising: an output request input unit for taking, as an input, an output request for a specific sound; an overtone output unit for outputting an overtone, the number of vibrations of which is greater than the basic number of vibrations for a specific sound; and a mixture sound output unit for outputting a mixture sound in which a fundamental sound, having a basic number of vibrations, and an overtone for a specific sound are mixed. According to one embodiment of the present invention, an absolute pitch training method for training an absolute pitch is proposed, enabling persons necessarily requiring an absolute pitch to train so as to achieve an absolute pitch.

column12: Door of a drum type washer
column13: A drum type washer (1) and a door (5) thereof are provided to eliminate moisture inside a door glass (30) using natural convection. The door of the drum type washer includes a door glass (30), an inner door (40) having a holder (41) integral to the inner door to support an outer surface of the door glass (30), an outer door (20) having a support rib (21) integral to the outer door to support an inner surface of the door glass, the support rib including a hole set (24) formed in the support rib (21) such that an inside of the door glass communicates with an exterior of the drum type washer. With this configuration, the moisture created inside the door glass can be rapidly eliminated.

column12: Method for tunnel junction sensor with magnetic cladding
column13: Methods and apparatus are provided for sensing physical parameters. The apparatus (30) comprises a magnetic tunnel junction (MTJ) [32] and a magnetic field source (34) whose magnetic field (35) overlaps the MTJ and whose proximity to the MTJ varies in response to an input to the sensor. A magnetic shield (33) is provided at least on a face of the MFS away from the MTJ. The MTJ comprises first and second magnetic electrodes (36, 38) separated by a dielectric (37) configured to permit significant tunneling conduction therebetween. The first magnetic region has its spin axis pinned and the second magnetic electrode has its spin axis free. The magnetic field source is oriented closer to the second magnetic electrode than the first magnetic electrode. The overall sensor dynamic range is extended by providing multiple electrically coupled sensors receiving the same input but with different individual response curves and desirably but not essentially formed on the same substrate.

column12: Test socket
column13: The present invention relates to a test socket capable of quickly forming a high or low temperature environment condition. According to the present invention, the test socket comprises: a housing including a test connector to electrically connect a device to be tested with a testing apparatus and a reception space to receive the device to be tested, and having an opened upper part; a cover opening/closing the opened upper part of the housing; a pusher device disposed on the cover and pressing the device to be tested mounted in the housing toward the test connector; an air injection unit injecting air or coolant of a predetermined temperature into the receiving space to adjust the temperature of the receiving space; an air discharge unit discharging the air or coolant injected into the receiving space; and a sealing means sealing the receiving space from the outside when the cover closes the housing.

column12: TRANSFORMABLE CATERPILLAR
column13: The present invention relates to a transformable caterpillar. The transformable caterpillar comprises a chute plate and a compressing means. The chute plate comprises at least one hinge and at least one plate connected through the hinge and has a substantially planar shape. The compressing means applies force in the side direction of the caterpillar to allow the chute plate to be deformed. The chute plate is deformed to have a shape protruding to the upper side or the lower side of the caterpillar when force is applied in the side direction of the caterpillar by the compressing means and can be returned to the planar shape when the applied force is removed. Further, strong grounding force can be provided to a vehicle as the chute plate of the caterpillar is deformed.

column12: AC POWER CONTROLLER
column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To linearly reduce the load voltage of large capacity by means of a mutual induction reactor that has the considerably small capacity compared with the load capacity by applying selectively the output voltage of an autotransformer to the mutual induction reactor after actuating a switch array at the outputs of a current comparator and a phase comparison controller. SOLUTION: A phase comparison controller 1, a voltage variable autotransformer 2 and a voltage reducing mutual induction reactor 3 are placed at the input of a power supply. On the other hand, a voltage comparator 4 and a current comparator 5 are placed at the output of the power supply. A logical controller 6 is placed at the outputs of the comparators 4 and 5 and the controller 1 respectively. A switch array 7 is actuated by the controller 6. Then the deformed output voltage that passed through the transformer 2 and the bypass voltage that did not pass through the transformer 2 are selectively applied to the reactor 3. Thus, the output voltage of the reactor 3 can be controlled.

column12: SYSTEM, METHOD AND COMPUTER READABLE RECORDING MEDIUM FOR MANAGEMENT BY OBJECTIVES

column12: Lightning protection and grounding device for vehicle

column12: Bipolar discharge-dissipation lightning air terminals
column13: The present invention relates to a Bipolar Discharge-Dissipation Lightning Air-Terminals, and an object of the present invention is to disperse and discharge an earth charge following a thundercloud approach in a space according to electric dipole, bipolar and electric double layer principle. The above object of the present invention is achieved by providing the bipolar discharge-dissipation lightning air-terminals comprising: a base member fixed and installed in a top region of a protected object, including a coupling projection on whose inner periphery surface coupling screw grooves are formed, the coupling projection protruded and formed at a side of an upper surface of the base member, and a grounding piece formed at a side opposite to the coupling projection in order to earth a ground electrode and a grounded lightning wire; a discharge member coupled releasably to the base member, for focusing an earth charge following a thundercloud approach on the upper surface of the base member; and a potential modifying unit attached releasably on the discharge member so that the potential modifying unit is charged with different charges by electric dipole, bipolar and electric double layer principle according to the thundercloud approach to disperse and discharge the earth charge in a space separated from the discharge member.

column12: PLANE MICRO GAS SENSOR AND PRODUCTION METHOD THEREOF
column13: PURPOSE: Plane micro gas sensor and production method are provided to reduce the producing processes, to improve the uniformity of a temperature on a gas detecting film and to solve the lack of the stability. CONSTITUTION: Insulated supporting films(20a,20b) are spread on the upper part and the lower part of a p-typed silicon wafer substrate(10). The lower center of the lower insulated supporting film is removed by an anisotropy etching of the silicon through a first mask. A diaphragm window is formed in the center of the upper insulated supporting film. A heater(30a) is formed on the upper insulated supporting film. A gas detecting film(40) is shielded by the heater and heated by the heater through the upper insulated supporting film. Electrodes(30c) for the detecting film are located under the gas detecting film by forming in the upper insulated supporting film. Thereby, the unbalance of the temperature distribution in the detecting film is solved.

column12: FLAT ELECTRODE TYPE DIPOLE LIGHTNING ARRESTER
column13: PURPOSE: A planar electrode type dipole lightning arrester is provided to rapidly discharge lightning by forming a wrinkle part and a sawtooth part on a charged body. CONSTITUTION: A rod(100) of a conductive object is installed on the upper side of the object and is connected to a ground. The rod penetrates through the center of an electric charge pipe(310). A charging unit is comprised of a first cap(320) and a second cap(330) which combines the rod with both ends of the electric charge pipe. A charging plate(400) is electrically connected to the rod and is comprised of the first charge plate and the second charge plate. A third charging plate and a fourth charging plate are formed between the second charging plate and the second cap. A concavo-convex part is repeatedly formed on the fourth charging plate. A rod cap induces the lightning and is integrated with the first charging plate.

column12: CONNECTOR AND FABRICATION METHOD OF CONNECTOR
column13: The present invention relates to a connector for connection and a method to manufacture the connector for connection. More specifically, in accordance to the connector for connection which connects a port of a tested device and a pad of a test device electrically by being arranged between the test device and the tested device requiring mutual electrical connection, the present invention relates to the connector for connection comprising: a sheet member which has a plurality of through-holes on every position corresponding to a port of the tested device, and is formed with a flexible and insulating material; a connection sheet combined to the through-hole of the sheet member, and formed with a conductive electrode protruded further than an upper plane of the sheet member and a lower plane of the sheet member; and an anisotropic sheet comprising a conduction part arranged below a conductive electrode of the connection sheet, contacting the conductive electrode and having conductivity along a thickness direction, and an insulation part which supports the conduction part and insulating the conduction part. An edge of a part protruded more than a lower plane of the sheet member in the conductive electrode of the connection sheet has a round shape.

column12: DEGASSING INK BULK SYSTEM

column13: A source driving circuit includes a source driver circuit, an intermediate voltage generator, and a switching control unit. The source driver circuit receives display data and generates a source driving voltage corresponding to the received display data. ELECTRODE STRUCTURE FOR MEASURING BIO-SIGNAL AND APPARATUS FOR MEASURING ELECTROCARDIOGRAM USING THE SAME
column13: Disclosed are an electrode structure for measuring a biosignal and an apparatus for measuring an electrocardiogram using the same. The electrode structure comprises: an electrode plate which is capacitively coupled with a skin surface of a body to acquire a biosignal; a humidity absorption layer formed on one side of the electrode plate; and a first stage amplifier which is electrically connected to the electrode plate, filters a noise from the biosignal inputted through the electrode plate, amplifies the biosignal, and outputs the amplified biosignal. The apparatus for measuring an electrocardiogram comprises: first and second electrodes which adopt a configuration of the electrode structure and measure a biosignal; a differential measurement amplifier, which receives output signals from the first and second electrodes and amplifies a difference between the output signals; a signal processing unit which receives an output signal from the differential measurement amplifier, filters a noise from the output signal, and outputs the filtered signal; and a wireless sensor node which performs analog-digital conversion on an output signal from the signal processing unit and wirelessly transmits the converted result. According to this configuration, an initial noise stabilization time is reduced, and stable electrocardiogram signals are obtained without noise within a short period of time.

column12: Reducing coupling noise in an output driver
column13: An output driver may reduce coupling noise. The output driver may include a first transistor, a second transistor, and/or a noise-eliminating portion. The first transistor may have a first terminal connected to a first voltage, a second terminal connected to a first node, and a gate to which data is applied. The second transistor may have a first terminal connected to the first node and a second terminal connected to an output node. The noise-eliminating portion may be connected between the gate of the first transistor and a gate of the second transistor. The noise-eliminating portion may be a capacitor. The capacitor may substantially eliminate coupling noise introduced at the gate of the second transistor, due to coupling capacitance between the gate of the second transistor and the output node and coupling capacitance between the gate of the second transistor and the first node, by using the data applied to the gate of the first transistor.

column12: Amplifier with a voltage-controlled quiescent current and output current
column13: An amplifier capable of controlling the magnitudes of quiescent and output current, using externally supplied voltages. The amplifier includes: an input circuit converting a voltage difference between input signals into a current; an output circuit outputting an output current to the outside of the (class AB) amplifier (in response to a change in voltages at the first and second output nodes of the input circuit); a first control circuit generating a first bias current (when a first control voltage is applied), and a first control current; and a second control circuit generating a second bias current (whose magnitude is less than that of the first bias current) when a second control voltage is applied, and a second control current. In a first operating mode the first bias current controls the magnitude of quiescent flowing through the output circuit. The first control circuit and the output circuit form a current mirror. In a second operating mode, the first and second control circuits change the magnitudes of the first and second control currents so as to control the magnitude of the output current. The magnitudes of quiescent current and output current can be easily controlled, and the amplifier can operate stably regardless of external manufacturing process change since there are a few circuit parameter variations.

column12: FBG Direct reading instrument using FBG sensor and industrial control system using the same
column13: The present invention relates to an industrial control facility technique and, more specifically, to a direct-reading instrument using an FBG sensor and an industrial control system using the same, which can greatly improve the safety of an industrial site. The industrial control system comprises: a plurality of direct-reading instruments installed at a site of the inside and outside of a dangerous area; an FBG interrogate for receiving measurement values as optical signals from the direct-reading instruments; a controller for controlling site facilities by receiving data of the FBG interrogate; and an actuator for controlling the operating state of the site facilities in accordance with a control signal of the controller. According to one embodiment of the present invention, the direct-reading instrument comprises: a temperature sensing unit for sensing the temperature of site facilities; a temperature indication unit for displaying a sensing value of the temperature sensing unit as an indication to observe the sensing value with naked eyes; an FBG sensor for detecting a displacement amount of the temperature indication unit as an optical signal; a housing for accommodating parts and providing an observation window for viewing an indication value of the temperature indication unit with naked eyes; and an optical port formed on the housing to connect an optical signal to the FBG sensor. The temperature measurement values of the site facilities are displayed to be observed at the site with naked eyes, and the measurement values can be transmitted as optical signals.

column12: Expansion of searching technology by index
column13: PURPOSE: The extending method of a searching function using a classification is provided to obtain only the searching data closer to a desired result through the searching for an item within a desired interesting field by using a keyword and the classification information at the same time. CONSTITUTION: A screen making a user conveniently use a keyword index and the searching at the same time is inserted into an initial screen or is popped up as a popup screen. When outputting the searching result, the user adds the keyword and a classification searching standard to the screen and selects an output form from a present sorting order and the sorting order arranged by each classification. In case of the classification arrangement, the searching result is outputted faster. Because the desired items are outputted to one position, the fast movement to the desired result is possible by applying the movement using a tree.

column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a misfire detecting method for a vehicular engine for sensing a misfire and determining a misfired cylinder by correcting a reference value for sensing and determining the misfire and a reference phase angle range for sectioning the misfired cylinder. SOLUTION: The method comprises a sensor characteristic measuring step of measuring the change of signals from a wide-range oxygen sensor before and after a reduction in fuel injection amount, a reference value correcting step of correcting the reference value for determining the misfire according to the measured change of the signals from the wide-range oxygen sensor, a phase angle range correcting step of correcting the reference phase angle range for discriminating the misfired cylinder, a misfire determining step of determining the occurrence of the misfire when exceeding the range, a phase difference calculating step of calculating a phase difference between the secondary peaks of rates of change of the signals from the wide-range oxygen sensor, and a cylinder discriminating step of discriminating the misfired cylinder.

column12: System and method for characterizing solar cell conversion performance and detecting defects in a solar cell
column13: A system and method for characterizing the solar cell conversion performance and detecting a defect in a solar cell includes applying an optical test signal to the solar cell using the multiple-scanning method, measuring the solar cell photocurrent in response to the solar cell illumination by the multiple-scanning method, and detecting a defect and finding its location based on the characteristic mapping of solar cell photocurrent, which is obtained by the multiple-scanning method through the divisional control of light transmittance by the LVP (light valve panel). The defect may be a solar cell subsection which has abnormally low photocurrent below a critical value and can be caused by a short between the emitter and the base of solar cell. The LVP may be realized in any one of a variety of ways. For example, the LVP may be a flat-panel display such as AMLCD (Active-Matrix Liquid Crystal Display) and AMOLED (Active-Matrix Organic Light Emitting Diode).

Data receiver and data receiving method using signal integration
column13: A data receiver and data receiving method using signal integration and capable of reducing high-frequency noises generated upon high-speed data detection. The data receiver includes an integration amplification circuit receiving at least two differential reference signals and N (where N is a natural number greater than zero) data signals and integrating and amplifying differences between the at least two differential reference signals and one or more of the N data signals and outputting at least first differential signals and at least second differential signals and a detection amplification circuit for receiving the at least first differential signals and the at least second differential signals and detecting a difference between the at least first differential signals and the at least second differential signals to detect a value of one or more of the N data signals. The data receiver and data receiving method, using signal integration, can reduce high-frequency noises generated when data is detected at a high speed. The data receiver and data receiving method, where signals inputted through two reference signal lines and one data line are integrated and amplified to detect data, provide accurate data detection at a high speed using differential signaling, irrespective of changes in a process, voltage level, or temperature.

column12: MULTI-TYPE ACTIVITY MONITORING SYSTEM
column13: PURPOSE: A multi-type activity monitoring system is provided to prevent missing children and monitoring children within a certain range by continuously monitoring motion state and position of the children to take a necessary steps if any problems happen in the position or motion of the children by generating a warning signal wirelessly. CONSTITUTION: A multi-type activity monitoring system includes at least one motion state monitoring part(3) for sensing at least one of motion, temperature, pulse or environmental sound of an object to transmit the sensed one with an intrinsic code via an antenna after processing the sensed one to a living body activity data, and a central controlling and monitoring bureau(1) for recognizing a living body state and observation range from the transmitted living body activity data to generate a normal or warning signal.

column12: Lightning arrester
column13: Provided is a lightning arrester capable of preventing damage caused by a lightning by discharging charges charged by approach of a thundercloud. The lightning arrester includes: a conductive rod installed at an upper part of an object to be protected from a lightning and connected to a ground part; a charge pipe having a cylindrical shape, formed of an insulating body to be insulated from the rod, and electrically charged with charges having a polarity opposite to ground charges; and a plurality of charge pins disposed on the charge pipe such that space charges in the air are charged to the pins by a thundercloud.

column12: Current mode output driver
column13: A current mode output driver and output current control method of controlling an output current using a gate voltage are provided. The current mode output driver, which outputs data read from a memory core to a transmission line, includes a gate voltage control circuit, a bias circuit, and a driver circuit. The gate voltage control circuit generates a predetermined gate voltage in response to a current control signal. The bias circuit outputs the gate voltage as a first enable signal in an active mode, and outputs a ground voltage as a second enable signal in a standby mode. The driver circuit drives a predetermined output current in response to the first enable signal, outputs the predetermined output voltage to the transmission line according to the data, and stops its operation in response to the second enable signal. The gate voltage control circuit changes the level of the gate voltage according to a value of the current control signal and output the changed result. Therefore, it is possible to easily increase resolution of an output current and reduce the occupied area of the current mode output driver, thereby facilitating a circuit design.

column12: Reinforcement-Plate of Marble for a Structure
column13: PURPOSE: A reinforcement plate of stone for building structure is provided to reduce the weight while maintaining the strength of the stone by the reinforcement plate, reduce the cost of stone in constructing the building structure, and improve the construction performance by the reduced weight. CONSTITUTION: In a reinforcement plate(120a) of stone for interior decoration and facing of a building structure, the reinforcement plate having the same size as the stone comprises a square plane plate(121). Plural holes(121a) are bored in the square plane plate. The plane plate is combined to the outer wall or the inner wall or the bottom surface of the stone and the building structure by a binder. Protrusions(121b) and uneven grooves(121c) are formed to the outer surface of the reinforcement plate.

column13: A system and method of monitoring LCD production yields, predicting the effects of different testing methodologies on LCD production yields, optimizing production yields, and detecting defects in TFT-array panels is provided that compares the effect of different testing methodologies on the yields at various stages in the LCD testing and assembly process. The present invention can also be used to predict the effect of different testing methodologies on user-defined parameters, such as profit. The present invention can also detect defects in TFT-array panels with improved defect detection accuracy.

column12: CONNECTOR FOR ELECTRICAL CONNECTION
column13: The invention provides a connector for electrical connection. The connector is arranged between a detection device and detected equipment. The connector comprises a signal conductive part, a grounding conductive part and a metal frame part. The signal conductive part comprises a transmission part and an insulation part. The conveying part is composed of a plurality of first conductive particles which are in conductive contact in the vertical direction. The insulating portion is integrally formed with the conveying portion so as to surround the conveying portion in a horizontal direction perpendicular to the vertical direction, and a thickness of the insulating portion in the horizontal direction is greater than a maximum width of the conveying portion in the horizontal direction. The ground conductive portion is spaced apart from the signal conductive portion in a horizontal direction. The metal frame part separates the signal conductive part and the grounding conductive part in the vertical direction and the horizontal direction, and is electrically connected with the grounding conductive part.

column12: AUTO DETECTING SYSTEM OF P.C.B. USING CAMERA
column13: A circuit board (1) to be inspected and having a plurality of holes is scanned using a camera (2) to obtain an image of the board (1) and to detect the position of holes on the image, with the circuit board (1) being placed on an inspecting position. Then the height and the positional angle of the camera (2) relative to the circuit board (2) are roughly determined to set up initial values of the height range and the angular range of the camera (2). Then the world coordinate of the camera (2) is converted into the camera lens coordinate to convert it into an image coordinate. Then a conversion parameter is obtained by substituting the image coordinate into the initial values of the camera (2). Then the difference between the actual and extracted positions of the image is obtained, and the image position is determined based on the difference.

column12: Flat Passband Arrayed Waveguide Grating Wavelength Router Based on Fourier Optics and Misaligned Waveguides
column13: PURPOSE: An optical waveguide string grating router is provided to accomplish an electro-optical network with a high reliability by obtaining flat pass band characteristics. CONSTITUTION: A grating router includes an input waveguide(101) for inputting optical wave, the first slap waveguide(102) for branching the input optical wave, an optical waveguide string having a predetermined path difference, the second slap waveguide(105) and an output waveguide(106). A transform section(103) is constituted by the first section where a dislocated waveguide is employed so as to damp the incident optical wave, the second section where an optical waveguide corresponding to a half-wave length is added so as to transform the optical wave into the wave having a distribution of sinc function through the dislocated waveguide and phase inversion, and the third section where a dislocated waveguide is employed. Thus-constituted transform section is interposed between the first slap waveguide string and the second slap waveguide string of the optical waveguide string.

column12: Alternating current power control device
column13: An alternating current power control device comprising a phase comparison controller for comparing a phase of an input voltage with that of a first reference voltage, a single-winding transformer for varying the input voltage, a mutual induction reactor for lowering the input voltage by a desired level in response to an output voltage from the single-winding transformer, an output voltage comparator for comparing an output voltage with a second reference voltage, an output current comparator for comparing an output current with a reference current, an OR logic controller for performing an OR operation with respect to output signals from the phase comparison controller and output current comparator, and a switch array for selectively transferring the output voltage from the single-winding transformer to the mutual induction reactor in response to output signals from the output voltage comparator and OR logic controller. According to the present invention, the mutual induction reactor is implemented on the basis of the principle of a linear transformer and has a small capacity corresponding to about 1/10 of a load power. Therefore, a proper power necessary to the saving of energy can be supplied by using the mutual induction reactor. <IMAGE>

column13: 본 개시의 일 측면에 따르면, 사용자 특징을 지시하는 태그를 생성하기 위한 장치가 제공될 수 있다. 본 개시에 따른 장치는, 하나 이상의 프로세서 및 상기 하나 이상의 프로세서에 의한 실행 시, 상기 하나 이상의 프로세서가 연산을 수행하도록 하는 명령들이 저장된 하나 이상의 메모리를 포함하고, 상기 하나 이상의 프로세서는, 상기 명령에 따라, 복수의 사용자 각각에 대한 사용자 정보 및 상기 복수의 사용자 각각에 대한 결제 정보를 획득하고, 상기 사용자 정보 및 상기 결제 정보에 기초하여, 상기 복수의 사용자 각각에 대해 하나 이상의 1차 태그를 생성하고 - 상기 하나 이상의 1차 태그는 하나 이상의 1차 사용자 특징을 각각 지시하고, 상기 하나 이상의 1차 사용자 특징 각각은 상기 사용자 정보 및 상기 결제 정보 중 적어도 하나에 의해 특정됨 - , 상기 복수의 사용자 중에서 미리 결정된 표본 사용자 그룹 내 표본 사용자 각각에 대한 하나 이상의 1차 태그에 기초하여, 상기 복수의 사용자 각각과 상기 표본 사용자 그룹 사이의 유사도를 결정하고, 상기 유사도에 기초하여, 상기 복수의 사용자 각각에 대해 2차 태그를 생성 - 상기 2차 태그는 상기 표본 사용자 그룹과 관련되 2차 사용자 특징을 지시함 - 할 수 있다.

column12: METHOD OF PRODUCING SEMI-CIRCULAR GLASS TUBE FOR ELECTRODELESS CIRCULAR LAMP
column13: PURPOSE: A method for manufacturing a semi-circular glass tube for an electrode-less circular lamp is provided to prevent the sagging phenomenon or twisting phenomenon of the glass tube by fixing the glass tube to be surrounded by a heating furnace. CONSTITUTION: A method for manufacturing a semi-circular glass tube for an electrode-less circular lamp includes the following: A linear glass tube(10a) is prepared. The glass tube is fixed to a heating furnace(20) such that the entire longitudinal direction of the glass tube is heated. The heated glass tube is loaded at a die, and air is injected to form a semi-circular glass tube. The semi-circular glass tube includes a bending part and a sealing part. The sealing part is formed at both end parts of the bending part. The diameter of the sealing part is smaller than that of the bending part.

column12: APPARATUS FOR HANDLING EMERGENCY BROADCASTING IN TELEVISION AND METHOD THEREFOR
column13: A device and a method for processing emergency broadcasting on television are provided to receive emergency broadcasting in a state that an unnecessary set-top box is not connected, by installing a high frequency modem and an emergency broadcasting processing algorithm inside the television, thereby reducing cost. A tuner(246) of a television converts high frequency signals of general broadcasting frequency into audible aural signals and visible video signals. If signals of a specific communication frequency modulating digital communication data into high frequency signals are demodulated into digital communication data to be transmitted to a TV CPU(248), the TV CPU compares whether the digital communication data accords with an address recorded at an EEPROM(Electrically Erasable and Programmable Read Only Memory)(254) embedded in the television. If so, a two-way high frequency modem(242) executes a command of the transmitted digital communication data and modulates data of the result and digital data of a current television state into inversely transmittable specific high frequency to transmit the modulated high frequency to a two-way splitter(240). The TV CPU is installed in the television inside for controlling to display emergency broadcasting when the emergency broadcasting is inputted. The EEPROM has basic address information needed when the TV CPU loads, and includes an address required for emergency broadcasting. If the emergency broadcasting is inputted, a switch unit(256) is controlled by the TV CPU for turning on or off the television, connecting the emergency broadcasting signals with stopping signals broadcasted on the television to send out emergency broadcasting. If the emergency broadcasting is terminated, the switch unit connects the previous broadcasting to send out the previous broadcasting.

column12: SOURCE DRIVER, COMMON VOLTAGE DRIVER, AND METHOD OF DRIVING DISPLAY DEVICE USING TIME DIVISION DRIVING METHOD
column13: A source driver and a common voltage driver for a display device using a time division driving method, in which the source driver outputs an analog voltage corresponding to digital image data to a corresponding source line out of a plurality of source lines, after precharging the corresponding source line with a predetermined voltage. The common voltage driver discretely and sequentially increases or decreases the common voltage. By using the source driver and the common voltage driver, the power consumed upon driving of the display device can be reduced.

column12: PLASMA GUN AND PLASMA PROCESSING APPARATUS HAVING THE SAME
column13: PURPOSE: A plasma gun and a plasma processing apparatus including the same are provided to increase the lifetime of an electrode and reduce the number of process halts for electrode replacement. CONSTITUTION: A plasma gun(130) includes a housing(131), an electrode(132) and a gas supply unit(133). The housing having a cylindrical shape includes a first end part including an opening part and a second end part on the opposite side of the first end part. The electrode arranged inside the housing performs a main discharge in a gap with an anode through the opening part by supplying electric power. The gas supply unit supplies plasma generating gas inside the housing. The electrode consists of pieces formed by separating a disk having a penetration hole in the center into two or more pieces. The gas supply unit has a pipe shape extended to the first end part from the second end part of the housing and makes an end part penetrate the penetration hole.

column12: Apparatus for inspecting camera module
column13: The present invention relates to a camera module inspecting device, capable of fixing a camera module by pushing the camera module by the driving of a pneumatic cylinder and enabling a pogo block to be in contact with the camera module. Specifically, the camera module inspecting device includes: a base plate having a camera module mounting unit, wherein the camera module is mounted, and a pogo pin block which can move between a position coming into contact with the side of the camera module mounted on the camera module mounting unit and a position separated from the camera module; a pair of cam plates fixed to the base plate and separated from each other to face each other, wherein the a pair of cam plates is extended to be far from the camera module mounting unit and is erected to the upper side; the pneumatic cylinder installed between the pair of cam plates and ascending/descending on the base plate; a load block capable of moving forward to be adjacent to the camera module along an extension path of a cam hole installed in the cam plate by driving of the pneumatic cylinder; and a tension block moving forward with the load block by being elastically supported on the load block and fixing the camera module to the camera module mounting unit by pushing the camera module by descending while a distance from the load block is reduced, wherein a forward movement of the tension block is controlled when coming into contact with a stopper unit installed in the cam plate. column12: System and method for classifying defects in and identifying process problems for an electrical circuit
column13: A method for performing circuit defect analysis and process problem identification includes applying a test signal to a circuit, obtaining a signal generated in response to the test signal, comparing the response signal to reference information, classifying a defect in the circuit based on a result of the comparing step, and identifying a problem in a manufacturing process which caused the defect based on the classification. The reference information may include one or more signal profiles corresponding to predefined types of defects that can occur during the manufacturing process. Defect classification is preferably performed by determining whether the response signal falls within one or more of the signal profiles. If the response signal falls within two or more signal profiles, then probabilities may be determined for each profile. The defect may then be classified as corresponding to the defect type whose signal profile has the highest probability. A processing system performs defect classification and process problem identification using a similar approach.

The present invention is particularly suited for the testing of TFT-array panels that contain more pixels than can be measured by the sensor of the TFT-array tester in a single measurement. The system and method of the present invention calculates a reference pixel voltage at each pixel based on a low frequency component of the measured pixel voltage, and adjusts the thresholding parameters based on the calculated reference pixel voltage.

column12: RC OSCILLATOR UTILIZING CONTROLLABLE SCHMIDT TRIGGER AND REGARDLESS OF POWER SUPPLY VOLTAGE AND TEMPERATURE
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide an RC oscillator utilizing a controllable Schmidt trigger and regardless of a power supply voltage and a temperature.

SOLUTION: The RC oscillator utilizing the controllable Schmidt trigger and regardless of the power supply voltage and the temperature is provided with a transition voltage generating circuit, a Schmidt trigger circuit, an RC delay circuit and a quantizer. The transition voltage generating circuit generates a high transition voltage and a low transition voltage proportional to the power supply voltage. The Schmidt trigger circuit generates an output voltage of a first level when an input voltage is increased equally with or higher than the high transition voltage, or generates an output voltage of a second level when the input voltage is decreased lower than or equally with the low transition voltage. The RC delay circuit includes a resistor and a capacitor and generates an input voltage in response to the output voltage. The quantizer outputs an oscillated signal in the form of a rectangular wave by quantizing the input voltage. Thus, the oscillated signal having an oscillation frequency independent and stable in a change of an external condition such as the power supply voltage or the temperature is obtained.

column12: Adaptive input voltage controlled voltage booster
column13: Provided is a voltage booster adaptively controlled by an input voltage. The voltage booster includes an Operational Transconductance Amplifier (OTA) having positive and negative input terminals and generating an output current in response to a voltage difference between the positive and negative input terminals. The positive input terminal of the OTA receives a voltage obtained by dividing a target output voltage of the voltage booster by n, and the negative input terminal of the OTA receives a voltage obtained by dividing an output voltage of the voltage booster by n. The output current of the OTA charges an input capacitor to generate a first input voltage. A buffer receives the first input voltage and outputs a second input voltage. The second input voltage is input to a voltage boosting unit to generate the output voltage having a voltage equal to n times the second input voltage, where n≧1.

A pixel electrode is connected to a region of the drain which is not overlapped with the gate electrode and positioned at the inner side of the region forming the data line and the gate electrode.

column12: VISCOSITY SENSOR USING SOLENOID
column13: An oil viscosity sensor is provided to improve efficiency and reduce cost of measurement by using a solenoid and orifice-type cylinders rather than quartz. An oil viscosity sensor(100) using a solenoid(16) comprises as follows. An oil cylinder(10) is equipped with an oil inlet and an oil outlet at both ends thereof. A plunger(14) is positioned inside the oil cylinder and reciprocates vertically. A drive unit is mounted on the upper portion of the plunger and moves the plunger up and down. A capacitance sensing unit is attached to the inner surface of the oil cylinder. A smart circuit(22) is coupled to first and second capacitive probes(18,20) to exchange signals with each other.

column12: CLOTHING DRYER
MINDMAP SYSTEM USING MOBIL-PHONE AND METHOD THEREOF
column13: A mind map system using a mobile communication terminal and a service method therefor are provided to conveniently store information which constitutes a mind map in a web server regardless of time and place by using the terminal, so that a user can receive the mind map by accessing the web server with a user terminal. A mobile communication terminal(100) transmits mind map information inputted according to a user's operation to an MO(Message Oriented) server(120). The MO server(120) receives the mind map information to transmit the received information to a web server(140). The web server(140) receives the mind map information to convert into mind map configuration information as storing the converted information, and extracts the mind map configuration information according to a downloading request for the configuration information sent from a user terminal(150), then sends the extracted information to the user terminal(150). The user terminal(150) receives the configuration information by requesting downloading of the configuration information, and configures/displays a mind map by using the received configuration information. The mind map information consists of one character message, and the character message includes at least one identification code, which designates at least one mind map data and a position where each kind of mind map data is indicated on the mind map.

column12: Washing machine detecting condensed water temperature and drying control method of the same
column13: Disclosed herein are a washing machine with a drying unit and a drying control method of the same that is capable of controlling a drying time based on a temperature of condensed water used during a drying operation to accomplish optimum drying efficiency. The drying control method includes detecting the temperature of condensed water supplied during drying the laundry, setting the drying time based on the detected temperature of the condensed water, and operating the drying unit according to the set drying time to perform a drying operation.

column12: METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR GENERATING MULTI-SCALE FEATURE-BASED TRANSFORMER MODELS
column13: 멀티 스케일 특징 기반의 트랜스포머 모델 생성 방법 및 장치가 개시된다. 멀티 스케일 특징 기반의 트랜스포머 모델 생성 방법은 오디오 신호의 특징맵에 대한 차원 축소를 수행한 후, 트랜스포머 인코더를 적용하는 베이스라인 트랜스포머를 생성하는 단계; 컨볼루션 블록과 결합된 트랜스포머 인코더들을 이용하여 상기 특징맵의 멀티 스케일 특징을 추출하는 멀티-스케일 추출 모듈을 생성하는 단계; 상기 멀티-스케일 추출 모듈의 출력에 기초하여 상기 오디오 신호의 오디오 클래스를 분류하는 분류 레이어를 생성하는 단계; 및 상기 베이스라인 트랜스포머, 상기 멀티-스케일 추출 모듈, 및 상기 분류 레이어를 결합하여 멀티 스케일 특징 기반의 트랜스포머 모델을 생성하는 단계를 포함할 수 있다.

column12: SCANNING LIDAR APPARATUS AND METHOD APPLIED THERETO
column13: A scanning lidar apparatus is disclosed. The scanning lidar apparatus according to the present invention comprises: a laser unit for oscillating a laser signal toward a specific area in a surrounding space and receiving the laser signal; a first rotation unit for rotating the laser unit on a first horizontal surface; a position adjustment unit for adjusting an angle between the first horizontal surface on which the laser unit and the first rotation unit are positioned and a second horizontal surface which is a scanning reference surface; a plate for forming the second horizontal surface, and supporting one side of the first rotation unit and one side of the position adjustment unit; and a second rotation unit for rotating the plate on the second horizontal surface.

column12: CONTROL METHOD OF WASHING MACHINE HAVING DRYING DEVICE
column13: A method for controlling a washing machine having a dryer is provided to improve dry performance, and to reduce the power consumption by operating a drain pump for a longer time as an amount of clothes increases. A method for controlling a washing machine having a dryer comprises the steps: sensing an amount of clothes(S120); and repeatedly turning on and turning off a drain pump in accordance with the sensed weight of clothes for draining water(S150).

column12: Method and server readable recording medium for associating schedule information with mind map
column13: The invention provides a method for associating schedule information of an electronic diary with a mind map, and a server for providing a program for performing the same. The method for associating schedule information of the electronic diary with the mind map performed by an electronic diary device, including: (a) a step of providing an electronic diary interface displaying the schedule information; and (b) a step of associating the schedule information with the mind map in the case in which association between the schedule information displayed on the electronic diary interface and the mind map is requested.

column12: FUSE OF SEMICONDUCTOR DEVICE AND METHOD FOR FORMING THE SAME
column13: PURPOSE: A fuse of a semiconductor device and a method for forming the same are provided to improve the property and reliability of a semiconductor device by improving the property of a fuse in a blowing process to increase the margin of a repair process. CONSTITUTION: The fuse(33) of a fuse connection part(100), connected to the fuse either side of a fuse blowing region, is formed into a zig-zag type. The fuse of the fuse connection part and the fuse o the fuse blowing region(200) are formed with copper. The fuse of the fuse connection part has a dimension which is within 1/7 and 1 of the dimension of the fuse blowing region.

The marketing server transmits display information of the product object from the user terminal. The marketing server transmits occupiable display information and provides a benefit set to the product object. column12: ROTATING DEVICE OF MICRO ANTENNA FOR VEHICLES AND ROTATING CONTROL METHOD THEREROF
column13: A rotating device of a micro antenna for a vehicle and a rotating control method thereof are provided to improve receiving performance of a vehicle radio by rotating a direction of the micro antenna according to a running direction of the vehicle. A rotating device of a micro antenna(30) for a vehicle includes the micro antenna, a gyro sensor, and an audio device. The micro antenna is rotated by a driving motor(34) inside. The gyro sensor detects and outputs a running direction of the vehicle. The audio device measures receiving sensitivity according to a direction of the micro antenna, drives the driving motor based on the measured receiving sensitivity to direct the micro antenna toward a direction with the optimum receiving sensitivity, and drives the driving motor according to the running direction of the vehicle outputted from the gyro sensor to rotate the direction of the micro antenna.

column12: Test socket and conductive particle
column13: The present invention relates to a test socket and, more specifically, relates to the test socket which is disposed between a test target device and a test device and electrically connects a terminal of the test target device and a pad of the test device. The test socket comprises: a plurality of conductive portions which are disposed to be separated but facing at each position corresponding to the terminal of the test target device, and are provided with a plurality of conductive particles arranged in a thickness direction in an elastic insulation material; and an insulation support portion which is disposed among the conductive portions separated from each other, supports each conductive portion, and insulates the facing conductive portions. The conductive particle includes a body portion, and two or more protrusions protruding from the upper end of the body portion. A groove portion recessed toward the body portion is provided between the adjacent protruding portions, and the angle between the facing inner surfaces in the adjacent protruding portions have an acute angle less than 90.

column12: Large-sized exterior awning device for high-rise building
column13: The present invention comprises: a winch (100) provided to an upper story, the roof or the ground of a high-rise building, and releasing or winding up a cable (110); two guide wires (200) connected to a lower story or the ground of the high-rise building from the upper story or the roof of the high-rise building, and spaced apart at a predetermined distance to be provided in parallel; a plurality of raising and lowering rods (300) provided in the horizontal direction, and provided with, at each of the left and right end portions thereof, wire-passing holes (310) through which the guide wires (200) pass such that the raising and lowering rods are raised and lowered along the guide wires (200); and an awning (400) coupled to the raising and lowering rods (300), and unfolded so as to block the sunlight when the raising and lowering rods (300) are spaced apart from each other while being raised or lowered, wherein the cable (110) is connected to the uppermost or lowermost raising and lowering rod (300) among the raising and lowering rods (300).

column12: IMAGE SENSOR COMPRISING MOS STRUCTURE WITH GATE ELECTRODE WHICH IS TRANSMITTING LIGHT
column13: An image sensor with an MOS structure including a gate electrode to transmit light is provided to enhance a dynamic range of the image sensor by increasing a measurable light intensity range using a transmissive gate electrode. An image sensor includes a photodiode. A transmissive conductive layer(41) and a dielectric layer(44) are arranged on a substrate of the photodiode adjacent to a diffusion region(40) of the photodiode. A constant gate voltage is applied to the conductive layer. The photodiode is a pn-junction diode. Alternatively, the photodiode is a pinned diode. The transmissive conductive layer is made of a transparent or semi-transparent conductive material. The conductive layer and the dielectric layer form a MOS(Metal Oxide Semiconductor) capacitor structure with the substrate of the photodiode. The image sensor includes plural MOS capacitor structures.

column12: Mobilephone Electromagnetic-wave Absorbing and Shielding Double Shieldcase
column13: PURPOSE: A double sealed case in a mobile telephone is provided to extinguish or reduce damage to a head by absorbing and shielding effect of an electromagnetic wave radiated from a body output section to the head through a double sealed case installed in the body output section. CONSTITUTION: A front case(11) of a mobile telephone has a function selecting button and an LCD protective panel. A circuit board(12) includes an LCD panel being operated by the function selecting button, a number of control elements, a main output unit for transceiving a radio wave and an antenna. A rear case(13) is connected to a rear side of the circuit board(12) and assembled with a battery. A dual sealed case is manufactured of a shielding metal for absorbing and shielding electromagnetic waves which are radiated from a radio wave output section and radiated to a head of a human body.

column12: ELECTRODELESS DISCHARGE LAMP LUMINAIRE FOR CEILING
column13: PURPOSE: An electrodeless lighting device is provided to prevent the damage of an electrodeless lamp by installing an electrodeless lamp to the inner wall of a reflector. CONSTITUTION: A stabilizer box(30) stores a stabilizer. A device body(50) is arranged under the stabilizer box. The device body comprises an upper plate, a reflector, and an electrodeless lamp. A lamp mounting bracket is arranged in the inner wall of the reflector. The electrodeless lamp is installed in the lamp mounting bracket. A connecting member(70) interlinks the stabilizer box and the device body. The connecting member includes three space fastening components.

column12: Alternating current power control device
column13: An alternating current power control device comprising a phase comparison controller for comparing a phase of an input voltage with that of a first reference voltage, a single-winding transformer for varying the input voltage, a mutual induction reactor for lowering the input voltage by a desired level in response to an output voltage from the single-winding transformer, an output voltage comparator for comparing an output voltage with a second reference voltage, an output current comparator for comparing an output current with a reference current, an OR logic controller for performing an OR operation with respect to output signals from the phase comparison controller and output current comparator, and a switch array for selectively transferring the output voltage from the single-winding transformer to the mutual induction reactor in response to output signals from the output voltage comparator and OR logic controller. According to the present invention, the mutual induction reactor is implemented on the basis of the principle of a linear transformer and has a small capacity corresponding to about 1/10 of a load power. Therefore, a proper power necessary to the saving of energy can be supplied by using the mutual induction reactor.

column12: Pusher apparatus
column13: The present invention relates to a pusher device, and more particularly, to a pusher device for pressing terminals of an inspected device to an inspection device, which comprises a housing, a valve structure, and a pressurizing means. The housing comprises: a pusher accommodating space disposed at the center and opened downward; a valve accommodating space disposed adjacent to the pusher accommodating space and capable of accommodating the valve structure; an inlet passage having one end connected to an external air inlet and the other end connected to the valve accommodating space; a discharge passage having one end connected to the outside and the other end connected to the valve accommodating space; and a connection passage having one end connected to the valve accommodating space and the other end connected to the pusher accommodating space. The valve structure selectively communicates the connection passage to one of inlet passage and the discharge passage. When the inlet passage and the connection passage are communicated and air is introduced into the pusher accommodating space from the air inlet, the pressurizing means can pressurize the inspected device to the inspection device by contacting the inspected device by descending by air pressure. The valve structure and the pressurizing means are arranged in a single housing. The valve structure and the pressurizing means are disposed in a single housing so that the space for inspecting a semiconductor device can be minimized.

column12: TWO-PHASE REACTOR FOR MANUFACTURING OF HYDROGEN PEROXIDE AND METHOD FOR MANUFACTURING HYDROGEN PEROXIDE USING THE SAME
column13: The present invention relates to an abnormal reactor for manufacturing hydrogen peroxide, and a method for manufacturing hydrogen peroxide using an abnormal reactor for manufacturing hydrogen peroxide. According to an embodiment of the present invention, the abnormal reactor for manufacturing hydrogen peroxide comprises an oil reaction unit, a water reaction unit, and a connection unit. According to the present invention, the abnormal reactor for manufacturing hydrogen peroxide, and the method for manufacturing hydrogen peroxide using an abnormal reactor for manufacturing hydrogen peroxide can improve manufacturing efficiency of hydrogen peroxide.

A COMPACTOR FOR GROUND TAMPING
column13: PURPOSE: A compactor for compaction of the ground is provided to improve durability while reducing the diameter of a bearing and to improve the number of rotation of a rotator. CONSTITUTION: A compactor for compaction of the ground comprises housing(110), a compaction plate member(120), a support cover unit(130), and a rotation support unit(150). A rotator(140) is accommodated into the housing. The compaction plate member is connected to the bottom surface of the housing and comes into contact with the ground. The support cover unit comprises a first support cover(131) and a second support cover(133), and the first support cover and the second support cover comprise side support members(131a,133a) and connection hole units(131b,133b). The support cover unit is individually connected to both sides of the housing in order to support both ends of the rotator. The rotation support unit supports rotation of the rotator and comprises a ball bearing member(151) and a roller bearing member(153).

column12: BEARING SUPPORT SYSTEM FOR THE POWER DRIVE SHAFT
LADLE OF STEEL MAKING
column13: Disclosed is a steelmaking ladle which easily reduces a variation of components and temperature of a molten steel. According to an embodiment of the present invention, the steelmaking ladle comprises: on a bottom, a bubble generating member to accommodate molten steel tapped from an electric arc furnace, and forming an upward air stream necessary to stir the accommodated molten steel.

column12: MANUFACTURING METHOD FOR HIGH VOLTAGE DEVICE IN ELECTRICALLY ERASABLE PROGRAMMABLE READ ONLY MEMORY
column13: A method for fabricating a high voltage device in an EEPROM is provided to eliminate the necessity for additionally performing a plurality of cleaning processes by introducing an etch process for adjusting the thickness of a gate oxide layer of a high voltage device. A high voltage device formation region, a cell formation region and a logic device formation region are defined in a substrate(1), and a floating gate is formed in the cell formation region of the substrate. A high-voltage gate oxide layer(9) made of a dual layer is deposited on the resultant structure. The high-voltage gate oxide layer deposited in the logic device formation region is etched by a photolithography process. A photoresist pattern is formed in the logic device formation region, and an upper part of the high-voltage gate oxide layer formed in the high-voltage device formation region and the cell formation region is etched by using an HF solution of 1:99 to adjust the thickness of the gate oxide layer. The photoresist pattern is removed, and a logic gate oxide layer(11) is formed in an exposed logic device formation region. An electrode material is deposited on the resultant structure and is patterned to form a high voltage gate in the high voltage device region.

column12: Method of detecting engine misfiring
column13: A control system for an internal combustion engine monitors the variation of the oxygen content in the exhaust system and relates the measurements to individual cylinders and to timing angles for each cylinder. The variation of the maxima of the oxygen levels are compared with reference values to determine persistent misfirings. This enables the engine management system to correct the control e.g. vary the fuel/air mixture. An Independent claim is also included for a system for detecting engine misfiring.

column12: VIBRO GRAB FOR TREE
column13: The present invention relates to a vibration machine for trees, comprising: a main body having a vibrator; tongs part installed in the main body to be rotated; a driving part to provide rotary power for the tongs part in order to make the trees be interposed between the main body and the tongs part; a bracket installed in the driving arm of an excavator; a mount connected to the bracket to be rotated or able to be protruded; a mount connection part installed between the mount and the main body to support the main body to be moved; and an elastic rotational connection part to keep the mount protruding from the bracket, and to restrict the rotational angle of the bracket.

column12: SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR DETECTING DEFECTS IN A SOLAR CELL AND REPAIRING AND CHARACTERIZING A SOLAR CELL
column13: A system and method for detecting a defect in a solar cell and repairing and characterizing a solar cell includes applying a test signal to the solar cell, monitoring the response of solar cell, detecting a defect associated with its location during the monitoring step, removing or isolating the defect from a solar cell and characterizing solar cell performance. The defect may be a short between the emitter and the base of solar cell. The system and method also detect a precise location of the defect based on the use of light valve panel (LVP), which can control the input beam to or output beam from the solar cell in terms of size, position, gray level, and wavelength of the transmitted light. The LVP may be realized in any one of a variety of ways. For example, the active matrix liquid crystal display (AMLCD) such as Thin Film Transistor driven LCD (TFT-LCD) may be used as the LVP.

column12: STEERING CONTROL METHOD USING ABS, ESC AND EPS FOR A CAR
column13: A steering control method using ABS, ESC and an EPS is provided to perform direct driving stably in an asymmetry road rapidly by using a method adding steering torque to a measured value of a steering torque sensor. A steering control method using ABS, ESC and an EPS comprises the following steps of: inputting an initial addition steering torque value in case difference is generated in quick braking(S1); amending the addition steering torque value in case the inputted steering torque value is excessive(S2); performing proportional control according to wheel breaking pressure difference with a proper gain value after stabilizing vehicles with a straight traveling state(S3); and inputting the addition steering torque value(S4).

column12: Bipolar multi electrostatic inducing discharge-dissipation lightning air terminals
column13: Disclosed is a bipolar multi electrostatic inducing discharge-dissipation lightning air terminal, in which different charges are applied to upper and lower sections thereof by an isolation polymer insulator in such a manner that an earth-charge is preliminarily discharged as a thundercloud approaches, so that a thunderbolt is prevented from falling onto a building, thereby preventing a loss of lives and protecting electronic products installed in a building from being damaged. The bipolar multi electrostatic inducing discharge-dissipation lightning air terminal has a fixing bar vertically installed at an upper surface of the fixing member, an electrostatic induction member, which is provided at an upper portion of the fixing bar and upper and lower sections of which are charged with different charges based on an electric double layer theory and an electric dipolar action caused by an electrostatic induction in order to dissipate and discharge an earth-charge into an atmospheric space as a thundercloud approaches, and including an isolation polymer insulator provided at the upper portion of the fixing bar for increasing an insulation distance, an auxiliary discharging member, which has at least one thin plate to be stacked and through a center of which a lower end part of the isolation polymer insulator passes, a preliminarily discharging cap member made of conductive material and positioned at a lower surface of the auxiliary discharging member, and a preliminarily discharging member fixed to the fixing bar in such that the preliminarily discharging member maintains a non-contact state with respect to a lower surface of the auxiliary discharging member, and a cap member detachably coupled to a free end of the fixing bar for pressing an upper portion of the electrostatic induction member and for discharging the earth-charge as the thundercloud approaches.

column12: PARTICIPATION BROADCASTING AND AUCTION BROADCASTING
column13: PURPOSE: A participation broadcasting and auction broadcasting is provided so that a televiewer easily participates in the broadcasting, and express televiewer's intention or progress auction through a general telephone or a mobile phone. CONSTITUTION: A DTMF(Dual Tone Multi Frequency) decoder recognizes a button pushed by a televiewer, and collects the number of buttons pushed by the televiewer in a PC2 connected through a communication interface such as a serial or LAN(Local Area Network). A VoIP(Voice over Internet Protocol) gateway having a DTMF recognition function collects the number of buttons pushed by the televiewer in a PC connected through the communication interface. The collected result is used in a real-time public opinion poll.

column12: Test socket and conductive particle
column13: The present invention relates to a test socket. More specifically, the test socket is disposed between a tested device and a testing device to electrically connect a terminal of the tested device and a pad of the testing device. The test socket comprises: a plurality of conductive units disposed to be separated from each other in a surface direction in every position corresponding to a terminal of the tested device, and having multiple conductive particles arranged in an elastic insulating material in a thickness direction; and an insulating support unit disposed between the conductive units separated from each other to support each of the conductive units and insulate the conductive units in a surface direction. Each of the conductive particles comprises: a pillar-shaped body part; and two or more projection parts protruding from the top end of the body part. A groove part recessed toward the body part is prepared between adjacent projection parts, and an angle between facing inner surfaces of the adjacent projection parts is an obtuse angle which is greater than 90.

column12: ID CHIP SOCKET FOR TEST CONNECTOR ASSEMBLY, TEST CONNECTOR ASSEMBLY INCLUDING ID CHIP SOCKET, AND TEST EQUIPMENT SET INCLUDING TEST CONNECTOR ASSEMBLY

column12: Test socket
column13: The present invention relates to a test socket. Particularly, the present invention relates to a test socket including: a housing including an accommodation space to accommodate a test-target device to be electrically tested, the housing having an open upper portion; a cover configured to open and close the open upper portion of the housing; a pusher device provided on the cover and configured to downwardly press the test-target device placed in the housing; a temperature adjustment means configured to inject air or a refrigerant having a predetermined temperature into the accommodation space to thereby adjust an inside temperature of the accommodation space; and a sealing means configured to seal the accommodation space from the outside of the accommodation space when the housing is closed by the cover, wherein the sealing means includes: a first packer arranged on an upper surface of the housing and surrounding the accommodation space, the upper surface of the housing facing the cover; a second packer arranged on the upper surface of the housing in such a manner that the second packer is spaced apart from the first packer and surrounds the first packer; and a vacuum means configured to create a vacuum between the first and second packers.

column12: DRY AIR GENERATION DEVICE, DRY AIR GENERATION METHOD AND SUBSTRATE PROCESSING SYSTEM
column13: To consecutively generate dry air whose dew-point temperature is 0°C or less.SOLUTION: A dry air generation device comprises a first heat exchanger, a second heat exchanger, a switching valve, and a control device. The first heat exchanger and the second heat exchanger, provided in a flow path for air, remove moisture included in air by cooling the air flowing through the flow path down to 0°C or less. The switching valve switches directions of air flowing in the first heat exchanger and in the second heat exchanger. The control device controls the first heat exchanger, the second heat exchanger and the switching valve. The first heat exchanger and the second heat exchanger are connected in series to each other in the flow path for air.SELECTED DRAWING: Figure 2

column12: Method of detecting defects in TFT-arrays and a TFT-array testing system incorporating the same
column13: A system and method for detecting defects in TFT-array panels is provided that improves defect detection accuracy by adjusting the thresholding parameters used to classify defective pixels in accordance with the standard deviation of the measured pixel voltages. The present invention is particularly suited for the testing of TFT-array panels that contain more pixels than can be measured by the sensor of the TFT-array tester in a single measurement. The system and method of the present invention calculates a reference pixel voltage at each pixel based on a low frequency component of the measured pixel voltage, and adjusts the thresholding parameters based on the calculated reference pixel voltage.

column13: 본 발명은 침입자의 걸음걸이를 감지하는 방범용 침입감지시스템에 관한 것이다. 본 침입감지시스템은 침입자를 감지하는 방범용 침입감지시스템에 있어서, 상기 침입자로부터 운동에너지를 감지하여 소정의 전기에너지를 발생하는 에너지센싱부와, 상기 전기에너지를 정전압으로 전력변환시키는 전력발생부와, 상기 전력발생부의 정전압에 기초하여 침입사실을 인식하고 판단한 후에 제어신호를 발생하는 제어부와, 상기 제어부의 제어신호에 기초하여 사용자에게 시각과 청각 중 적어도 어느 하나로 상기 침입사실을 알리는 경보부를 포함한다. 이에 따라, 침입자의 걸음걸이를 운동에너지로 감지함과 동시에 그 운동에너지로 전기를 발생시켜 침입사실을 외부로 알리기 때문에 센싱중에는 전력소비가 거의 없어 에너지절약효과가 탁월하며, 이에 따른 경제적인 부담감 또는 경감되고, 침입자의 걸음걸이로부터 운동에너지를 감지 하기 때문에 적외선에 의해서 감지되지 않는 경우에도 감지되므로 신뢰성을 향상시키고, 다수개의 공간을 두고 있는 경우 침입한 장소를 용이하게 파악할 수 있기 때문에 침입자를 적절하게 감금시킬 수 있는 효과가 있다.

column12: A CONTROL METHOD OF A DRUM TYPE WASHING MACHINE
column13: A method for controlling a frontload washer is provided to reduce an amount of remaining detergent by blowing air to a door primarily and supplying water to the door secondarily. A method for controlling a frontload washer comprises the steps: judging whether the present process is the right before a final rinse process(S120); and supplying air to the door direction to eliminate a detergent residue remaining on the door if the present process is the right before a final rinse process(S130).

column12: LETTER COGNITION METHOD FOR GUIDEPOST SHAPE
column13: PURPOSE: A method for recognizing a document with a graphic form is provided to improve recognition performance of the document, and correctly reform a diagram, by extracting a line and a feature point that has a directional component, using an opening technique. CONSTITUTION: A line component is extracted by the opening technique(S101). An envelope is obtained from the extracted line component. Four kinds of corners are extracted(S102). With the combination of the extracted corners, a sort of a feature point having a directional component may be defined. A network is formed on a basis of the feature point having the same(S103). A completed network comprises a perfect layout of the diagram. A necessary item is extracted for each cell, using a projection profile and connected component. The extracted item is applied to a recognizer so that it can recognize the item(S104).

column12: PDA CMS Method and system for mobile Car Management System by PDAPersonal Digital Assistant
column13: PURPOSE: A mobile CMS(Car Managing System) system and method using a PDA is provided to connect a user on an off-line to a service on the on-line Internet in real time and manage the user and the service by interlocking a database in a physical server, a mobile communication network, and PDA(Personal Digital Assistant) therewith. CONSTITUTION: An authority and a use or not of a user are authenticated using a wireless Internet(mobile communication) network and a program. Data service is received by interlocking with a web site in real time using the wireless Internet network. When a version of the program is upgraded, a confirmation upgrade is performed using the wireless Internet network automatically. Data are compressed using a sync-server and transmitted through a PDA. A PDA service such as a car management, a financial commodity management, a client management, a notice board management, selling article information, and a user management is provided.

column12: UNIVERSAL JOINT

PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a universal joint which is smoothly contracted when axial pressure is applied in the state where rotating torque operates on the universal joint, and whose tortional breakdown strength is increased to improve a safety factor with supporting operation of a guide ball when tortional breakdown torque operates on a slip bush.
