It has at least one guide hole 300 formed in the outer peripheral face of the slip bush in the longitudinal direction, the guide ball 310 inserted into the guide hole, and at least one C-type portion formed on the outer peripheral face of the slip bush in the longitudinal direction.

column12: Drum type washer and door
column13: A drum type washer and a door thereof are provided to eliminate moisture inside a door glass using natural convection. The door of the drum type washer includes a door glass, an inner door having a holder integral to the inner door to support an outer surface of the door glass, an outer door having a support rib integral to the outer door to support an inner surface of the door glass, the support rib including a hole set formed in the support rib such that an inside of the door glass communicates with an exterior of the drum type washer. With this configuration, the moisture created inside the door glass can be rapidly eliminated.

column12: VOICE GUIDE APPARATUS AND METHOD OF ESCALATORS
column13: A voice guide apparatus and a method for upward/downward escalators are provided to reduce an unpleasant feeling by supplying a clear voice guide broadcasting to passengers by performing synchronized voice guide broadcasting in the upward/downward escalators. In a voice guide apparatus for upward/downward escalators, upward and downward object sensors(21,22), mounted around the upward/downward escalators respectively, sense the entering object to each escalator. A microcomputer(23) controls an operation of the escalators and a voice guide by receiving the object sensing signal, sensed by the upward and downward object sensors. A common voice guide module(24) outputs a synchronized voice guide signal through upward and downward speakers, which are installed around the upward/downward escalators, by the voice guide signal of the microcomputer.

column12: UNMANNED GUARD SYSTEM
column13: PURPOSE: An unmanned guard system is provided to inform an indoor or outdoor space of an invader in a specific space through a communication or other alarm devices by sensing a blind area and a three-dimensional space exactly. CONSTITUTION: An unmanned guard system includes a sensing unit(1), a signal processing unit(3), a control unit(5) and an alarm unit(7). The sensing unit(1) detects at least one of the inherent smell or sound of an invader. The signal processing unit(3) amplifies the sensed signal to a specific size of gain and filters a noise signal thereof to standardize the wave form. The control unit(5) makes an alarm signal based on comparison between the output signal and reference signal. The alarm unit(7) alarms an indoor or outdoor space of the invader through at least one of visual or audio line.

column12: Digital to analog converter, delay-locked loop, memory device and counting method
column13: A digital to analog converter (DAC) can comprise: an escalator code generator; and an escalator-code-to-analog converter (ECAC). The generator can (1) represent base 10 numbers with a mixed code having a coin code portion and a cash code portion, which will eliminate multi-bit changes in the cash code upon changes in count direction; and (2) represent a count in a first direction as the sum of the coin code and the cash code. The generator can alter the coin code when the count changes direction while the cash code remains the same until a count capacity of the coin code is exceeded, at which point the cash code can be altered. Cycling between adjacent base 10 numbers is absorbed by the coin code while keeping the cash code the same, which reduces noise introduced into an output of the ECAC due to such cycling.

column12: QUICK COUPLER FOR EXCAVATION
column13: The present invention comprises: a body connected to an arm of an excavator; a driving hook installed to be rotated in the body, wherein a rotational axis of a bucket is coupled; a first hydraulic cylinder installed in the body for the driving hook to be rotated; a safety pin equipped in the body to appear toward the driving hook; a second hydraulic cylinder moving the safety pin as a rod appears by a working fluid supplied from the first hydraulic cylinder; and a hydraulic valve supplying a working fluid to the second hydraulic cylinder for the safety pin to be moved to the driving hook when the working fluid is filled over predetermined pressure inside the first hydraulic cylinder.

column12: Test socket
column13: The invention provides a test socket. The test socket comprises a first thin sheet type connector, multiple conductive elastic units and a second thin sheet type connector. The conductive elastic units are arranged under the first thin sheet type connector. The second thin sheet type connector is arranged under the conductive elastic units. The upper part and the lower part of each of the conductive elastic units are supported by the first thin sheet type connector and the second thin sheet type connector. Empty space is formed near each of the conductive elastic units and is not liable to prevent the conductive elastic units from being pressed in the thickness direction. The conductive elastic units extend in the direction of surfaces. By use of the test socket, when numbers of terminals on a to-be-tested device are increased, electrical performance tests can be easily executed on the to-be-tested device.

column12: Contact device for electrical test
column13: The present invention relates to a probe device for testing and, more specifically, to a probe device for testing which has at least a part inserted into a pipe with an internal space so as to be used in a test socket. The probe device for testing comprises: a second body part which has a polygonal or circular column shape; a first body part which is stacked on an upper portion of the second body part, integrally formed with the second body part, and having a polygonal or circular column shape; an intermediate part which is stacked on an upper portion of the first body part, integrally formed with the first body part, and having a pointed first protrusion formed on an upper side thereof, wherein the first protrusion has a first peak part; and a contact part which is formed on an upper surface of the intermediate part to be integrated with the intermediate part, and having a second protrusion formed in a position corresponding to the first protrusion, wherein the second protrusion has a height which increases in a direction perpendicular to the upper surface of the intermediate part along the external appearance of the first protrusion, and is provided with a second peak portion. The second body part, the first body part, the intermediate part, and the contact part are sequentially and upwardly stacked, the intermediate part and the contact part are made of different materials, and the first protrusion is provided in the second protrusion. According to the present invention, the contact part and the intermediate part are not separated from each other even when loads in different directions are applied.

column12: METHOD AND SYSTEM FOR TRANSMITTING/RECEIVING DATA IN THE HETEROGENEOUS COMMUNICATION SYSTEMS
column13: A method and a system for transceiving data in heterogeneous communication systems are provided to support handover in case an MS(Mobile Station) moves between the heterogeneous communication systems, thereby seamlessly providing a service which has been provided to the MS. A method for transceiving data in heterogeneous communication systems comprises the following steps of: maintaining an active session with a first communication system according as a mobile station connects to the first communication system(1001~1003); requesting an active session from a second communication system by being connected to the second communication system if handover to the second communication system is sensed while the active session with the first communication system is maintained(1017); and maintaining the active session with the first communication system through the active session with the second communication system corresponding to the request.

column12: ELECTRICAL TEST SOCKET AND METHOD FOR MANUFACTURING CONDUCTIVE PARTICLE FOR ELECTRICAL TEST SOCKET
column13: The present invention relates to an electrical test socket and a method for manufacturing a conductive particle for an electrical test socket and, more specifically, to an electrical test socket, disposed between terminals of a device to be tested and pads of a test device to electrically connect the terminals and the pads, and a method for manufacturing a conductive particle for an electrical test socket. The electrical test socket comprises an anisotropic conductive sheet that includes: a plurality of conductive sections in the positions corresponding to the terminals of the device to be tested, each conductive section having a plurality of conductive particles arranged in the thickness direction within an insulating resilient material; and an insulating support section that insulates the conductive sections while supporting the same, wherein each conductive particle includes a conductive core and a conductive protrusion extending from the surface of the conductive core in the radial direction and integrally attached to the conductive core, and the conductive protrusions of the conductive particles adjacent to each other become entangled when the conductive particles are arranged in the insulating resilient material.

column13: To provide a substrate processing system capable of increasing controllability of temperature distribution in a plane of a substrate mounted on a mounting table.SOLUTION: A substrate processing system of an embodiment comprises: a processing container; a mounting table provided inside the processing container; a first gas hole provided on a surface of the mounting table; a first gas passage connected to the first gas hole; a first gas branch passage branching from the first gas passage; a second gas hole provided on the surface of the mounting table and different from the first gas hole; a second gas passage connected to the second gas hole; a second gas branch passage branching from the second gas passage; a gas supply passage connected to the first gas passage and the second gas passage; a gas exhaust passage connected to the first gas branch passage and the second gas branch passage; and a control unit. column12: SKIN-CONDITION IMPROVING COMPOSITION COMPRISING VACCINIUM ULIGINOSUM EXTRACT AND METHOD FOR PREPARATION THEREOF
column13: The present invention relates to a composition for the improvement of skin conditions, comprising an extract of Vaccinium uliginosum as an active ingredient. The Vaccinium uliginosum extract has the effects of inhibiting and scavenging reactive oxygen species produced in skin tissue as a result of ultraviolet irradiation to the skin, effectively inhibiting tyrosinase activity to inhibit the production of melanin in melanin cells, inhibiting the secretion of cytokines in keratinocytes, promoting the production of procollagen, and inhibiting the decomposition of collagen. Thus, the extract will be useful for the prevention of skin photo aging caused by ultraviolet radiation, the enhancement of skin whitening and the improvement of wrinkles. In addition, the Vaccinium uliginosum extract is suitable to use as a component for improving skin wrinkles in cosmetics, foods and drugs, because the Vaccinium uliginosum extract can achieve the effect of improving skin conditions, even when it is applied to the skin or used internally.

column12: VCOM GENERATOR AND METHOD
column13: A method for generating a common voltage, a common voltage generating circuit, and a liquid crystal display device are provided to reduce a chip size by minimizing calculation resistances and the number of OP(Operational) amplifiers. A common voltage generating circuit includes a digital logic calculator(310), an input reference voltage generating unit(320) and a buffer(330). The digital logic calculator receives an amplitude control register value in which target amplitude of common voltage is set up, and then outputs a second control register value in which second target voltage of the common voltage is set up. The input reference voltage generating unit receives a first control register value, which is set a first target voltage of the common voltage, and the second control register value, and generates first and second input reference voltages. The buffer receives the first and second input reference voltages, and outputs first and second common voltages.

column12: CLAYMORE MINE ON WHICH DEVICE FOR PREVENTING BREAKDOWN ATTRIBUTABLE TO POWER NOISE HAS BEEN MOUNTED
column13: Disclosed is a claymore mine on which a device for preventing a breakdown attributable to a power noise has been mounted. In order to prevent an electric primer from operating due to a power noise induced by a magnetic field or generated by the falling of a thunderbolt or other factors, such as a communication device, a shield layer formed by weaving or braiding a conductive fiber, such as a carbon fiber, or weaving or braiding a copper-plated tin wire, is formed in the wire and percussion unit of the claymore mine. In order to discharge a power noise introduced into the wire and the percussion unit to the earth, a power noise discharge adaptor including a plurality of diodes, a TVS, a GDT, and an SPD is formed. Accordingly, the introduction of a power noise can be fundamentally blocked, and a power noise can be safely discharged to the earth if the power noise is introduced.

column12: Apparatus for Inspecting Camera Module
column13: The invention provides an apparatus for inspecting a camera module. The apparatus herein includes: a chassis which is provided with a spring needle block and a main printed circuit board, a cable being connected to the spring needle block and the main printed circuit board; a pair of cam disks which are fixedly installed in the lower parts of the chassis; cam holes which are arranged in the cam disks; a pneumatic cylinder which is configured to the low part of the chassis; a tension block which is configured to be driven by the pneumatic cylinder to move backwardly to the chassis along the path over which the cam holes extend; and a module accommodating block which accommodates a camera module. The module accommodating block is supported in an elastic manner by the tension block and is configured to move backwardly along with the tension block and stop moving backwardly upon contacting stoppers on the cam disks. The module accommodating block is configured to rise along with the rise of the tension block, such that the camera module and the spring needle block are brought into contact. Therefore, the moving path of a detection device is improved and the cable can be prevented frombeing cut off. Also, component elements are simplified and raw cost is lowered.

column12: VOLTAGE BOOST CIRCUIT AND VOLTAGE BOOSTING METHOD USING VOLTAGE BOOST CLOCK SIGNAL WITH VARYING FREQUENCY
column13: A voltage boost circuit and a method of boosting voltage using a voltage boost clock signal with varying frequency, in which the voltage boost circuit includes a boost voltage generator that responds to a voltage boost clock signal in order to boost an input voltage and outputs the boosted input voltage as an output a boost voltage; and a boost voltage frequency control unit that responds to the result obtained by comparing a level of the output boost voltage and a level of a target boost voltage so as to change the boost voltage frequency of the voltage boost clock signal and outputs the voltage boost clock signal having the changed boost voltage frequency. The voltage boost circuit and the voltage boosting method can prevent a waste of the operating current during the boosting of the voltage.

column12: CONCRETE COMPOSITION HAVING REDUCTION OF ALKALI AGGREGATE REACTION, CHLORIDE RESISTANCE, CORROSION INHIBITION AND PAVING METHOD USING THE SAME
column13: PURPOSE: A concrete composition is provided to reduce initial shrinkage by mixing hydrophilic fiber. CONSTITUTION: A concrete composition contains a binder, fine aggregate, thick aggregate, water, water reducing agent, hydrophilic fiber and air entraining agent. The binder contains 70-95.5 weight% of cement, 4-16 weight% of one of silica fume and methakaolin, 0.1-12 weight% fly ash, 0.04-0.1 weight% of alkoxy aliphatic alcohol and 0.07-0.2 weight% of alkyl amine derivative salt based on 100 weight% of binder. The alkyl amine derivative salt contains 70-80 weight% of cyclo amine derivative and 20-30 weight% of branched amine derivative. The hydrophilic fiber comprises one of polyvinyl alcohols(PVA), polypropylenes(PP), and polyethylenes(PE).

column12: METHOD OF CREATING APPLICATION PROGRAM SOURCE FOR DATABASE AND DEVICE THEREOF
column13: PURPOSE: A database application program source generation method and a device thereof are provided to use not only a program source according to a storage unit of a table and view unit but an SQL, thereby conveniently generating a program source corresponding to a plurality of tables and views related. CONSTITUTION: A UI(User Interface) unit(10) receives an SQL(Structured Query Language) syntax from a user, or sets up output column information. An SQL executing unit(53) executes the SQL syntax in a database. A column information recognizer(55) extracts column meta information according to the execution result. A source generator(57) generates a program source by using the column meta information.

column12: LIQUID CRISTAL DISPLAY DEVICE
Circuits and methods providing reduced power consumption for driving flat panel displays
column13: Circuits and methods are provided for driving flat panel displays (e.g., a liquid crystal display (LCD)), which provide reduced power consumption for driving data lines and common electrodes of flat panel displays. Source driving circuits and methods for driving data lines and circuits and methods for driving a common electrode use both intermediate reference voltages and boosted driving voltages in each driving cycle (as opposed to entirely using boosted driving voltages) to reduce power consumption and provide charge recycling.

column12: CAMERA MODULE TEST SOCKET
column13: The present invention relates to a camera module test socket comprising: a base plate disposed on and supported by a camera module test equipment; a socket cover, disposed on the base plate, for covering a camera module seating part; a down base disposed in the back of the socket cover and provided with a tapered hinged part hinged to the socket cover; a pneumatic cylinder support interposed between a pneumatic cylinder and the base plate; the pneumatic cylinder, disposed on the pneumatic cylinder support, for moving a roller block forward and backward; and the roller block which advances, by a part of the single stroke of the pneumatic cylinder, to induce the socket cover to cover and close the camera module seating part, and which pushes, by the progression of rest of the stroke of the pneumatic cylinder, the tapered hinged part of the down base so as to induce the tapered hinged part to descend, and as such, a vertical contact is established on the clamshell-type socket cover to receive the contact force vertically, and thus damage to a pogo pin can be prevented. Furthermore, as the lifespan of the pogo pin is extended due to the reduced impact thereto, economic benefits such as reduced maintenance expense and personnel can be attained.

column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide compact designs that enable smaller chip area for gate drier ICs.

SOLUTION: A semiconductor integrated gate driver IC comprises a plurality of gate driver circuits, wherein each gate driver 300 drives corresponding gate lines (GL1 to GLn) and a level shifter circuit 320, for generating a precharge control signal. Each gate driver comprises a line decoder 322 for generating a gate line control signal and a precharge circuit 310 for precharging a gate driver turn-on voltage before activating the gate line. During a driving phase, the precharged gate driver turn-on voltage is discharged when the gate line is activated in response to the decoded gate line control signal, whereas the precharged gate driver turn-on voltage is maintained when the gate line is not activated in response to the decoded gate line control signal.

column12: Oscillator having comparator circuits having adjustable driving capabilities and method for operating the same
column13: An oscillator includes a first comparator circuit, a second comparator circuit, an oscillation signal generator circuit, and a frequency voltage generator circuit. The first comparator circuit generates a first pulse when a frequency voltage reaches a first reference voltage, and the second comparator circuit generates a second pulse when the frequency voltage reaches a second reference voltage. The oscillation signal generator circuit generates an oscillation signal by latching a first voltage in response to the first pulse and latching a second voltage in response to the second pulse. The frequency voltage generator circuit raises or lowers the frequency voltage in response to the oscillation signal. The driving capability of the first comparator circuit is reduced at the latching of the first voltage and is restored at the latching of the second voltage. The driving capability of the second comparator circuit is reduced at the latching of the second voltage and is restored at the latching of the first voltage.

The elastic conductive sheet is detachably mounted on an upper portion of the pin support and the device to be tested is mounted on the elastic conductive sheet. The elastic conductive sheet includes a plurality of elastic conductive portions which are in contact with the plurality of terminals and the plurality of contact pins in the vertical direction. The housing is coupled to the pin support and accommodates the elastic conductive sheet. The pusher is movably coupled to the housing in the vertical direction. The latch device is operatively connected to the housing and the pusher and fixes the device to be tested to the elastic conductive sheet to be releasable in conjunction with the movement of the pusher.

column12: Claymore mine on which device for preventing breakdown attributable to power noise has been mounted
column13: Disclosed is a claymore mine on which a device for preventing a breakdown attributable to a power noise has been mounted. In order to prevent an electric primer from operating due to a power noise induced by a magnetic field or generated by the falling of a thunderbolt or other factors, such as a communication device, a shield layer formed by weaving or braiding a conductive fiber, such as a carbon fiber, or weaving or braiding a copper-plated tin wire, is formed in the wire and percussion unit of the claymore mine. In order to discharge a power noise introduced into the wire and the percussion unit to the earth, a power noise discharge adaptor including a plurality of diodes, a TVS, a GDT, and an SPD is formed. Accordingly, the introduction of a power noise can be fundamentally blocked, and a power noise can be safely discharged to the earth if the power noise is introduced.

TEMPERATURE MEASUREMENT DEVICE AND SUBSTRATE PROCESSING APPARATUS INCLUDING THE SAME
column13: A temperature measuring unit according to an embodiment of the present invention includes a blocking member. The blocking member allows a target point of a substrate to be exposed to the temperature measuring member, and blocks a portion of the substrate other than the target point. Therefore, the temperature measuring member may accurately measure the temperature of the target point without being interfered with by heat other than the target point. Accordingly, in the process of processing the substrate by a substrate processing apparatus, the temperature measurement reliability of the substrate is remarkably improved compared to a conventional temperature measurement unit, so that the temperature of the substrate can be accurately controlled. That is, in the temperature measuring unit according to the present invention, the substrate (W) is excessively heated and the substrate (W) is damaged, or the substrate (W) is not heated to the temperature required for the reaction, so that the thermal chemical reaction is caused properly. In addition, the temperature measuring unit according to the present invention rotates the blocking member with a driving member at the same rotation speed as the rotation speed of the substrate, so that only the target point can be exposed to the temperature measuring member. Accordingly, the precision of temperature measurement of the substrate can be improved.

column12: OIL FAST WARM UP SYSTEM COMBINED WITH EXHAUST GAS RECIRCULATION CIRCUIT
column13: PURPOSE: A system for quickly warming up oil by being connected to a recirculation circuit is provided to reduce engine friction by increasing temperature of an oil cooler and allowing EGR gas to travel to a suction system. CONSTITUTION: A system for quickly warming up oil by being connected to a recirculation circuit comprises an EGR outlet pipe (31), an EGR cooler (30), an EGR return pipeline (32), and bypass pipes (41, 42). The EGR outlet pipe sucks some exhaust gas from an exhaust side of a cylinder head. The EGR return pipeline sends EGR gas back to a suction system. The bypass pipes directly transfers the EGR gas to the EGR return pipeline without going through the EGR cooler. A first pipe (41) of the return pipes is connected to an oil cooler (14), and exchanges heat with engine oil traveling in the oil cooler. A second pipe of the return pipes is connected to the EGR return pipeline. A cut-out valve (40) for diverting the EGR gas is installed in a branch point of the first pipe. column12: Escalator code-based DAC and delay-locked loop apparatus and corresponding methods
column13: A digital to analog converter (DAC) can comprise: an escalator code generator; and an escalator-code-to-analog converter (ECAC). The generator can (1) represent base  10  numbers with a mixed code having a coin code portion and a cash code portion, which will eliminate multi-bit changes in the cash code upon changes in count direction; and (2) represent a count in a first direction as the sum of the coin code and the cash code. The generator can alter the coin code when the count changes direction while the cash code remains the same until a count capacity of the coin code is exceeded, at which point the cash code can be altered. Cycling between adjacent base  10  numbers is absorbed by the coin code while keeping the cash code the same, which reduces noise introduced into an output of the ECAC due to such cycling.

column12: Data receiver and data receiving method using signal integration

column13: A broadcast signal includes an information table (EIT) or an application information table (AIT) which includes a descriptor. The descriptor includes image data representative of a thumbnail image to be displayed within an electronic program guide (EPG). A decoder decodes the EIT or AIT from a broadcast signal, and an application manager displays the thumbnail image within an EPG to indicate that a channel scheduled to carry a broadcast program is also scheduled to carry broadcast data simultaneously.

According to an embodiment of the present invention, the apparatus to dry a ladle is inserted into a molten metal outlet in case of drying a ladle by a concurrent heating burner flame, and comprises: a reflective member inserted into the molten metal outlet to reflect radiant heat of the flame to a surrounding of the molten metal outlet; and a reflective panel supported by an outer side of a bottom of the ladle to seal the molten metal outlet.

Write head control device and method
column13: A write head 10 for an ink jet printer is disclosed. The head includes one or more chambers 12 having a lower portion containing a quantity of liquid metal 20 and an upper ink reservoir 15, an ink channel 14 connecting the ink reservoir to an ink cartridge and a nozzle 13 for ejecting ink droplets from the ink reservoir. A magnetic field is established across the liquid metal by opposite magnetic bodies 18, 19 and opposing electrodes 16, 17 are provided to pass an electric current through the liquid metal 20 perpendicular to the magnetic field to cause the liquid metal 20 to move and expel an ink droplet from the ink reservoir through the nozzle 13. A temperature sensor 21 senses the temperature at a predetermined position on the write head 10 and a heating element 22 heats the liquid metal 20 when the temperature sensed drops below a preset value. This maintains the temperature of the liquid metal 20 above its melting point.

column12: PAVING STRUCTURAL MATERIALS OF ELASTIC MAT IN ORDER TO ABSORB SHOCK
column13: A pavement structure of an elastic mat for absorbing shock is provided to improve appearance and function, and to buffer shock by firmly assembling an elastic color surface layer with an upper part of the elastic mat. A leg(3) is formed in a lower part of an elastic shock absorbing mat(1), and shock is absorbed by forming a lower space(4) between the legs and forming an upper space(2). Primer of 0.3 Kg/m^2 is spread on the elastic shock absorbing mat, and mixture is evenly spread thereon by mixing a color rubber chip of 100 wt% and synthetic resin adhesive of 20 to 30 wt%. A release agent is applied in a mold, and elastic layer material of 6 cm in thickness is charged in the mold. The elastic shock absorbing mat is manufactured by pressurizing material at 160‹C for 12 minutes and separating a product from the mold. Sand of 2 to 3 cm in thickness is evenly spread on a floor, and the elastic shock absorbing mat is installed thereon.

column12: OUTLINE SHAPE RECOGNITION SYSTEM OF IRON PLATE
column13: PURPOSE: An outline recognition system of a steel plate is provided to simplify an assembly and maintenance and repair by installing a light blind, a laser irradiating unit, and a camera into one head unit. CONSTITUTION: An outline recognition system of a steel plate comprises a steel plate, a head unit(210), a camera(120), a light blind(200), a recognition unit, and a control unit. The steel plate is placed on a set work area. The head unit comprises a laser irradiation unit(110) irradiating line beams while moving along an edge portion of the steel plate. The camera senses laser beams reflected from the steel plate. The light blind prevents lights flowing in into the laser irradiating unit or the camera from outside. The recognition unit recognizes an outline shape of the steel plate by using detection signals detected by the camera. The control unit recognizes the outline of the steel plate while tracing by using a location of the head unit and the recognized outline of the steel plate.

column12: LIDAR SYSTEM
column13: Provided is a light detection and ranging (LIDAR) system. The LIDAR system includes: a housing including a first region and a second region, the second region including a plurality of openings; a laser disposed in the first region of the housing and configured to emit light; a plurality of optical fibers disposed in the second region, and configured to receive, at one ends thereof, and transmit, at the other ends thereof, the light emitted from the laser to an outside of the housing through the plurality of openings; and a detector configured to receive the light transmitted from the plurality of optical fibers to the outside and reflected from the outside, and convert the received reflected light into an electrical signal.

column12: Room temperature process for preparation of pearl pigments by precipitation method
column13: The present invention relates to a process for preparing a pearl pigment, comprising the steps of (a) adding an aqueous solution of metal oxide to a substrate in a reactor and (b) adding ammonium bicarbonate aqueous solution as a precipitating agent.

column12: Semiconductor device and method for manufacturing the same
column13: A semiconductor device and a method for manufacturing the same are disclosed. A recess gate structure is formed between an overlapping region between a gate and a source/drain so as to suppress increase in gate induced drain leakage (GIDL), and a gate insulation film is more thickly deposited in a region having weak GIDL, thereby reducing GIDL and thus improving refresh characteristics due to leakage current.

column12: OSCILLATOR AND OSCILLATION METHOD TEHEROF
column13: An oscillator and an oscillation method thereof are provided to reduce power consumption by reducing a driving force in finishing a voltage latch. When a frequency voltage(Vf) reaches a first reference voltage(V1), a first comparing circuit(220) generates a first pulse(Vs). When a frequency voltage reaches a second reference voltage(V2), a second comparing circuit(240) generates a second pulse(Vr). An oscillation signal generating circuit(300) latches a first voltage in response to the first pulse, and latches a second voltage in response to the second pulse. A frequency voltage generating circuit(400) raises or drops the frequency voltage in response to an oscillation signal. A driving force of the first comparing circuit is reduced in latching the first voltage, and is restored in latching the second voltage. A driving force of the second comparing circuit is reduced in latching the second voltage, and is restored in latching the first voltage.

column12: ANTENA FOR DUALBAND CIRCULAR POLARIZATION AND METHOD FOR DESIGNING THE SAME
column13: A dual-band circular polarization antenna comprises: a substrate where a ground surface is formed; a circular patch which forms a ring-slot on the substrate, and a cross-slot within the ring-slot; and a feed line having two microstrip lines which are extended from one port and formed at a right angle between the ground surface and the circular patch for orthogonal feeding via coupling. The present invention adjusts geometric parameters of the substrate and the circular patch to tune a first frequency band (L_1) and a second frequency band (L_2) which is different from the first frequency band (L_1). Therefore, an antenna can be miniaturized, and an antenna having desired performance can be designed by adjusting structural parameters.

column12: SCANNING RADAR APPARATUS
column13: Disclosed is a scanning lidar apparatus. According to the present invention, the apparatus comprises: a laser unit lasing a laser signal in the direction of a certain region of a surrounding space and receiving light; a first rotation unit rotating the laser unit on a first horizontal surface; a position adjustment unit adjusting an angle between the first horizontal surface and a second horizontal surface which is a scanning reference surface, wherein the laser unit and the first rotation unit are placed on the first horizontal surface; a plate forming the second horizontal surface and supporting one side of the first rotation unit and one side of the position adjustment unit; and a second rotating unit rotating the plate on the second horizontal surface. column12: CONTACTOR FOR SEMICONDUCTOR TEST
column13: 본 발명은 미세 피치를 가지는 반도체 검사에 적용이 가능한 반도체 테스트용 콘택터에 관한 것이다. 본 발명의 실시예에 따른 반도체 테스트용 콘택터는 제1탐침부, 제2탐침부 그리고 탄성부를 포함한다. 여기서, 제1탐침부는 일단부가 피검사 디바이스의 단자에 전기적으로 접촉된다. 제2탐침부는 일단부가 검사장치의 패드에 전기적으로 접촉된다. 그리고 탄성부는 제1탐침부 및 제2탐침부와 일체로 형성되어 제1탐침부 및 제2탐침부를 전기적으로 연결하며, 탄성부는 제1탐침부 및 제2탐침부의 두께보다 얇은 두께를 가지도록 형성되고, 양단부는 각각 제1탐침부의 타단부의 일측 및 제2탐침부의 타단부의 일측에 연결되며, 제1탐침부의 타단부의 타측 및 제2탐침부의 타단부의 타측을 연결하는 제1가상 연결선 방향으로 굴곡 형성되되, 중앙부가 제1가상 연결선을 넘지 않도록 굴곡 형성된다.

column12: HEAT EXCHANGER OF HIGH EFFICIENCY
column13: PURPOSE: A heat exchanger of high efficiency is provided to reduce volume of a heat exchanger by improving the performance of a heat exchanger, thereby minimizing a space for the heat exchanger. CONSTITUTION: A heat exchanger is formed by accumulating two kinds of plates. One plate(A) has low side walls. The other plate(B) has slightly high side walls and poles periodically arranged. A plurality of long paths are formed on the one plate in a longitudinal direction for flowing a fluid of high temperature. A plurality of short paths are formed on the other plate in a width direction for flowing air for cooling. The fluid and the air exchange heat with each other.

column12: PAVING METHOD USING GLASS CHIPS
column13: The present invention relates to a paving method using glass chips which form a road with beautiful appearance by coating the pulverized glass chips in color and applying the coated glass chips to a paving of the surface of the road or square. The paving method provided by the present invention includes the following steps of: (a) pulverizing plate glass into glass chips; (b) selecting glass chips of a desired grain size; (c) forming the selected glass chips into beads with smooth surfaces by sintering the selected glass chips in a firing furnace; (d) washing and drying the beads; (e) coating the surface of the dried beads with color ink at room temperature; and (f) coating the surface of a paving construction with a mixture of the beads and the 5-8 parts by weight of a binder about the 100 parts by weight of the beads.

column13: A system and method of monitoring LCD production yields, predicting the effects of different testing methodologies on LCD production yields, and optimizing production yields is provided that compares the effect of different testing methodologies on the yields at various stages in the LCD testing and assembly process. The present invention can also be used to predict the effect of different testing methodologies on user-defined parameters, such as profit.

column12: TEST SOCKET AND CONDUCTIVE PARTICLES
column13: The present invention relates to a test socket and conductive particles, and more specifically, to a test socket disposed between a device to be tested and a testing device so as to electrically connect a terminal of the device to be tested and a pad of the testing device. The test socket comprises: a plurality of conductive parts provided at each position corresponding to the terminal of the device to be tested, and having a plurality of conductive particles arranged in the vertical direction within an elastic insulating material; and insulating support parts provided between the plurality ofconductive parts, and electrically insulating the conductive parts from each other while supporting each of the conductive parts, wherein at least one of the conductive particles includes: a body part made of a metal material and forming an outer shape of the conductive particle; and a plurality of silica particles having one part fixed within the body part, having the remaining part protruding from the body part, and making contact with the elastic insulating material, which forms the conductive parts, so as to be firmly coupled to the elastic insulating material.

column13: 본 발명은, 종래 자동차용 조향장치에 적용되는 핸들컬럼의 높이조절장치의 불합리한 단점들에 의해 나타났던 여러 가지 문제점 등을 해결보완하기 위하여 안출된 것으로서, 칼럼샤프트를 일측 칼럼샤프트와 타측 칼럼 샤프트로 양분하여 끝단의 결합부에 형성된 사각봉과 사각관의 결합에 의해 직선 이동이 용이하도록한 뒤, 상기 내측튜브의 외주연부에는 고정벤드와 압지밴드에 의해 내측튜브를 압지하거나 탈압지하는 수단에 의해 핸들의 높이를 운전자의 신체적 조건 및 취향에 맞추어서 조절할 수 있도록된 자동차의 조향장치용 핸들 칼럼의 높이 조절장치를 제공한다.

column12: Display device capable of detecting battery removal and a method of removing a latent image
column13: Provided is a display device capable of detecting battery removal and a method of removing a latent image from a panel. The display device includes a panel, and a driver unit displaying an image on the panel, wherein the driver unit comprises: a controller, generating a control signal and color data in response to a first power supply voltage; a voltage generator, generating control voltages in response to the control signal and a second power supply voltage; a voltage level controller, receiving the control voltages, outputting the control voltages in a first operation mode, and outputting the control voltages as first-level voltages in a second operation mode; and a source driver and a gate driver, controlling source lines and gate lines of the panel, respectively, in response to the color data, the control signal, and the control voltages. The first operation mode indicates that the display device is operating normally and the second operation mode indicates that the battery has been removed from the display panel.

Sawtooth wave generating circuit and switch mode power supply having the same
column13: A sawtooth wave generating circuit that outputs a sawtooth wave signal after calibration and a switch mode power supply device including the sawtooth wave generating circuit is disclosed. The sawtooth wave generating circuit includes a capacitor, a calibration circuit, a charging circuit, discharging circuit and a control unit. The calibration circuit feedbacks a sawtooth wave signal, generates a plurality of voltage signals based on the sawtooth wave signal, and selects one of the voltage signals to generate a calibration output signal. Therefore, the sawtooth wave generating circuit generates a stable sawtooth wave signal regardless of operating conditions.

column12: anisotropic conductive sheet
column13: The present invention relates to an anisotropic conductive sheet and conductive powders and, more specifically, to an anisotropic conductive sheet electrically arranged between a device to be tested and a testing device to electrically connect a terminal of the device to be tested and a pad of the testing device to each other. The anisotropic conductive sheet includes conductive passage forming units arranged in every positions corresponding to the terminal of the device to be tested and providing conductivity in a thickness direction and insulating units insulating the conductive passage forming units while supporting each conductive passage forming unit. Multiple conductive powders are arranged in the thickness direction within an elastic insulating substance. The conductive powder is formed into a mesh structure of a three-dimensional net form. Multiple pores connecting inner and outer sides are formed in the conductive powder, thus the elastic insulating substances forming the conductive passage forming units are integrally connected to the outer side of the conductive powder while filling the pores of the conductive powders.

column12: Escalator code-based delay-locked loop apparatus and corresponding methods
column13: A delay-locked loop (DLL) may include: a variable delay line arrangement operable to receive a reference clock and to output a delayed local clock; a phase comparator device operable to compare said reference clock and said local clock and to provide an up/down indication; and a delay control circuit, responsive to said up/down count-indication, to provide a reduced-noise delay control signal to said variable delay line arrangement, said delay control circuit being operable to count said up/down indication using an escalator code arrangement.

column12: CABLE-STAYED BRIDGE LIGHTNING PROTECTION APPARATUS FOR DISTRIBUTING LIGHTNING CURRENT
column13: "A cable-stayed bridge lightning protection apparatus for distributing a lightning current", according to the present invention, comprises: a lightning rod (40) provided at the cable-stayed bridge; a grounding body (80) for facilitating an electrical connection of the lightning rod and the ground; a down-conductor (50) for connecting the lightning rod and the grounding body; supporting cables (30) for connecting a tower and a deck of the cable-stayed bridge; a protective lightning inducing wire (60) of the supporting cable, supported at the uppermost supporting cable among the plurality of supporting cables by one or more of a plurality of insulating supporters (90), and connected to the down-conductor (50) at the lower end of the lightning rod (40); and current distribution conductors (70) provided in parallel to the supporting cables, and connected to the down-conductor (50) and the grounding body (80) at both end portions of the supporting cable. The present invention relates to the cable-stayed bridge lightning protection apparatus for distributing the lightning current, the apparatus allowing the lightning current (a current flowing in because of the lightning) to be distributed and flow to the down-conductor, and the current distribution conductors, provided in parallel to each supporting cable, when lightning (hereinafter, referred to as downward lightning), which is downwardly discharged from the thundercloud to the ground or lightning (hereinafter, referred to as upward lightning) upwardly discharged from the ground to the thundercloud, according to the polarity of a thundercloud, flows in through the lightning rod or the supporting cables provided at the cable-stayed bridge, such that the current, flowing to the supporting cables, particularly, to an assembly of steel wires forming the supporting cable, is minimized, thereby preventing a decrease, in the mechanical strength of the supporting cables, caused by a fire or heat at the supporting cables because of the heat generated from the supporting cables, that is, Joule's heat caused by the lightning current and electrical resistance of the steel wire assembly, such that the stability of the cable-stayed bridge can be ensured. Furthermore, the cable-stayed bridge lightning protection apparatus for distributing the lightning current has a dipolar lightning rod for minimizing a deviation of discharge start voltages according to the polarity of the thundercloud so as to minimize a deviation in the magnitudes of the currents flowing in the down-conductor and the current distribution conductor, thereby enabling the capacity of the down-conductor and the current distribution conductor to be easily selected when a lightning protection system of the cable-stayed bridge is designed. In addition, the lightning protection apparatus exhibits an effect of providing the lightning rods to each supporting cable (30) and respectively providing the down-conductors thereto in order to prevent the lightning flowing to the supporting cables (30), thereby having excellent complexity, constructability, and economic efficiency, which are provided to lightning protection devices for each supporting cable of the cable-stayed bridge by using one lightning rod.

column12: Display device capable of detecting battery removal and a method of removing a latent image
column13: Provided is a display device capable of detecting battery removal and a method of removing a latent image from a panel. The display device includes a panel, and a driver unit displaying an image on the panel, wherein the driver unit comprises: a controller, generating a control signal and color data in response to a first power supply voltage; a voltage generator, generating control voltages in response to the control signal and a second power supply voltage; a voltage level controller, receiving the control voltages, outputting the control voltages in a first operation mode, and outputting the control voltages as first-level voltages in a second operation mode; and a source driver and a gate driver, controlling source lines and gate lines of the panel, respectively, in response to the color data, the control signal, and the control voltages. The first operation mode indicates that the display device is operating normally and the second operation mode indicates that the battery has been removed from the display panel.

column12: PROBE MEMBER FOR POGO PIN, MANUFACTURING METHOD THEREFOR AND POGO PIN COMPRISING SAME
column13: The present invention relates to a probe member for a pogo pin, a manufacturing method therefor and a pogo pin comprising same. One embodiment of the present invention provides a probe member used in a test socket, the probe member comprising: at least one contact part having one end formed so as to be sharp and making contact with an object being inspected; a polygonal or cylindrical first body part having the other end of the contact part coupling to one end thereof; and a polygonal or cylindrical second body part having the other end of the first body part coupling to one end thereof, wherein the first body part and the second body part are stacked in the height direction with reference to the other end of the contact part, and at least one portion thereof are inserted in a pipe having an inner space formed therein.

column12: Method for producing conductive fiber
column13: The present invention relates to a method for manufacturing a conductive fiber and, more specifically, to a method for manufacturing a conductive fiber capable of manufacturing clothes made of fibers containing germanium and platinum. By wearing the clothes made of fibers containing germanium and platinum, the blood circulation of a wearer can be improved, and antistatic and far-infrared radiation effects can be achieved.

column12: CRABON FIBER
column13: PURPOSE: A carbon fiber heating wire is provided to be washable, bent easily, and washed easily, and to enable easy control of a heating level. CONSTITUTION: A base heating wire(21) and a structure fiber(22) are woven into a planar form. At this time, multiple circles are connected to touch each other; then the lower semicircle of one circle is rotated; and then the upper semicircle of the next circle is rotated; so that the structure fiber is rotated along the centers of the circles and is wrapped around the base heating wire while. The base heating wire is supplied with constant tension at the centers of the circles, thereby having uniform resistance, and is made in a flat shape by enabling the structure fiber to move in a planar way while being wrapped around the base heating wire.

column12: METHOD FOR FORMING A CIRCUIT LAYOUT
column13: PURPOSE: A circuit layout forming method of a semiconductor device is provided to minimize variation of critical dimension of a wafer design by extracting a correlation of pattern density of a sub layer and a focus. CONSTITUTION: A first proximity effect modeling operation is performed based on lithography proximity effect by a first layer(301). A second proximity effect modeling operation is performed based on lithography proximity effect by a second layer(303). A result of the first proximity effect modeling operation is combined with a result of the second proximity effect modeling operation in a modeling algorithm(304). A layout of a mask is controlled by performing proximity correction(307).

column12: TWEETER SPEAKER FOR VEHICLES
column13: PURPOSE: A tweeter speaker is provided to discharge the heat regardless of the arrangement of a soundproof pad by forming vents in various directions. CONSTITUTION: A quadrant inner cover(100) is fixed in a door panel of a vehicle. A speaker unit(200) is mounted in the quadrant inner cover. A soundproof pad(300) is formed between the door panel and the quadrant inner cover. A vent(310) is formed in the soundproof pad for discharging the heat generated from the speaker unit. The vent includes a main vent(311) and a sub vent(312). The main vent faces the speaker unit. The sub vent is formed in the main vent in a width direction of the soundproof pad. The sub vent is separately formed to the penetration direction of the main vent.

column12: INSPECTION PRESSING DEVICE
column13: The present invention relates to an inspection pressing device and, more specifically, to an inspection pressing device for pressing, toward an inspection apparatus, a device to be inspected, the inspection pressing device having a valve structure, which slides along a valve accommodation space and is in a no-load state while moving between an open position and a closed position.

column12: AN AUTOMATIC PRUNING SHEARS
column13: PURPOSE: Automatic pruning scissors capable of adjusting the location of an operation blade by the thickness of tree branches is provided to enable users to easily cut the tree branches by a simple switch manipulation process. CONSTITUTION: Automatic pruning scissors comprise the following: a fixed blade(30) fixed to one side of a storage case; an operation blade(40) rotatably installed on the fixed blade; a drive motor(50) installed on the other side of the storage case for the forward and reverse rotation; a gear unit(60) with one end connected to the drive motor, and the other end connected to the operation blade for rotating the operation blade by the drive force of the drive motor; a controller(70) controlling the operation of the drive motor; a drive control switch(72) controlling the drive motor; a position control switch adjusting the location of the operation blade; the storage case(24) for storing the fixed blade, the operation blade, the drive motor, the gear unit, and the controller; and a cover case(26) for covering the storage case.

column12: Circuit chess board
column13: The elements used in this patent are nodes, stretchable electric wires, bendable wire connectors and a base. The purposes of this designation which can be easily understood by the first figure is trying to let people can easily assemble their circuit based on schematic; people even can make their schematic be one part of this circuit as shown in Fig. 1. As a whole, (1) what you see is what you get, so that it can be debugged easily; (2) no soldering, make all the elements recyclable; (3) if the stretchable wire is used with the bendable wire connector, we can reduce the possibility to make specific wire by ourselves; (4) easy to plug the stretchable wires into your circuit.

column12: MOCK BULLET OF A TANK FOR CHARGING BULLETS HAVING AN ELECTRIC DETONATOR AND LOADING THE MAIN ARMAMENT OF THE TANK DUE TO A SIMILAR SHAPE WITH THE BULLET OF THE MAIN ARMAMENT
column13: PURPOSE: A mock bullet of a tank is provided to reduce the training cost by charging bullets having an electric detonator instead of an expensive mock bullet and to increase reality of the training by making the mock bullet similar to the main armament bullets and charging the actual main armament. CONSTITUTION: A mock bullet of a tank is composed of a mock bullet mold(10) having an exterior shape of the main armament bullet of the tank; a long pipe-shaped gun path(20) formed in the mock bullet mold to have the caliber enough to pass the bullets; a power chamber(30) connected to the gun path and formed in the size enough to fit actual bullets; and a stub case(40) positioned in the rear side of the mock bullet mold to fix the bullets and mounted with an electric detonator structure(43) for transmitting electric shock to the bullets.

column12: Low-resistance carbon grounding module and method for manufacturing the same
column13: The present invention provides a low-resistance carbon grounding module and a method for manufacturing the same, which can increase strength for durability against external environmental changes by varying the type and mixing ratio of raw materials for a carbon resistor without using any heat source. The low-resistance carbon grounding module comprises a carbon resistor extending in the longitudinal direction thereof and a conductive core bar installed in the center of the transverse section of the carbon resistor, wherein the carbon resistor comprises graphite, cement, and feldspar. Thus, it is possible to prevent the durability from being deteriorated due to external environmental changes, water, or electrical resistance, thus improving the quality and reliability of the product while minimizing the production of CO 2 .

column12: Semiconductor device having control bitline to prevent floating body effect
Method for fabricating a semiconductor device using a modeling algorithm to model the proximity effect from the sub-layer
column13: A method for forming a circuit layout comprises performing process proximity effect modeling based on process proximity effects caused by a sub-layer, wherein the sub-layer comprises an active layer positioned under a gate poly, and wherein performing the process proximity effect modeling includes calculating a pattern density of the sub-layer, incorporating results of the process proximity effect modeling into a modeling algorithm, and performing proximity correction using the results to manipulate a layout of a mask to be used when forming the circuit layout by photolithography.

column12: CARBON GROUNDING MODULE FOR IMPEDANCE REDUCTION TYPE
column13: PURPOSE: An impedance reduction type carbon earth module is provided to have a discharging member which has good conductivity more than carbon resistance, thereby current due to surface effect of carbon resistance is discharged more rapidly to the ground. CONSTITUTION: A carbon resistance(100) is formed extensively according to the longitudinal direction. A conductive cored bar(200) is installed in transverse section central part of the carbon resistance to the longitudinal direction. A discharging member(300) covers the adhesive state about the outer circumference of the carbon resistance. A metal sheet(310) copes with the outer shape and is transformed.

column12: Supercooling system
column13: The present invention relates to a supercooling system and a method for displaying a supercooled state which can accurately display a supercooled state of a stored object in spite of the external influence. The supercooling system includes a cooling apparatus including a storing unit storing a stored object, a cooling means cooling the storing unit, and a main control unit receiving external commercial power and controlling the cooling means to maintain the temperature in the storing unit at a temperature below at least the maximum ice crystal formation zone, and a supercooling apparatus including an independent storage room having a storing space therein to store an object and mounted and cooled in the storing unit, a temperature sensing unit sensing the temperature of the independent storage room, a temperature control means mounted in the independent storage room and controlling the internal temperature, a display unit displaying the state of the current control, and a sub-control unit controlling the temperature control means based on the sensed temperature from the temperature sensing unit to store the object received in the independent storage room in a supercooled state, and displaying the state of the stored object on the display unit with the proceeding of the cooling of the stored object or the storing space.

column12: CONNECTOR FOR ELECTRICAL CONNECTION

The connector includes a plurality of elastic conductive portions and an elastic insulating portion. The plurality of elastic conductive portions are conductive in a vertical direction. The elastic insulating portion separates and insulates the plurality of elastic conductive portions in a horizontal direction. The elastic insulating portion includes a plurality of electromagnetic wave shielding portions, and the plurality of electromagnetic wave shielding portions include a plurality of magnetic carbon nanotubes distributed and arranged in a vertical direction.

LIGHTNING PROTECTING APPARATUS FOR SPREADING LIGHTNING CURRENT FOR CABLE-STAYED BRIDGE
column13: According to the present invention, a lightning protecting apparatus for distributing lighting current comprises: a lightning rod (40) installed in a cable-stayed bridge; a ground body (80) for facilitating an electrical connection between the lightning rod and the earth; a down conductor (50) for connecting the lightning rod and the ground body; a support cable (30) for connecting a tower of the cable-stayed bridge and an upper plate of the bridge; a lightning inducing line (60) for protection on the support cable which is supported on the uppermost support cable among the multiple support cables by one or more insulating supports (90) and is connected in a lower part of the lightning rod (40) and the down conductor (50); and a conductor (70) for distributing current established in the support cable connected to the down conductor (50) and the ground body (80) in both end parts of the support cable, thereby minimizing current that flows in the support cable, especially, in an assembly of a steel wire forming the support cable, so as to secure stability of the cable-stayed bridge.

column12: TESTING SOCKET AND CONDUCTIVE PARTICLES

The testing socket comprises: a plurality of conductive parts distanced from each other in the planar direction at each location corresponding to a terminal of a device to be tested, and having a plurality of conductive particles arrayed in the width-wise direction in flexible insulating material; and insulating support parts, placed between the plurality of conductive parts distanced from each other, for supporting each conductive part and insulating same in the planar direction, wherein each conductive particle comprises: a columnar trunk part; and two or more protrusions protruding from the top end of the trunk part, wherein between the adjacent protrusions is a groove which is recessed toward the trunk, and the angle between the opposing inner surfacesof the adjacent protrusions is an obtuse angle of greater than 90 DEG.

The method of manufacturing a door for an electronic product comprises: a stainless steel plate preparing step of preparing a stainless steel plate made of metal; a surface roughness-forming step of polishing both surfaces of the stainless steel plate to form surface roughness; a film layer forming step of forming a film layer on one surface of the stainless steel plate to cover a surface forming the surface roughness; a door body forming step of forming the stainless steel plate into a door body having a foam space formed therein, and exposing the film layer to the foam space; and a foam step of foaming insulation foam in the foam space to fill the foam space. column12: Apparatus for measuring energy resolving power of X-ray monochromator and solid sample using in the same
column13: Provided is an apparatus for measuring an energy resolving power of X-ray monochromator and a solid sample used for the same. The apparatus comprises an X-ray generator, a monochromator to select a X-ray discharged from the X-ray generator, a main chamber to which the selected X-ray by the monochromator is injected, a solid sample disposed in the main chamber where the selected X-ray is injected for measuring the energy resolving power of the monochromator, and equipments to analyze and handle data obtained from the solid sample while the X-ray is injected to the solid sample. The solid sample is composed of a plurality of atoms, wherein a molecule having at least two atoms exists between the plurality of atoms.

column12: DEVICE FOR PREVENTING ARTICLES FROM BEING LOST
column13: PURPOSE: A device for preventing articles from being lost is provided to equip detectors in detection-targeted objects such as notebooks and bags and to equip controllers on users or detecting subjects, so as to previously prevent precious articles from being lost. CONSTITUTION: A first sensor(11) of a detector(1) senses a vibration of a detection-targeted article, and outputs an electrical signal. A first communicator(12) transceives data with a controller(2) through an antenna(ANT1). A first signal processor(13) processes the electrical signal and synthesizes the electrical signal with a preset inherent code, then transmits the synthesized signal to the controller. The first signal processor processes an alarm signal generated from the controller and outputs the alarm signal to a backside. A first alarming unit(14) displays an alarm with a vibration alarm, a light emitting alarm, and an alarming sound according to the alarm signal. The controller equipped in a detecting subject detects movements of the article, and compares presently-detected information with movement state information of the detector. If differences between the two information are bigger than a setup value, the controller drives a self alarming unit and transmits the alarm signal from the detector.

column12: System and method of monitoring, predicting and optimizing production yields in a liquid crystal display (LCD) manufacturing process
column13: A system and method of monitoring LCD production yields, predicting the effects of different testing methodologies on LCD production yields, and optimizing production yields is provided that compares the effect of different testing methodologies on the yields at various stages in the LCD testing and assembly process. The present invention can also be used to predict the effect of different testing methodologies on user-defined parameters, such as profit.

column12: BATTERY OPERATED CORDLESS BRUSH CUTTER
column13: PURPOSE: A cordless bush cutter using a battery is provided to reduce the noise and vibration of a motor and remove exhaust gas by using an electric motor. CONSTITUTION: A DC electric motor is installed in the middle or rear side of a bush cutter operation rod pipe(11). The grass, weeds or scrubs are cut by rotating a blade(23) with power from a motor. A bush cutter includes an emergency motor stop or transmission control function. A radiation fin is installed on both end covers of the motor or outside a drive motor.

column12: ANISOTROPIC CONDUCTIVE SHEET COMPRISING CONDUCTIVE PARTICLES INCLUDING DIFFERENT KINDS OF PARTICLES MIXED THEREIN
column13: An embodiment provides an anisotropic conductive sheet for electrically connecting a terminal of a device to be tested and a pad of a testing device, the sheet comprising a plurality of conductive portions which are formed in a thickness direction inside an insulating support portion and comprise multiple conductive particles, wherein the conductive particles are implemented by mixed particles including a highly-conductive metal and magnetic particles.

column12: MANUFACTURING METHOD OF SPECIMEN FOR TRANSMISSION ELECTRON MICROSCOPY
column13: A method for manufacturing specimens for a transmission electron microscope for observing images of a sectional surface of an inorganic pigment is provided to realize thickness measurement, component analysis, and sectional structure analysis precisely by a transmission electron microscope by manufacturing specimens having a thickness of 150nm or less in a relatively simple manner. A method for manufacturing specimens for a transmission electron microscope for observing images of a sectional surface of an inorganic pigment includes the steps of preparing a silicon dummy specimen in the circular plate shape, in which a silicon dummy stack is fixed in a metal ring, mechanically polishing both surfaces of the silicon dummy specimen into a predetermined thickness, making the thickness thinner to form a concave groove in the center of one of the surfaces by dimpling, and obtaining a final specimen with a thickness for transmitting electron beams by carrying out ion beam polishing on the dimpled surface.

column12: BAMBOO PILLOW
column13: PURPOSE: Provided is a bamboo pillow having an effect on keeping cool and stimulating a specific acupoint on human body when a user takes a nap or to sleep with it on a hot summer day. This pillow having the nickname of "bamboo wife"(jukbuin, Korean native name) is made from a bamboo, a coil spring, cushion material and an acupressure. CONSTITUTION: A tubular type body part(11) is formed with a mesh web to be opened on both sides. An opening part is formed in a longitudinal direction on one side on the outer surface of the body part and a plurality of pocket parts(14) with a space in a longitudinal direction are formed on the outer surface of the body part and a coil spring(13) is inserted into the inside of the body part to form the shape of a body part. Acupressure balls(15) such as ceramic, jade or magnetic are inserted into a pocket part(14).

column12: Pogo pin, the fabrication method thereof and test socket using the same
column13: Disclosed is a pogo pin including: a hollow body having a spring structure by spirally cutting at least a portion of an outer surface thereof; and a conductive material filling at least an inside of the body. According to the present invention, when testing a semiconductor package, error rate in contact between the package, the pogo pin and a test board can be remarkably reduced, and simultaneously can enhance rigidity and electrical conductivity of the pogo pin. Further, simple componentry of the pogo pin can facilitate its fabrication, reduce fabrication costs, and even foresee fabrication of a micro-pogo pin.

column12: SOCKET FOR ELECTRICAL TEST
column13: According to one embodiment of the present invention, provided is a socket for test, comprising: a plurality of conductive elastic units arranged on a position corresponding to a terminal of a test target device, and having a plurality of conductive particles arranged in an insulating elastic material in a vertical direction; an elastic support unit for supporting the conductive elastic units while surrounding the conductive elastic units; an insulation support unit formed with a first insertion hole to which lower parts of the conductive elastic units are inserted and supported, and formed with a second insertion hole which is disposed on a lower part of the first insertion hole and to which a pad of an inspection device is inserted; a plurality of guide units coupled to an upper surface of the insulation support unit, and guiding a movement of a terminal of the test target device; and a conductive pad supported and fixed to the guide units such that a conductive unit is arranged on upper surfaces of the conductive elastic units, and configured to be detached from the guide units.

column12: SUPER FINISHING APPARATUS
column13: PURPOSE: A super-finishing apparatus is provided to facilitate the initial setup of workpieces by maintaining the constant pressure of a super-finishing wheel against the curved surface orbit of workpieces. CONSTITUTION: A super-finishing apparatus(2) comprises a super-finishing wheel(6), a wheel axle(8), a pressure holding unit(10) and a damper. The super-finishing wheel processes a workpiece(4). The super-finishing wheel is installed in the wheel axle. The wheel axle is connected to the piston rod of a pressurizing cylinder. The pressure holding unit operates the pressurizing cylinder through a pressure driving unit(12) with the hydraulic pressure and maintains a present processing location of the super-finishing wheel. The elastic body of a damper is inserted in the cylinder main body of a pressurizing cylinder into the piston rod. The damper minutely adjusts the present processing location of the super-finishing wheel.

column12: Liquid crystal display module including hook assembly
column13: A liquid crystal display device includes a liquid crystal display panel, a backlight unit under the liquid crystal display panel, a bottom frame under the backlight unit, a main frame surrounding portions of the liquid crystal display panel and the backlight unit, and a top frame covering top edge portions of the liquid crystal display panel. column12: VERTICAL TRANSISTOR OF SEMICONDUCTOR DEVICE AND METHOD FOR FORMING THE SAME
column13: A vertical transistor of a semiconductor device and a method for forming the same are disclosed. The vertical transistor comprises a silicon fin disposed on a semiconductor substrate, a source region disposed in the semiconductor substrate below a lower portion of the silicon fin, a drain region disposed in an upper portion of the silicon fin, a channel region disposed in a sidewall of the silicon fin between the source region and the drain region, a gate oxide film disposed in a surface of the semiconductor substrate and the sidewall of the silicon fin, and a pair of gate electrodes disposed on the gate oxide films.

column12: Electric test socket and method of manufacturing conductive particles for electric test socket
column13: The present invention relates to an electric test socket and a method of manufacturing conductive particles for electric test sockets. column12: AN ALKALINE ELECTROLYTIC LIQUID WASHING COMPOSITION
column13: PURPOSE: An environment-friendly alkaline electrolytic liquid cleansing composition is provided to prevent water pollution and environmental contamination and to wash various contaminants. column13: 본 발명은 음양곽의 엑기스를 활성성분으로 함유하고 통상의 부형제를 보조성분으로 함유하는 간세포보호제에 관한 것으로, 음양곽을 물, 저급알칸올, 헥산 및 클로로포롬에서 선택된 통상의 용매로 추출 하여 얻어진 엑기스를 약제학적 또는 식품공학적으로 사용가능한 통상의 보조제와 혼합하여 통상의 식품공학적 또는 약제학적 제형으로 제제화한 간세포보호제제를 제공한다. 본 발명에 있어서, 음양곽 엑기스를 활성성분으로 하는 간세포보호제는 음양곽 엑기스의 새로운 용도를 제공한다.

column12: APPARATUS FOR HIGH FREQUENCY TREATMENT OF OBESITY PREVENTING SPARK
