column12: MATCH BOX
Circuits and methods providing reduced power consumption for driving flat panel displays
column13: Circuits and methods are provided for driving flat panel displays (e.g., a liquid crystal display (LCD)), which provide reduced power consumption for driving data lines and common electrodes of flat panel displays. Source driving circuits and methods for driving data lines and circuits and methods for driving a common electrode use both intermediate reference voltages and boosted driving voltages in each driving cycle (as opposed to entirely using boosted driving voltages) to reduce power consumption and provide charge recycling.

column12: LOCATION RECOGNITION SYSTEM
column13: The present invention relates to a position recognition system. The position recognition system comprises: a laser light source unit to emit laser light; a light division unit to divide the laser light to emit the divided laser light to a monitoring area, and allow the divided laser light to form a plurality of spots having a grid pattern in the monitoring area; an image acquisition unit to photograph the spots having the grid pattern to acquire image data; and a position recognition unit to detect a position change of at least one among the spots based in the image data, and recognize a position of a target body by the detected position change of the spot.

column12: APPARATUS FOR LEAKAGE-CURRENT PREVENTION IN THE LIQUID CRYSTAL DISPLAY EQUIPMENT
BIPOLAR LIGHTNING ARRESTER COATED WITH MAGNETIC MATERIAL
column13: The present invention relates to a lightning arrester that self-discharges electric charges caused by the close approach of a thundercloud before a lightning strike occurs, thereby preventing the lightning strike. To this end, the present invention provides a bipolar lightning arrester coated with a magnetic material, comprising: a conductive rod that is installed on the upper end portion of an object to be protected from a lightning strike and is connected to a ground means; an insulator coupled to one end of the rod; and a charged plate having one side coated with a magnetic material, wherein the charged plate is charged according to the close approach of a thundercloud and electrically performs preliminary discharge to the rod.

column12: Structure for TFT-LCD
column13: A structure for a thin film transistor LCD includes a data line extending in a first direction; a source electrode protruded for a predetermined length from the data line; a gate electrode in a second direction so as to be overlapped with a portion of the source electrode and the data line; and a drain electrode of which a portion is overlapped with the gate electrode. The drain electrode is bent according to the contours of the data line and the source so that wider channel can be obtained even without increasing the width of the gate electrode. A pixel electrode is connected to a region of the drain which is not overlapped With the gate electrode and positioned at the inner side of the region forming the data line and the gate electrode.

column12: CHARGE PUMP CIRCUIT AND METHOD FOR CHARGE PUMPING
column13: PURPOSE: A charge pump circuit and a method for charge pumping are provided to generate a booted voltage having a stable level regardless of the change of a boost voltage ratio by allowing a capacitor to have a period in which a charged voltage level is changed in advance. CONSTITUTION: In a charge pump circuit and a method for charge pumping, a plurality of capacitors(C11,C12,C13) perform a voltage boosting operation. A switch control part(310) responses to a boosting ratio and generates a plurality of switch control signals. A switch element(320) controls a plurality of capacitors.

column12: Alternating current power control device
column13: An alternating current power control device comprising a phase comparison controller for comparing a phase of an input voltage with that of a first reference voltage, a single-winding transformer for varying the input voltage, a mutual induction reactor for lowering the input voltage by a desired level in response to an output voltage from the single-winding transformer, an output voltage comparator for comparing an output voltage with a second reference voltage, an output current comparator for comparing an output current with a reference current, an OR logic controller for performing an OR operation with respect to output signals from the phase comparison controller and output current comparator, and a switch array for selectively transferring the output voltage from the single-winding transformer to the mutual induction reactor in response to output signals from the output voltage comparator and OR logic controller. According to the present invention, the mutual induction reactor is implemented on the basis of the principle of a linear transformer and has a small capacity corresponding to about 1/10 of a load power. Therefore, a proper power necessary to the saving of energy can be supplied by using the mutual induction reactor.

column12: Alternating current power control device
column13: An alternating current power control device including a phase comparison controller for comparing a phase of an input voltage with that of a first reference voltage, a single-winding transformer for varying the input voltage, a mutual induction reactor for lowering the input voltage by a desired level in response to an output voltage from the single-winding transformer, an output voltage comparator for comparing an output voltage with a second reference voltage, an output current comparator for comparing an output current with a reference current, an OR logic controller for performing an OR operation with respect to output signals from the phase comparison controller and output current comparator, and a switch array for selectively transferring the output voltage from the single-winding transformer to the mutual induction reactor in response to output signals from the output voltage comparator and OR logic controller. According to the present invention, the mutual induction reactor is implemented on the basis of the principle of a linear transformer and has a small capacity corresponding to about 1/10 of a load power. Therefore, a proper power necessary to the saving of energy can be supplied by using the mutual induction reactor.

column12: TRANSMISSION DISTANCE EXTENDING APPARATUS OF S-INTERFACE IN PRIVATE N-ISDN
column13: 본 발명은 S인터페이스의 전송거리 확장에 관한 것으로, 특히 PBX((Private Branch Exchange : 구내 교환기)의 고속 데이타 통신에 적당하도록 한 구내 NISDN(Narrow band Integrated Services Digital Network : 협대역 종합 정보 통신망) 서비스에서 S인터페이스의 전송거리 확장장치에 관한 것이다. 본 발명의 목적은 S인터페이스와 U인터페이스를 양쪽으로 접속하고 있는 NTE(Network Termination Equipment)를 PBX와 TE(Terminal Equipment)사이에 접속 가능하도록 하여 보다 넓은 서비스 영역을 가질 수 있도록 하는 장치를 제공함으로써 S인터페이스의 전송거리 한계의 문제점을 극복하고자 하는 것이다. 이에 따라, U인터페이스를 제공하는 NTE를 PBX에 적용함으로써 S인터페이스의 거리 한계가 연장되어 보다 넓은 구내 내에서의 NISDN 서비스 제공이 가능하게 된다.

column12: LIGHTING APPARATUS FOR THE BOAT PASTEURIZATION AND ILLUMINATION
column13: 본 고안은 사용 목적을 달리하는 복수의 조명등이 동시에 수용되는 등기구에 관한 것으로, 특히 살균등 및 조명등이 각각 수용될 수 있도록 등기구 본체를 균등하게 구획분할하고 본체 개방부에는 커버가 삽탈가능하게 체결수단이 일체로 압출성형된 살균 및 조명 겸용등기구에 관한 것으로, 이는 일체로 사출성형된 격리판에 의해 장방향으로 양분되고 상기 격리판과 본체 하단부의 내측면에 걸림턱이 형성된 본체와, 상기 본체의 하단부 걸림턱에 끼워맞춤식으로 탄접고정되게 탄편을 갖는 커버로 이루어지며; 양분된 본체의 일측 수용홈 양측면에는 소켓을 체결하기 위한 브라켓트를 설치하고 타측 수용홈에는 살균등의 길이를 감안한 간격으로 소켓을 체결하기 위한 브라켓트를 설치하며, 상기 브라켓트 외측 양공간에는 안정기 및 스타트램프와 커버 외측으로 스위치가 돌출시키며 자외선이 조사되는 부분에 내측면으로 별도의 커버가 탄접고정되는 걸림턱이 구비된 개구부가 형성되어 있으며, 본체 외측으로는 내향으로 개구된 캡이 본체 양측면에 착탈가능하게 설치되도록 하는데 특징이 있는 것이다.

column12: Sterilization and deodorization method for confined area
column13: PURPOSE: A method for deodorizing sterilization of a fixed place is provided to protect a user from ozone or ultraviolet rays generated in case of operating an ozone generating instrument and a ultraviolet rays generating instrument by operating the ozone and ultraviolet rays generating instruments in case that there isn't the user in the fixed space. CONSTITUTION: In the method for deodorizing sterilization of the fixed place, a body sensor(10), a control portion(20), an ozone generating portion(30), an ultraviolet rays generating portion(40), a timer(50) and an instrument(60) for crime prevention are included. The body sensor(10) senses if there is a body in the using space or not and outputs the sensed signal. The control portion(20) outputs the control signal selectively if the signal sensed in the body sensor(10) is output. The ozone generating instrument(30) is operated selectively according to the output of the control portion. The ultraviolet rays generating portion(40) is operated according to the output of the control portion. The timer(50) stops the operating of the ozone generating portion(30) and the ultraviolet rays generating portion(40) if the set time goes by. The instrument(60) for crime prevention informs the invasion of the other person to the set telephone number if the control signal for informing rising of the temperature in the using space is output.

column12: Weight Memory System Used Capacitance and Operating Method Thereof
column13: 커패시터의 용량을 감소시키고, 증폭기의 작은 스윙폭을 갖는 정전용량을 이용한 가중치 메모리 시스템 및 이의 동작방법이 개시된다. 신경망을 구성하는 시냅스 가중치 소자로서 개별 비트 라인에 공통 연결된 두 커패시터로 구성된 용량성 차동쌍을 도입하고, 용량성 차동쌍에 각각 연결된 쌍을 이루는 워드 라인에 차동 형태의 전압 펄스를 입력하여 비트 라인에 커플링 동작을 유도한다. 커플링 동작을 통해 비트 라인에 누적 합산되는 전체 전하량은 용량성 차동쌍을 이루는 두 커패시턴스의 차이인 차동 모드의 커패시턴스와 해당 차동쌍에 입력되는 전압 펄스의 곱들의 합산에 해당하기 때문에, 커플링 동작이 이루어지는 시냅스 가중치 소자가 비트 라인에 다수개 연결되더라도 비트 라인에서 출력되는 전체 전하량은 크게 감소한다. 따라서, 전체 전하 변동량을 저장하는 피드백 커패시터의 크기를 줄일 수 있다. 또한, 감소된 전체 전하 변동량에 의해 출력 전압의 변동폭을 감소시킬 수 있기 때문에 출력 전압의 스윙폭도 감소시킬 수 있다.

column12: COLOR CHANGEABLE TEST SOKET AND METHOD FOR MANUFACTURING THEREOF
column13: The present invention relates to a test socket which includes a color changeable material and represents an opaque color at a normal temperature and in which the color is changed to the other color according to test conditions such as light and temperature. Accordingly, when testing a BGA-type semiconductor element and also the other kinds of semiconductor elements, a test socket keeps an opaque state at a normal temperature. Therefore, when photographing a test socket by a photographing device, it is possible to accurately confirm a replacement state of the semiconductor element, and also it is possible to accurately determine whether there is a defect such as short and bridge of the semiconductor element. In addition, since the test socket keeps the opaque state at the normal temperature, it is possible to keep security for the semiconductor element, and it is possible to simply and easily perform a test of the semiconductor element by changing a kind and a color of a color-changed material included in the test socket according to test conditions such as light and temperature. Moreover, when the test socket is configured such that a color is changed according to the change in temperature, it is possible to obtain information about a heating state of the semiconductor element according to the change in temperature without separate additional equipment, it is possible to easily and accurately perform a temperature test of the semiconductor element, and it is possible to improve reliability of the temperature test.

column12: Source driver, common voltage driver, and method of driving display device using time division driving method
column13: A source driver and a common voltage driver for a display device using a time division driving method, in which the source driver outputs an analog voltage corresponding to digital image data to a corresponding source line out of a plurality of source lines, after precharging the corresponding source line with a predetermined voltage. The common voltage driver discretely and sequentially increases or decreases the common voltage. By using the source driver and the common voltage driver, the power consumed upon driving of the display device can be reduced.

column12: Composition for topical spray for preventing or treating of atopic dermatitis comprising synbiotics fermentation product
column13: A spray agent containing a Synbio-glucan composition of the present invention has an effect of relieving and alleviating itching caused by atopic dermatitis when topically administered to the skin of an animal model with atopic dermatitis, and thus excellently alleviates erythema, lichenification, abrasions, and hair loss of skin lesions. Therefore, the spray agent can be usefully used as a composition for topical spray for preventing or treating atopic dermatitis.

column12: TEST SOCKET
column13: A test socket is configured to be disposed between a test target device and a test apparatus for electrically connecting terminals of the test target device to pads of the test apparatus. The test socket includes: a support sheet formed of an insulative material and including penetration holes at positions corresponding to the terminals of the test target device; inserts including first conductive parts and elastic insulative parts, wherein the first conductive parts are disposed in the penetration holes of the support sheet and formed by arranging a plurality of first conductive particles in an insulative elastic material in a thickness direction of the support sheet, and the elastic insulative parts are formed of an insulative elastic material and disposed between the first conductive parts and inner walls of the penetration holes to surround the first conductive parts; and an anisotropic sheet including second conductive parts and an insulative support part, wherein the second conductive parts are disposed under the first conductive parts and formed by arranging a plurality of second conductive particles in an insulative elastic material in a thickness direction of the anisotropic sheet at positions corresponding to the penetration holes, and the insulative support part is disposed under the support sheet to support and insulate the second conductive parts.

column12: RESTORATION METHOD FOR CHARACTER IMAGE DAMAGED THROUGH THE LINE
column13: PURPOSE: A restoration method of a character image damaged by line is provided to improve recognition ability by using cross point of border of boundary line of character and boundary line of line. CONSTITUTION: A preliminary character is extracted by getting histogram of black pixel against lateral axis and longitudinal axis of image when inputting binary image data. A part to be contacted and folded with the extracted preliminary character is divided with line component and the others is divided with character component(S23). An average thickness of the preliminary character is gotten by using character component that is divided above(S24). A cross point of border of boundary line of character and outline line of line is gotten from line component divided from above(S25). A kind of line component element is classified with basis on cross point of border(S26). And then a damaged character is restored to an original character image by using line component element(S27).

column12: Apparatus for adjusting focus of camera module
column13: The present invention relates to an apparatus for adjusting a focus of a camera module, and more specifically, to an apparatus for adjusting a focus of a camera module, adjusting a focus of a camera module including: a sensor body including an image sensor; and a lens barrel coupled to the sensor body through a screw and having a lens positioned on a position corresponding to the image sensor. The apparatus for adjusting a focus of a camera module comprises a housing and a collection means. The housing comprises a base part and a cover part. The base part has the camera module mounted thereon to maintain a position of the camera module. The cover part is arranged on an upper side of the base part to cover the base part and has a center hole formed on a part where the lens barrel of the camera module is arranged to allow the camera module to be exposed to the outside. The collection means is arranged on the cover part to be rotated and relatively rotates the lens barrel with respect to the sensor body while being in contact with a side surface of the lens barrel. When the collection means is in contact with the side surface of the lens barrel to be rotated, the lend barrel together with the collection means perform relative rotation with respect to the sensor body to change a relative distance between the lens and the image sensor, thereby adjusting the focus of the camera module.

column12: LEATHER WATCH BAND AND MANUFACTURING METHOD THEREOF
column13: The present invention relates to a method for manufacturing leather watch bands, which comprises the following steps: forming a bonded skin (10) having a round by adhering a leather inner skin (11) and a leather outer skin (12) in close contact with a frame (20) having a round; and cutting the bonded skin (10) and sewing the cut skin with a thread to form a plurality of stitches. According to the present invention, the leather watch band is comfortable to wear from beginning of wearing and is not wrinkled on the inside thereof, thereby providing an advantage of elegant aesthetics. In addition, possibility of thread bursting and peeling due to a pressure difference between inner and outer stitches is reduced, thereby providing an advantage of significantly reducing a defect rate.

column12: LUBRICATING SYSTEM OF A CAR
Semiconductor device having control bitline to prevent floating body effect
column13: A vertical semiconductor device is provided. The semiconductor device includes a cell array including a control bit line connected to cells and electrically isolated from a bit line, and a floating body control circuit for applying a floating control voltage to the control bit line in a predetermined period.

column12: FOLDING TYPE BASKETBALL SUPPORT
FAR-INFRARED RADIATIVE CERAMIC COMPOSITION AND ITS METHOD
column13: 본 발명은 알루미나 76∼88중량%, 산화마그네슘 1.8∼2.2중량%, 산화칼슘 1.8∼2.0중량%, 산화나트륨 1.0~1.4중량%, 산화칼륨 0.1∼0.3중량%, 철분 0.1∼0.3중량% 및 실리카 6∼8중량%를 함유하는 천연광물 분말 7∼10중량%; 증류수 83∼86중량%; 항균조제 1∼2중량%; 우레탄실리콘수지 1∼2중량%; 및 이온화촉매제 2∼3중량%를 혼합하여, 그리고 선택적으로 쾌적향 원료와 대전방지제를 더 첨가하여 조성하는 것으로, 이들을 1,2차 교반에 의해 이온화시켜 방치함으로써 제조된다.이렇게 제조되는 원적외선 방사 조성물은 항균, 방취 기능 및 대전방지 기능이 있어 섬유에 적용시 독특한 천연향기가 발생되어 기분 좋은 향기와 상쾌함 등을 줄수 있을 뿐 아니라 신체 주위의 각종냄새를 제거하여 쾌적한 생활을 영위할 수 있도록 하고, 기존 원료에 비해 가격이 훨씬 싸서 대증화에 용이함은 물론 중성으로 제조 가능하여 섬유 전 분야에 부작용 없이 널리 이용될 수 있는 효과를 갖는다.

column12: Lightning rod
Circuits and methods for driving flat panel displays
column13: Circuits and methods for driving gates lines of a flat panel display, wherein gate driver circuit architectures provide compact designs that enable smaller chip sizes for gate driver ICs. In one aspect, a semiconductor integrated gate driver IC comprises a plurality of gate driver circuits, wherein each gate driver circuit drives a corresponding gate line of a display, and a level shifter circuit, for generating a precharge control signal for the gate driver circuits. Each gate driver circuit comprises a line decoder for decoding a gate line control signal and generating a decoded gate line control signal and a precharge circuit for precharging a gate driver turn-on voltage in response to the precharge control signal before activating the gate line. During a driving phase, the precharged gate driver turn-on voltage is discharged when the gate line is activated in response to the decoded gate line control signal, whereas the precharged gate driver turn-on voltage is maintained when thegate line is not activated in response to the decoded gate line control signal.

HEAT EXCHANGER
column13: PURPOSE: A heat exchanger using carbon heating element is provided to rapidly heat water and air passing through the inside of a pipe, since a conduit is efficiently heated by a carbon heating element wound outside the conduit. CONSTITUTION: A heat exchanger using carbon heating element(1) comprises a conduit(2). The conduit is formed of a flat pipe or a bellows pipe(22). The carbon heating element winds the outside of a conduit and heats air and water passing through the inside of the conduit. A spiral groove(23) is formed in the bellows pipe, and the carbon heating element is wound in the spiral groove. The spiral groove is inclined in the direction for the flow of water and air.

column12: PLASMA PROCESSING APPARATUS
column13: PURPOSE: A plasma processing apparatus is provided to improve productivity by increasing a period stopping equipment in order to replace with a new source tablet by having a hearth including multiple dipping holes arranged along a circumference and being formed to be able to rotate and replace a source tablet stored in dipping holes. CONSTITUTION: A plasma processing apparatus(100) includes a processing chamber(110) processing a plasma process; a hearth(120) arranged inside of a process chamber(110), including multiple dipping holes arranged along a circumference, and formed to replace a source table(ST) stored in dipping holes by being formed to be rotatable; a plasma gun(130) including a gas supply part(133) for supplying plasma-generating gas and an electrode for changing plasma-generating gas into a plasma state, and supplying a plasma(P) to a processing chamber(110); and a power supply part(140) for discharging by applying an electric potential difference to a place between an electrode and a source tablet dipped in the hearth, operating the source tablet with an anode, and operating the electrode with a cathode.

column12: CONDUCTIVITY RUBBOR SOCKET, BACK LIGHT UNIT AND LIQUID CRYSTAL DISPLAY DEVICE USING THE SAME
column13: A conductivity rubber socket, a backlight unit, and a liquid crystal display device using the same are provided to simplify the assembly, and improve the productivity by using the conductivity rubber for a socket material. A backlight unit of a liquid crystal display device comprises a conductive rubber socket(100), and a body portion(102). The body portion is integrated with the conductive rubber. A lead wire is inserted to an inserting part(104). A lamp is inserted at an settling unit(106). The lead wire is connected to a connection part(108). A socket fixing unit(110) supports a body portion.

column12: FOREIGN SUBSTANCE CLEANING SHEET FOR TEST SOCKET
column13: The present invention relates to a foreign substance cleaning sheet for a test socket and, more specifically, to a foreign substance cleaning sheet for a test socket, the foreign substance cleaning sheet being used in a test socket in order to remove foreign substances from the surface of the test socket, the test socket comprising a plurality of conductive portions in which a plurality of conductive particles are blended with silicone rubber and are arranged in the thickness direction at locations corresponding to terminals of a device to be tested, and insulation portions respectively supporting and insulating the conductive portions, and the foreign substance cleaning sheet comprising: a base sheet having a size corresponding to the size of the surface having foreign substances in the test socket; an adhesive sheet arranged on a surface of the base sheet and having adhesive strength so as to remove the foreign substances from the surface of the test socket; and protruding adhesive portions which are provided at each one of the positions on the adhesive sheet corresponding to the conductive portions of the test socket, and which protrude from the surface of the adhesive sheet and have a hemispherical shape and adhesive strength.

column12: A METHOD FOR PREPARING EXTRACT FOR THE PREVENTION AND TREATMENT OF HYPERLIPIDEMIA AND OBESITY FROM THE EXTRACT OF ASTER SPATHULIFOLIUS AERIAL PART AND COMPOSITION CONTAINING THE SAME
column13: The present invention relates to a method for preparing an extract of the aerial part of Aster spathulifolius effective in preventing and treating hyperlipidemia and obesity and a composition comprising the extract. Since most of salt which is originally abundant in Aster spathulifolius, phenolic compounds which are unstable and susceptible to oxidation, and mucous substances are simply removed by the preparation method in accordance with the present invention, the present invention can significantly increase the content of terpenes, or the active ingredient, and reduce production cost. The composition of the present invention can be used as functional food for aiding the prevention and treatment of hyperlipidemia- and obesity-related arteriosclerosis, cardiovascular disease, cerebral thrombosis, liver disease, thrombosis, diabetes, etc.

column12: TEST SOCKET
column13: Provided is a test socket for electrically connecting a device to be inspected and an inspection device. The test socket comprises: an insulation film having a first through hole and a second through hole that are spaced apart from each other in the horizontal direction; an elastic insulation sheet attached to the lower surface of the insulation film and having a third through hole communicating with the first through hole; and an anisotropic conductive sheet attached to the lower surface of the elastic insulation sheet and including a first conductive portion and an insulation portion. A second conductive portion connected to the first conductive portion is formed in the first through hole and the third through hole, the second through hole consists of an empty space, and the lower portion of the second through hole is blocked by the elastic insulation sheet.

column12: System and method of monitoring, predicting and optimizing production yields in a liquid crystal display (LCD) manufacturing process
column13: A system and method of monitoring LCD production yields, predicting the effects of different testing methodologies on LCD production yields, and optimizing production yields is provided that compares the effect of different testing methodologies on the yields at various stages in the LCD testing and assembly process. The present invention can also be used to predict the effect of different testing methodologies on user-defined parameters, such as profit.

column12: Source driver circuits and methods providing reduced power consumption for driving flat panel displays
column13: Circuits and methods are provided for driving flat panel displays (e.g., a liquid crystal display (LCD)), which provide reduced power consumption for driving data lines of flat panels displays. Source driving circuits and methods for driving data lines use both intermediate reference voltages and boosted driving voltages in each driving cycle (as opposed to entirely using boosted driving voltages) to reduce power consumption and provide charge recycling.

column12: Probe card for electrical test and probe head for probe card
column13: Provided is a probe head for fixing, to a circuit board assembly to be conductively connected to an inspection apparatus, a plurality of probes coming into contact with a device to be inspected. The probe head comprises a first plate, a second plate, nut members, and first bolt members. The first plate and the second plate maintain the plurality of probes. The second plate is placed below the first plate. The nut members are coupled to the second plate. The first bolt members are screw-coupled to the nut members at a first position and a second position through the circuit board assembly. The first bolt members are screw-coupled to the nut members at the first position such that the first plate and the second plate come into close contact with each other. The first bolt members are screw-coupled to the nut members at the second position such that the second plate is distanced from the first plate.

column12: A METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR CANCELLATION OF OFFSETS IN COMPARATORS
column13: A method and an apparatus for reducing offsets of comparators are provided to converge the offsets of the comparator to 0 by performing repeatedly basic operations for reducing offsets in a device including a plurality of comparators having different offset values. Two input terminals(31,32) of a comparator are precharged by the same voltage. A sign of an offset of the comparator is determined by using a sign of an output voltage by enabling the comparator while two input terminals have the same voltage. Charges of a channel region are captured by a gate dielectric and the drain current characteristic of the corresponding transistor is changed by applying stress.

column12: SYSTEM FOR ISSUING AND COLLECTING DISCOUNT TICKET OR ENTRANCE TICKET AND STORING ISSUED TICKET ON INTERNET SYSTEM BY USING MOBILE TERMINAL AND PHONE
column13: PURPOSE: A discount ticket or entrance ticket issuing and collecting system is provided to issue coupons via an SMS(Short Message Service) and to store the coupons at an internet system so that a user carries the coupons or checks the coupons though the user loses a mobile terminal. CONSTITUTION: A user accesses an internet system. The user transmits an identification number or a resident registration number to the internet system. The internet system stores the identification number or the resident registration number. The internet system generates a coupon number by using a coupon number generation algorithm. The internet system issues the coupon via an SMS and at the same time stores a specification on the generation of the coupon. A user shows the issued coupon on an LCD of a mobile terminal to a coupon issuer. The coupon issuer requests the internet system to approve the coupon. The coupon issuer offers a service or a commodity to the user according to a coupon approval result.

column12: Contact sheet and socket structure
column13: The present invention relates to a contact sheet and a socket structure. The contact sheet is configured to be brought into contact with a test target device including an electrode pattern having a predetermined arrangement for making electric connection with the test target device, the contact sheet being configured as a sheet having a predetermined area and thickness, the contact sheet including: a sheet body, as a main part of the contact sheet, having a predetermined area and formed of an insulative material; and a plurality of contact pattern elements arranged in the sheet body and configured to be electrically connected to the electrode pattern of the test target device, wherein the contact sheet has different thicknesses at an outer portion and a center portion of the contact sheet.

column12: DATA CACHE METHOD AND DEVICE FOR DATABASE SYSTEM
column13: PURPOSE: A data cache method for a database and a device thereof are provided to process questions which are transmitted to the database, thereby offering effective and fast responses. CONSTITUTION: A question analysis unit (210) analyzes an inputted question and distinguishes the same for the inquiry or for the update. When the inputted question is for the query, a cache management unit (230) confirms the inputted question in a cache storage unit (220). When the inputted question is stored in the cache storage unit, the cache management unit extracts and outputs result information according to the inputted question. When the inputted question is not stored in the cache storage unit, the cache management unit receives/outputs the result information by calling the inputted question to a database and registers the inputted question and the result information in the cache storage unit. column12: OUTPUT DRIVER FOR REDUCING COUPLING NOISE AND METHOD FOR REDUCING COUPLING NOISE
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide an output driver and method for reducing the coupling noise.

SOLUTION: The output driver for reducing the coupling noise comprises a first transistor, a second transistor, and a noise filter part. In the output driver, the first transistor has a first end connected to a first voltage, a second end connected to a first node, and data applied to the gate. The second transistor has a first end connected to the first node and a second end connected to the output node. The noise filter can be constituted of a capacitor connected between the gate of the first transistor and the gate of the second transistor. A coupling capacitor between the gate of the second transistor and the output node and a coupling capacitor between the gate of the second transistor and the first node can remove the coupling noise, which occurs on the gate of the second transistor, by using the data applied to the gate of the first transistor.

column12: System and method for classifying defects in and identifying process problems for an electrical circuit
column13: A method for performing circuit defect analysis and process problem identification includes applying a test signal to a circuit, obtaining a signal generated in response to the test signal, comparing the response signal to reference information, classifying a defect in the circuit based on a result of the comparing step, and identifying a problem in a manufacturing process which caused the defect based on the classification. The reference information may include one or more signal profiles corresponding to predefined types of defects that can occur during the manufacturing process. Defect classification is preferably performed by determining whether the response signal falls within one or more of the signal profiles. If the response signal falls within two or more signal profiles, then probabilities may be determined for each profile. The defect may then be classified as corresponding to the defect type whose signal profile has the highest probability. A processing system performs defect classification and process problem identification using a similar approach.

column12: OIL PUMP CONTROL SYSTEM FOR VEHICLE

CONSTITUTION: A system for controlling an oil pump for a vehicle includes the oil pump (110), an oil pressure control valve (112), and a controller (130). The oil pump feeds oil to an engine. The oil pressure control valve controls oil pressure at the outlet of the pump. The controller controls the oil pressure control valve in order to maintain the oil pressure at the outlet of the pump within a predetermined range in response to information about the oil pressure and driving condition of the engine among vehicle information from outside. column12: One-touch folding type simple bath
column13: Disclosed is a one-touch foldable simple bathtub. The disclosed one-touch foldable simple bathtub comprises: a bathtub sheet unit made of soft waterproof fabric and having a square bathtub shape with an open upper side and providing a space for accommodating bathing water inside; and a water pressure support frame unit which is installed to surround a circumference of the bathtub sheet unit and to support a water pressure of the bathing water in the bathtub sheet unit, and which includes a front surface plate unit in close contact with a front surface sheet of the bathtub sheet unit, a rear surface plate unit in close contact with a rear surface sheet of the bathtub sheet unit, and a pair of side surface plate units connecting the front surface plate unit to both side units of the rear surface plate unit, and having a front end unit and a rear end unit respectively rotatably configured on the front surface plate unit and the rear surface plate unit, and having a plurality of side surface plates which can be folded or unfolded in a zigzag pattern to each other. When the front surface plate unit is moved to be further away from the rear surface plate unit, the plurality of side surface plates are unfolded and the bathtub sheet unit is also unfolded, so the bathtub sheet unit becomes an available mode to be used with bathing water inside. When the front surface plate unit is moved to be closer to the rear surface plate unit, the front surface plate unit, the plurality of side surface plate units, and the rear surface plate unit are folded in a zigzag pattern, and the bathtub sheet unit is folded to be a storage mode. The present invention aims to provide a one-touch foldable simple bathtub which is capable of being very convenient to use and store.

column12: LINEAR GUIDE HAVING END SEAL PROVIDED WITH FLOW PASSAGE OPENING/CLOSING ELASTIC BODY

Accordingly, the lubricant is prevented from flowing backward in the lubricant channels of the end seals.

column12: SPINDLE MOTOR FOR HDD IMPROVED ON PROCESSING CONSTRUCTION OF SLEEVE AND GROOVE OF HUB
column13: A spindle motor for a hard disc drive with an improved machining structure of grooves for a sleeve and a hub is provided to improve reliability while securing a large oil keeping space by the grooves substituted for conventional thrust bearing. A spindle motor for a hard disc drive with an improved machining structure of grooves for a sleeve and a hub includes a stopper(40). The stopper of a predetermined diameter is fitted to a lower part of the sleeve(50) and supports a shaft(30) fitted thereto. The sleeve has a flange(100) projected on the top of the sleeve, which is connected to a hub(10) vertically. A first groove(821) is formed at the upper surface of the sleeve to generate axial dynamic pressure. The hub is has a flange(110) having an inner diameter corresponding to the outer diameter of the sleeve to insert a part of the upper end of the sleeve, and has a groove(120) recessed to correspond to the flange of the sleeve. A second groove(822) is formed on the surface of the center portion of the hub except for the flange and the groove to generate axial dynamic pressure. A part of the center portion of a base(60), which corresponds to the flange of the hub, is recessed in the hub combining direction.

column12: A public information guidance system having a button type interface device
column13: PURPOSE: A public information system having a button type interface is provided to enable a user who wants to obtain information in a public place to use the information by forming an information selection button in the type of button, and by marking an icon on the surface of a relevant button. CONSTITUTION: A computer(10) includes a processor(11), a memory(12) and a communication interface device(13). A display device(40) displays living information selected by the one touch button block(30) and public information automatically designated by the processor(11).

column12: PROBE CARD FOR ELECTRICAL INSPECTION, AND PROBE HEAD OF PROBE CARD
column13: Provided is a probe head for fixing, to a circuit board assembly to be conductively connected to an inspection apparatus, a plurality of probes coming into contact with a device to be inspected. The probe head comprises a first plate, a second plate, nut members, and first bolt members. The first plate and the second plate maintain the plurality of probes. The second plate is placed below the first plate. The nut members are coupled to the second plate. The first bolt members are screw-coupled to the nut members at a first position and a second position through the circuit board assembly. The first bolt members are screw-coupled to the nut members at the first position such that the first plate and the second plate come into close contact with each other. The first bolt members are screw-coupled to the nut members at the second position such that the second plate is distanced from the first plate.

column12: DC CIRCUIT BREAKER

column12: Apparatus for cleaning impurity of test socket

More specifically, the foreign matter cleaning sheet is used in an inspection socket having a plurality of conductive parts arranged in the thickness direction by fusion of a plurality of conductive particles to the silicon rubber at each position corresponding to a terminal of a device under test, and an insulating part for insulating each conductive part while supporting each conductive part. The foreign matter cleaning sheet for removing foreign matter adhering to the surface of the inspection socket comprises: a base sheet having a size corresponding to the surface on which the foreign matter is adhered in the inspection socket; an adhesive sheet disposed on one surface of the base sheet and having adhesive force to remove foreign matter adhering to the surface of the test socket; and a protruding adhesive portion provided in the adhesive sheet at each position corresponding to the conductive part of the inspection socket, protruding from the surface of the adhesive sheet, having a hemispherical shape, and having adhesive force.

column13: PURPOSE: A sanitary cover sheet for a toilet is provided to avoid inconvenience of spreading the cover sheet by making the cover sheet in a roll-type, to eliminate uncomfortable feelings due to adherence of the cover sheet relative to hip, and to improve air permeability and sanitary treatment. column12: Automobile engine misfire detecting method
column13: An automobile engine misfire detecting method adapted to use a wide-range oxygen sensor mounted at a gas exhausting system wherein an abrupt man-made concentration change of oxygen is generated prior to entry of conventional misfire detection judging logic and response characteristic of wide-range oxygen sensor is measured therefrom, on which standard value of misfire detection judgment and standard phase angle range for distinguishing misfired cylinder are corrected to perform the misfire detection and misfired cylinder discrimination, thereby enabling to minimize the influence caused by aged wide-range oxygen sensor and characteristics of each sensor and to effect a more accurate detecting operation.

column12: CODE CONVERTER, DIGITAL / ANALOG CONVERTER, AND DELAY LOCKED LOOP CIRCUIT
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a digital / analog converter the surface area on an integrated circuit of which can be reduced capable of decreasing noise caused in its output.

SOLUTION: The digital / analog converter comprises an escalator code generator and an escalator code / analog converter. The generator expresses a number whose lowest digit expresses 10 with a hybrid code having a coin code part and a cache code part in order to eliminate a multi-bit change in the cache code part following to a change in a count direction and expresses its count in a first direction by a sum of the coin code and the cache code. The generator changes the coin code when the cache code stays the same state until the count capability of the coin code is exceeded and the count changes its direction and the generator can change the cache code in this case. The circulation between numbers adjacent to each other whose lowest digit expressed 10 is absorbed by the coin code part while the cache code is kept in the same state.

column12: COMB WITH SPRAY
Drum type washer and door
column13: A drum type washer and a door thereof are provided to eliminate moisture inside a door glass using natural convection. The door of the drum type washer includes a door glass, an inner door having a holder integral to the inner door to support an outer surface of the door glass, an outer door having a support rib integral to the outer door to support an inner surface of the door glass, the support rib including a hole set formed in the support rib such that an inside of the door glass communicates with an exterior of the drum type washer. With this configuration, the moisture created inside the door glass can be rapidly eliminated.

column12: Magnetic tunnel junction pressure sensors and methods
column13: An integrated circuit device is provided which comprises a substrate, a conductive line configured to experience a pressure, and a magnetic tunnel junction ('MTJ') core formed between the substrate and the current line. The conductive line is configured to move in response to the pressure, and carries a current which generates a magnetic field. The MTJ core has a resistance value which varies based on the magnetic field. The resistance of the MTJ core therefore varies with respect to changes in the pressure. The MTJ core is configured to produce an electrical output signal which varies as a function of the pressure.

Tooth paste bottle
column13: PURPOSE: A toothpaste container is provided to pump toothpaste for an amount of single use, and to reuse the container by refilling. CONSTITUTION: By loosening a locking apparatus, a piston(34) is retreated to generate a negative pressure at a lower end portion of a cylinder(31). Then, toothpaste is a container is sucked through the cylinder. Herein, a film typed packing(38) of a cylinder head portion blocks a through hole(37) at the lower end portion of the cylinder. Therefore, the cylinder is filled with the toothpaste for single use. By pushing a cap(20), the piston progresses to generate positive pressure in the cylinder. Thus, the packing is opened to connect the cylinder with a toothpaste flowing conduit. Therefore, the toothpaste in the cylinder is discharged through a vent hole for being used. Moreover, a sucking tube is connected to the lower portion of the cylinder to empty the toothpaste in the container. And, toothpaste is filled in the container to reuse the container.

column12: A METHOD FOR PREPARING EXTRACT FOR THE PREVENTION AND TREATMENT OF HYPERLIPIDEMIA AND OBESITY FROM THE EXTRACT OF ASTER SPATHULIFOLIUS AERIAL PART AND COMPOSITION CONTAINING THE SAME
column13: A method for preparing an extract of Aster Spathulifolius aerial part, a composition for treating hyperlipidemia and obesity containing the extract prepared by the method, and a functional food containing the extract are provided to improve the effect for treating or preventing hyperlipidemia and obesity by increasing the content of terpene-based compounds such as germacrone. A method for preparing an extract of Aster Spathulifolius aerial part comprises the steps of washing the dried powder of Aster Spathulifolius aerial part with water at a room temperature and dehydrating it; dissolving the obtained powder of Aster Spathulifolius aerial part in ethanol, a mixture solvent of ethanol and water, or a mixture solvent of n-hexane and ethanol to obtain an extract of Aster Spathulifolius aerial part; optionally filtering it, concentrating the filtered one under reduced pressure and drying the concentrated one.

column13: PURPOSE: A constant speed driving control method of a vehicle is provided to use an electronic parking brake for controlling the vehicle in the speed lower than the predetermined speed. CONSTITUTION: A constant speed driving control method of a vehicle comprises the following steps: determining a stop/slowdown state of a constant speed driving apparatus(S10,S20); reducing the speed of the vehicle using a safety control device when the vehicle is in the stop/slowdown state(S30); determining whether the speed of the vehicle is lower than the predetermined speed(S40); and brake controlling and speed reduction controlling the vehicle using an electronic parking brake when the speed of the vehicle is lower than the predetermined speed.(S50).

column12: LOSS PROTECTION DEVICE OF VALUABLES IN BAG
column13: PURPOSE: A device for preventing handbag-picking is provided to prevent anxiety about the theft of an article of value of a user in the crowded place such as in the bus or subway by keeping the article of value of the user safe and to improve the convenience and safety of the user. CONSTITUTION: The device for preventing handbag-picking includes an electrode pad, an impedance sensor(10), an oscillating circuit portion(20), a comparing circuit portion(25), a recognizing and judging portion(30) and an oscillating alarm generating portion(35). The impedance sensor(10) senses impedance on the basis of the change of the line patterns. The oscillating circuit portion(20) generates the frequency appropriate to the impedance sensed from the impedance sensor(10). The comparing circuit portion(25) compares the frequency with the reference frequency. The recognizing and judging portion(30) judges the condition of cutting of the cloth on the basis of the result of the comparing circuit portion(25). The oscillating alarm generating portion(35) alarms the user as the hearing or visual sense.

column12: METHOD OF PRODUCING COATING SOLUTION FOR TOUCH SCREEN
column13: PURPOSE: A manufacturing method of coating solution is provided to provide a coating solution which operates a capacitive touch screen by coating a specific site. In the mixing step, the mixture is continuously stirred at low speed. The sodium hydroxide solution helps conductive materials to be dispersed easily and conductivity is increased by dispersion.

column12: AIR QUALITY SENSOR AND METHOD FOR MANUFACTURING THE SAME

column12: HONEY POWDERED APPARATUS
column13: The present invention relates to a honey powder manufacturing apparatus and, more specifically, to a honey powder manufacturing apparatus which sucks honey stored in a honey storage tank and reduces the amount of moisture contained in the honey through a high-speed rotating tube and a cooling unit to acquire functional honey powder. According to the present invention, the honey powder manufacturing apparatus comprises: a honey storage tank (100) in which a predetermined amount of honey is stored; a suction and transfer unit (200) which is connected to a honey suction pipe (210) extending from the inside of the honey storage tank (100) to suck and transfer the honey stored in the honey storage tank (100); a high-speed rotating tube (300) which is connected to the suction and transfer unit (200) through a connector (330) so that the honey sucked through the suction and transfer unit (200) can be introduced into the inside, and installed to rotate by a rotational motor unit (322); a cooling unit (400) which is installed to be disposed outside the high-speed rotating pipe (300); and a powder storage tank (500) which is installed to receive the longitudinal lower side of the high-speed rotating pipe (300).

column12: METHOD FOR MANUFACTURING OF SEMICONDUCTOR DEVICE
column13: A method for manufacturing a semiconductor device is provided to improve a characteristic of a bit line sense amplifier by reducing the variation of a threshold voltage by changing a thickness of a spacer. A method for manufacturing a semiconductor device includes the steps of: forming a gate in a top part of a semiconductor substrate(11) partitioned by an NMOS(N-type Metal Oxide Semiconductor) region and a PMOS(P-type Metal Oxide Semiconductor) region; forming a photosensitive film pattern for opening the gate of the PMOS region; forming a first LDD(Lightly Doped Drain) region(31) by performing a first ion injecting process by sloping the semiconductor substrate at both sides of the gate of the PMOS region; forming a second LDD region(33) by performing a second ion injecting process by sloping the semiconductor substrate at both sides of the gate of the PMOS region; forming a gate spacer(41) on a side wall by removing the photosensitive film pattern; and forming a junction region(43) by performing a third ion injecting process on the semiconductor substrate at both sides of the gate spacer.

column12: ACTIVE LIGHTNING ARRESTER
column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide an active lightning arrester that reduces the frequency of lightning strikes on a protection object.SOLUTION: An active lightning arrester comprises: a fixed plate 100 joined to grounding means; a rod member 200 engaged to the grounding means at one end in the longitudinal direction and charged with charges of the ground; a plurality of insulators provided in a state of being separated from each other in the longitudinal direction of the rod member; charging plates 400 provided between the neighboring insulators, separated and electrically insulated from the rod member, and charged with charges of the opposite polarity to the charges of the ground; a charging tube 500 arranged between the charging plate and the insulator, electrically connected to the charging plate, and charged with charges of the opposite polarity to the charges of the ground; a needle electrode member 600 provided at the upper end of the rod member and having a needle-shaped part 610; and a discharge induction conductor electrode 700 arranged between the insulator and the charging plate and electrically connected to the charging plate. The active lightning arrester causes discharge to occur between the needle electrode member and the discharge induction conductor electrode so that ion charges are emitted in the atmosphere, thereby forming a discharge path between a thundercloud and the needle electrode member.

column13: PURPOSE: The shoes with function of removing bad smell are provided to supply the mental convenience to a user unconcerned with the space because generation of bacteria and athlete's foot is prevented by removing the bad smell from the foot and the shoes. CONSTITUTION: The shoes with function of removing bad smell include an ozone generating portion(5) and an operation controlling portion(10). The operation controlling portion(10) is composed of a controlling and power portion(15), a distribution power generating portion(20), a timer and clock generating portion(30) and a high voltage generating portion(25). The controlling and power portion(15) generates the power and the controlling signal. The distribution power generating portion(20) receives the power of the controlling and power portion(15) and raises voltage of that as an appointed multiple. The timer and clock generating portion(30) generates the appointed frequency on the basis of the controlling signal of the controlling and power portion(15). The high voltage generating portion(25) transforms the power raised in the distribution power generating portion(20) into the high voltage and supplies it to the ozone generating portion(5) by compounding the high voltage with the frequency.

column12: METHOD FOR MEASURING PROPERTIES OF SUBSTRATE USING ANTENNA
column13: The present invention relates to a method for measuring properties of a substrate using an antenna. According to the present invention, the method for measuring properties of a substrate using an antenna comprises: a step of preparing a material sample of a target substrate; a step of using an antenna fabricated on a substrate for substrate properties measurement to measure distribution parameters of the material sample; a step of using a predetermined antenna simulation model to calculate the distribution parameters of the material sample; a step of comparing/analyzing the two sets of the distribution parameters obtained by measurement and calculation through an optimization algorithm (process) for error minimization; and a step of extracting a material constant of the material sample based on the comparison/analysis. According to the present invention, a comprehensive minimization value is found between an optimization variable and an error function based on an intelligently selected data point to reduce data collection and calculation efforts, thereby solving complex nonlinear problems to increase precision of properties measurement.

column12: Power supply voltage and temperature-independent RC oscillator using controllable Schmitt trigger
column13: A power supply voltage-independent and temperature-independent RC oscillator using a controllable Schmitt trigger comprises a transition voltage generator circuit, a Schmitt trigger circuit, an RC delay circuit, and a quantizer. The transition voltage generator circuit generates a high transition voltage and a low transition voltage. The high and low transition voltages are proportional to a power supply voltage. The Schmitt trigger circuit generates an output voltage having a first level when an input voltage becomes greater than the high transition voltage and having a second level when the input voltage becomes less than the low transition voltage. The RC delay circuit comprises a resistor and a capacitor and generates the input voltage in response to the output voltage. The quantizer quantizes the input voltage to output a square-wave oscillation signal. Accordingly, an oscillation signal having a stable oscillation frequency unaffected by the external conditions can be obtained.

column12: SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR CLASSIFYING DEFECTS IN AND IDENTIFYING PROCESS PROBLEMS FOR AN ELECTRICAL CIRCUIT
column13: A method for performing circuit defect analysis and process problem identification includes applying a test signal to a circuit, obtaining a signal generated in response to the test signal, comparing the response signal to reference information, classifying a defect in the circuit based on a result of the comparing step, and identifying a problem in a manufacturing process which caused the defect based on the classification. The reference information may include one or more signal profiles corresponding to predefined types of defects that can occur during the manufacturing process. Defect classification is preferably performed by determining whether the response signal falls within one or more of the signal profiles. If the response signal falls within two or more signal profiles, then probabilities may be determined for each profile. The defect may then be classified as corresponding to the defect type whose signal profile has the highest probability. A processing system performs defect classification and process problem identification using a similar approach.

column12: Feedback control system and method
column13: A feedback control system and method thereof are provided. The feedback control method includes (a) comparing the level of a reference signal with the levels of first and second signals, (b) if the levels of the first and second signals are lower than the level of the reference signal, generating a first control signal, if the levels of the first and second signals are higher than the level of the reference signal, generating a second control signal, and if the level of the reference signal is between the level of the first signal and the level of the second signal, generating a third control signal, (c) controlling the level of an output signal in response to the first through third control signals, and (d) outputting the controlled output signal and generating the first signal and the second signal.

column12: Control method of broadcasting system using a telephone and control device thereof
column13: The present invention relates to a control method of broadcasting system using a telephone and control device thereof The method comprises the steps of: connecting to a tone detector of the control system by switching a hook switch when a bell signal transmitted by a call of the subscriber is detected more than a set number; after the connection step, sending a previously recorded guidance voice to the subscriber under control of a central processing unit and detecting telephone button signals generated by a manipulation of the subscriber by frequency values of tone frequency; determining which broadcast region the subscriber wants based on the telephone button signals and driving corresponding relays; and connecting electrically the broadcasting system to a broadcast destination of the selected broadcast region to broadcast speech signals to the broadcast destination, the speech signals being sent from the subscriber. A control device comprises: a bell signal detector ( 20 ) connected to a telephone line ( 10 ) for detecting bell signals that ring by a set number; a central processing unit ( 50 ) for, upon receiving signals applied from the bell signal detector ( 20 ), switching a hook switch (K 6 ) so that values of tone frequencies are applied and guidance voice is outputted simultaneously; a tone detector ( 30 ) for detecting the tone frequencies of telephone buttons and applying the detected tone frequencies to the central processing unit ( 50 ) in binary code form; a broadcast equipment controller ( 60 ) for receiving binary values from the tone detector ( 30 ) and supplying a power to a broadcast equipment to maintain broadcasting state; and an output controller ( 70 ) for receiving the binary values from the tone detector ( 30 ), determining locations of broadcast destinations and driving relays.

The auto elevating type 3D printing apparatus includes a printer housing; a printing unit installed at an upper portion of the printer housing to perform 3D printing of a molded body while discharging a molding material; a molding bed elevatably installed in the printer housing to form a molding space of the molded body; a surface treatment unit installed at a lower portion of the printer housing to descend the molding bed with the molded body, and to provide polishing gas for smoothly treating the surface of the molded body in which the 3D printing is performed; a bed elevator to perform a surface treatment process of the molded body in which molding is performed while descending the molding bed to the surface treatment unit, and to withdraw the molded body in which the surface treatment process is performed from the surface treatment unit while elevating the molding bed; and a controller to control operations of the printing unit, the surface treatment unit, and the bed elevator.

column12: SUPERCOOLING SYSTEM
column13: PURPOSE: A super cooling system is provided to prevent freezing nucleus from created in a supercooling state and to steadily maintain the stored goods in a supercooling state. CONSTITUTION: A super cooling system comprises: a cooling unit(100) which comprises a storage, a cooling member which cools the storage, and a main control unit which maintains the temperature of the storage inside at least under the maximum ice crystal generating temperature by controlling the cooling member; and a super cooling unit(200) which includes an independence storage room which includes a receiving space and is installed in the storage, a temperature sensing unit which senses the temperature of the independence storage room, a temperature controller which controls the indoor temperature with being installed in the independence storage room, a display unit which indicates a state about a presently performing control, and a sub controller which stores stored goods in the independence storage room in the supercooling state by controlling the temperature controller based on the sensing temperature from the temperature sensing unit, and indicates the state of the stored goods through the display unit.

column12: Circuit and method for driving a liquid crystal display device using low power
column13: Provided are a circuit and method for driving a liquid crystal display device using low power. The circuit includes a display data latch, a gamma decoder, and a driver cell circuit. The display data latch latches display data from a memory. The gamma decoder receives a plurality of gray scale voltages, and selects and outputs one of the plurality of gray scale voltages in response to the display data. The driver cell circuit receives an output voltage of the gamma decoder and generates an output voltage applied to the liquid crystal display device. The driver cell circuit controls a slew rate in response to comparison result of current data and previous data of the display data. The driver cell circuit includes a previous data latch, a bias control voltage generator, and a driver amplifier. The previous data latch receives a portion or the whole of the display data and outputs the portion or the whole of the display data as the previous data. The bias control voltage generator compares the current data and the previous data of the display data and generates a control signal. The driver amplifier receives the output voltage of the gamma decoder, generates the output voltage applied to the liquid crystal display device, and controls the slew rate in response to the control signal.

CONSTITUTION: A general form of a domain(1a) is displayed in various modes such as http://domain.co.kr/¯user, http://domain.co.kr/user/, http://user.domain.co.kr. A general form of an e-mail(1b) is represented as a single shape of mail to:user@domain.co.kr. An e-mail form of a general domain(1c) is represented as http://user@domain.co.kr. In case that http:// is omitted and inputted to an address window in connecting to an Internet homepage through a web browser, the web browser automatically recognizes the http://. Therefore, the connection to the web site is performed with the e-mail form of the domain name, user@domain.co.kr.

And a separation gap is formed between the plurality of crushing parts and the rotating roller part, so that the waste mask passing through the feeding opening enters for crushing treatment.

column12: Skin-condition improving composition comprising vaccinium uliginosum extract and method for preparation thereof
column13: The present invention relates to a composition for skin whitening and unwrinkling, comprising an extract of Vaccinium uliginosum as an active ingredient, and a preparation method thereof. The Vaccinium uliginosum extract has the effects of inhibiting and scavenging reactive oxygen species produced in skin tissue as a result of ultraviolet irradiation to the skin, effectively inhibiting tyrosinase activity to inhibit the production of melanin in melanin cells, inhibiting the secretion of cytokines in keratinocytes, promoting the production of procollagen, and inhibiting the decomposition of collagen. Thus, the extract will be useful for the prevention of skin photo aging caused by ultraviolet radiation, the enhancement of skin whitening and the improvement of wrinkles. In addition, the Vaccinium uliginosum extract is suitable to use as a component for improving skin wrinkles in cosmetics, foods and drugs, because the Vaccinium uliginosum extract can achieve the effect of improving skin conditions, even when it is applied to the skin or used internally.

column12: Write head control device and method
column13: A write head 10 for an ink jet printer is disclosed. The head includes one or more chambers 12 having a lower portion containing a quantity of liquid metal 20 and an upper ink reservoir 15, an ink channel 14 connecting the ink reservoir to an ink cartridge and a nozzle 13 for ejecting ink droplets from the ink reservoir. A magnetic field is established across the liquid metal by opposite magnetic bodies 18, 19 and opposing electrodes 16, 17 are provided to pass an electric current through the liquid metal 20 perpendicular to the magnetic field to cause the liquid metal 20 to move and expel an ink droplet from the ink reservoir through the nozzle 13. A temperature sensor 21 senses the temperature at a predetermined position on the write head 10 and a heating element 22 heats the liquid metal 20 when the temperature sensed drops below a preset value. column12: Data receiver and data receiving method using signal integration
column13: A data receiver and data receiving method using signal integration and capable of reducing high-frequency noises generated upon high-speed data detection. The data receiver includes an integration amplification circuit receiving at least two differential reference signals and N (where N is a natural number greater than zero) data signals and integrating and amplifying differences between the at least two differential reference signals and one or more of the N data signals and outputting at least first differential signals and at least second differential signals and a detection amplification circuit for receiving the at least first differential signals and the at least second differential signals and detecting a difference between the at least first differential signals and the at least second differential signals to detect a value of one or more of the N data signals The data receiver and data receiving method, using signal integration, can reduce high-frequency noises generated when data is detected at a high speed. The data receiver and data receiving method, where signals inputted through two reference signal lines and one data line are integrated and amplified to detect data, provide accurate data detection at a high speed using differential signaling, irrespective of changes in a process, voltage level, or temperature.

The device (40, 61-13, 61-15, 61-18, 61-19) comprises a substrate (48, 72) with upper (37) and lower (63, 73) surfaces. A semiconductor (38, 72) is located proximate the upper surface (37) with a device region (26) therein. One or more cavities (67, 77) underlying the device region (26) are etched in the substrate (48, 72) from the lower surface (63, 73). A higher thermal conductivity material (68) versus the substrate (48, 72) fills the one or more cavities (67) and has an exposed surface (69, 69', 79, 79 ') underlying the device region (26) at or beyond the lower surface (63, 73). This provides the under-filled heat extractor(s) (46, 46', 78, 78'). A composite substrate (48) is preferred, having a first semiconductor (38) extending to the upper surface (37) containing the device region (26), a second semiconductor (42) extending to the lower surface (63) and an insulating layer (36) therebetween, wherein the one or more cavities (67) extend from the lower surface (63) to the insulating layer (36) and the etch depth (671) is self limiting.

column12: ELECTRODE STRUCTURE FOR MEASURING BIO-SIGNAL AND APPARATUS FOR MEASURING ELECTROCARDIOGRAM USING THE SAME
column13: The electrode structure for measuring a bio-signal and an apparatus for measuring an electrocardiogram using the same are disclosed. The electrode structure for measuring a bio-signal, comprises an electrode pad to measure bio-signals based on capacitive coupling between the electrode pad and human skin; an absorption layer formed at one side of the electrode pad; and a preamplifier which is electrically connected with the electrode pad and filters noise from the bio-signals from the electrode pad and amplifies and outputs the signals. Thus, the initial noise stabilization time can be reduced, and stable electrocardiogram signals can be obtained quickly without noises.

column12: System and method for reward marketing
column13: Disclosed are a reward marketing system and a method thereof. The reward marketing method of the present invention comprises the steps of: transmitting a first code including first identification information on a first purchaser in response to a request of a first purchaser terminal, and transmitting the same to the first purchaser terminal; receiving the first identification information and first purchase information on the first purchaser from a seller terminal obtained with first code information by scanning the first code, and registering the same; transmitting a recommendation request message including the first identification information and the first purchase information to the first purchaser terminal to allow a recommendation for purchase of the first purchaser to a second purchaser; generating a second code including the first identification information, the first purchase information, and identification information on the second purchaser in response to a request of the second purchaser terminal, and transmitting the same to the second purchaser terminal; receiving second code information and second purchase information on the second purchaser from the seller terminal obtained with the second code information by scanning the second code; and providing the first purchaser with a reward accumulation service for a recommendation activity of the first purchaser in accordance with a purchase of the second purchaser.

column12: POGO PIN, THE FABRICATION METHOD THEREOF AND TEST SOCKET USING THE SAME
column13: A pogo pin, a method for fabricating the same, and a test socket using the same are provided to reduce contact defects and to improve stiffness and electric conductance of a body of the pogo pin by incorporating the body with a conductive material. A pogo pin(100) is comprised of a hollow body(110) and a conductive material(120). A part of an outer surface of the hollow body is helically cut. The conductive material is filled in the hollow body. The hollow body has a cylindrical shape. A center portion of the hollow body is protruded toward a lateral direction. The hollow body is made of a metal material. The conductive material is made of an elastic rubber material. A metal powder is added to the conductive material. The conductive material is filled in the cut part of the outer surface of the hollow body. The conductive material is incorporated with the outer surface of the hollow body to configure a protrusion.

column12: Bipolar conventional lightning rod
column13: PURPOSE: A bipolar lightning rod is provided to generate easily thunderstroke under low thundercloud voltage by pre-discharging the thundercloud voltage according to an approaching state of thundercloud. CONSTITUTION: A dipolar lightning rod includes a thunderstroke receiving member(110) and an electric dipolar discharge unit(130). One end of the thunderstroke receiving member(110) is inserted into a fixing member. The electric dipolar discharge unit(130) includes a separation member(122), a ring member(126), and an insulator(128). The thunderstroke receiving member penetrates a center part of separation member(122). The ring member(126) is loaded on an upper surface of the separation member. Opposite charges to the separation member are electrified on an outer circumference of the ring member. The ring member is fixed on the insulator(128).

column12: TW I320404 B
HIGH PERFORMANCE DIPOLE LIGHTNING ROD
column13: PURPOSE: A dipole lightning rod is provided to reduce induced electricity due to a lightning current by installing a lightning prevention resistor between a dipole protrusion and the ground. CONSTITUTION: A pedestal(1) is installed in a building. The lower side of a resistor unit is fixed to the pedestal with a fixing part. The resistor unit includes a frame(3) and a coil(2). The coil is wound around the frame. One side of the coil is connected to a down-conductor through the pedestal. The other side of the coil is connected to the dipole protrusion through a connection bar(7). A lightning prevention cover(5) is fixed to the upper side of the resistor unit. The dipole protrusion is connected to the lightning prevention cover and the resistor unit.
