column12: ORGANIC LIGHT EMITTING DISPLAY DEVICE AND THE MANUFACTURING METHOD THEREOF
column13: An organic light emitting display device and a method for manufacturing the same are disclosed. The organic light emitting display device comprises: a sub-pixel including a pixel electrode, a counter electrode, and a light emitting layer interposed in-between; a planarization film for covering the counter electrode; and an auxiliary electrode formed in the planarization film to be connected to the counter electrode. With this structure, a problem of voltage drop can be solved effectively by connecting the auxiliary electrode and the counter electrode through the planarization film and, therefore, product reliability can be improved.

column12: PROBE MEMBER FOR POGO PIN, MANUFACTURING METHOD THEREFOR AND POGO PIN COMPRISING SAME
column13: The present invention relates to a probe member for a pogo pin, a manufacturing method therefor and a pogo pin comprising same. One embodiment of the present invention provides a probe member used ina test socket, the probe member comprising: at least one contact part having one end formed so as to be sharp and making contact with an object being inspected; a polygonal or cylindrical first body part having the other end of the contact part coupling to one end thereof; and a polygonal or cylindrical second body part having the other end of the first body part coupling to one end thereof, wherein the first body part and the second body part are stacked in the height direction with reference to the other end of the contact part, and at least one portion thereof are inserted in a pipe havingan inner space formed therein.

column12: Probe device for inspection
column13: A probe device for inspection, at least a portion of which is inserted into a tube having an internal space, for testing a socket, includes: a second body portion having a polygonal or circular column shape; a first main body part which is stacked on the upper part of the second main body part, is integrally formed with the second main body part, and has a polygonal or circular column shape; an intermediate portion stacked on the upper portion of the first body portion and integrally formed with the first body portion, the intermediate portion having a first protrusion having a first apex portion formed on the upper side thereof; and a contact portion integrally formed with the intermediate portion on an upper surface of the intermediate portion and having a second protrusion arranged along an outer shape of the first protrusion at a position corresponding to the first protrusion, the second protrusion having an increased height in a direction perpendicular to the upper surface of the intermediate portion and formed with a second apex portion, the second body portion, the first body portion, the intermediate portion, and the contact portion are formed by being stacked upward in this order, the intermediate portion and the contact portion are formed of different materials from each other, and the first protrusion is arranged inside the second protrusion.

column12: ELECTRICAL TEST SOCKET
column13: The present invention relates to an electrical test socket, and more specifically, to the electrical test socket for connecting a port of a tested device to a pad of a test device electrically. The electrical test socket of the present invention includes: a cover member which has an insertion hole into which the tested device is inserted in a center, and can move up and down; a base member which is arranged at a lower side of the cover member, has an accommodation hole at a position corresponding to the insertion hole and is installed at a side of the test device; and a latch unit which is connected to the base member and the cover member respectively, and opens and closes the accommodation hole by performing rotation as to the base member according to ascending and descending of the cover member. The cover member includes: a first cover member which is delivered with pressurizing force by coming into contact with an external pressurizing unit; a second cover member which is arranged at a lower side of the first cover member and is connected to the latch unit; and a stroke increasing unit which is in contact with the first cover member and the second cover member respectively, and makes descending stroke of the second cover member larger than descending stroke of the first cover member by increasing a relative distance between the first cover member and the second cover member when the first cover member descends.

column12: ELECTRICAL CONNECTION DEVICE HAVING POROUS INSULATING SHEET WITH THROUGH HOLE AND TEST SOCKET
column13: The present invention relates to an electrical connection device electrically connecting between a device to be tested and a test apparatus, comprising: a first supporting sheet configured for a porous insulating sheet of which a plurality of penetrating holds is formed on each location corresponded to a connection terminal of the device to be tested; a first elastic sheet comprising a conducting unit which is formed as an elastic material on a lower part of the first supporting sheet, and formed as a conducting particle is condensed on a location corresponded to the penetrating hole and an insulator which formed adjacent on the conducting unit and insulates and supports the conducting unit; a second supporting sheet comprising a porous insulating sheet in which a plurality of penetrating hole is formed on each location corresponded to a connection terminal of the device to be tested; and a second elastic sheet composing a conducting unit which is formed as the elastic material on a lower part of the second supporting sheet, and formed as a conducting particle is condensed on a location corresponded to the penetrating hole and the insulator which is formed adjacent on the conducting unit and insulates and supports the conducting unit. The second elastic sheet is positioned to be attached on the first elastic sheet, such that the penetrating hole of the first supporting sheet and the penetrating hole of the second supporting sheet is positioned in a row.

column12: FUSE OF SEMICONDUCTOR DEVICE AND METHOD FOR FORMING USING THE SAME
column13: PURPOSE: A fuse of semiconductor device and a method for forming using the same are provided to improve the reliability of a semiconductor device by preventing a fuse residue which is generated in fuse blowing from moving. CONSTITUTION: In a fuse of semiconductor device and a method for forming using the same, a trench nitride film(104) is formed on a semiconductor substrate(100). A trench oxide film(106) is formed on the trench nitride film. A fuse metal(108) is buried within the trench oxide film and the trench nitride film. A damascene nitride film(110) is formed on the top of the fuse metal. An LTS(Low Temperature Solder)(112) covers the damascene nitride sidewall, the trench oxide film sidewall, and the trench nitride side wall.

column12: HIGH PRESSURE HOMOGENIZER
INSULATING ELECTRIFICATION PLATE FERRITE APPLICATOR FOR A DIPOLE LIGHTNING ROD
column13: Disclosed herein is an insulating electrification plate ferrite applicator for a dipole lightning rod. The ferrite applicator may include a compression air generation unit configured to generate and charge compressed air, a storage tank connected to the compression air generation unit and configured to stored a ferrite coating material, an applicator body equipped with a turntable configured to rotatably support an electrification plate and an operation control unit, a spray nozzle unit installed on top of the applicator body and configured to spray and supply the ferrite coating material, and a location tracking unit configured to guide the spray nozzle unit so that the spray nozzle unit performs a straight-line reciprocating motion horizontally and vertically. Accordingly, there are advantages in that a ferrite coating task for lowering a corona pre-discharge current and a corona preliminary discharge voltage can be automated and uniformly performed and the reliability and productivity of a task can be significantly improved.

column12: COMMON LEVEL SHIFTER, PRECHARGE CIRCUIT, SCAN LINE DRIVER HAVING THE SAME, LEVEL SHIFTING METHOD AND SCAN LINE DRIVING METHOD
INSERT BASE AND TEST SOCKET FOR USE IN TESTING SEMICONDUCTOR DEVICE
column13: Provided is a test socket used for the semiconductor device inspection. The test socket has a base mounted to an inspection apparatus and an insert inserted into the base. The insert receives the semiconductor device inspected by the inspection apparatus. The insert has an insert body and a floating device. The insert body penetrates in the vertical direction and has a device receiving portion for receiving the semiconductor device. The floating device is coupled to the insert body and floats the insert body upwards from the inspection apparatus. When the insert body is moved downwards toward the inspection apparatus by an external force, the floating device resists the insert body. When the external force is removed from the insert body, the floating device moves the insert body upwards.

LIQUID DISPLAY DEVICE
TEMPERATURE CONTROL METHOD
column13: Provided is a temperature control method, capable of improving controllability of temperature distribution in a surface of a substrate provided on a holding table. According to one embodiment of the present invention, the temperature control method, which is the temperature control method of an object to be processed, provided on the holding table, comprises: a process of supplying electric heating gas between the object to be processed and the holding table from one gas hole among a plurality of gas holes provided on the holding table and exhausting the electric heating gas from a gas hole, which is different from the gas hole; a process of detecting pressure of the gas hole for supplying the electric heating gas and the gas hole for exhausting the electric heating gas; and a process of controlling the pressure.

column12: Connection connector
column13: The present invention relates to a connection connector and, more specifically, to a connection connector which is disposed between a device to be tested and a testing apparatus and is for electrically connecting a terminal of the device to be tested and a pad of the testing apparatus. The connection connector comprises: an anisotropic conductive sheet comprising a plurality of conductive parts, in which arranged are a plurality of conductive particles extending in the thickness direction inside an elastic insulating material and on places corresponding to the terminals of the device to be tested, and insulating support parts which are provided between each conductive part, support each conductive part and insulate the conductive parts from one another; and a sheet-type connector having a porous sheet, which is disposed between the upper side and lower side of the anisotropic conductive sheet, is inserted into the anisotropic conductive sheet, and has a plurality of gaps, and a plurality of electrodes which are disposed on places corresponding to the conductive parts and are integrally coupled to the porous sheet, wherein each electrode is formed from a metal material and is electrically connected to each conductive part.

column12: ENGINE THAT IS EQUIPPED WITH VARIABLE VALVE DEVICE
column13: .Engine equipped with a variable valve device according to an embodiment example of the present invention comprises; the first lever driving a valve by a cam on one side with the other side supported by a support part; and the second lever connected with the first lever through a hinge on one side with the other side being selectively fastened to the first lever by a latching part including a lock pin; and an electromagnet wherein the lock pin fastens the second lever to the first lever by pulling the lock pin; and a sensing part arranged adjacent to the lock pin to sense move positions of the lock pin; and a control part to determine an operation condition of the lock pin through the sensing part while moving the lock pin by selectively magnetizing the electromagnet. Therefore, the present invention can improve a fuel efficiency by operating the lock pin without using hydraulic pressures, improve a control speed of the lock pin and effectively sense moves of the lock pin. column12: Wechselstrom-Leistungssteuervorrichtung
column13: An alternating current power control device comprising a phase comparison controller for comparing a phase of an input voltage with that of a first reference voltage, a single-winding transformer for varying the input voltage, a mutual induction reactor for lowering the input voltage by a desired level in response to an output voltage from the single-winding transformer, an output voltage comparator for comparing an output voltage with a second reference voltage, an output current comparator for comparing an output current with a reference current, an OR logic controller for performing an OR operation with respect to output signals from the phase comparison controller and output current comparator, and a switch array for selectively transferring the output voltage from the single-winding transformer to the mutual induction reactor in response to output signals from the output voltage comparator and OR logic controller. According to the present invention, the mutual induction reactor is implemented on the basis of the principle of a linear transformer and has a small capacity corresponding to about 1/10 of a load power. Therefore, a proper power necessary to the saving of energy can be supplied by using the mutual induction reactor. <IMAGE>

column12: System and method of monitoring, predicting and optimizing production yields in a liquid crystal display (LCD) manufacturing process
column13: Disclosed is a system and a method of monitoring LCD production yields, predicting the effects of different testing methodologies on LCD production yields, and optimizing production yields is provided that compares the effect of different testing methodologies on the yields at various stages in the LCD testing and assembly process. The present invention can also be used to predict the effect of different testing methodologies on user-defined parameters, such as profit.

column12: FLUID TREATED POLYTETRAFLUOROETHYLENE PRODUCTS AND THEIR MANUFACTURE
METHOD FOR FABRICATING DRAM CELL WITH PLANAR CAPACITOR STRUCTURE OF LOW COUPLING NOISE TO INCREASE SENSING MARGIN OF SENSE AMPLIFIER
column13: PURPOSE: A method for fabricating a DRAM(dynamic random access memory) cell with a planar capacitor structure of low coupling noise is provided to increase a sensing margin of a sense amplifier by intercepting bitline coupling noise without an additional process. CONSTITUTION: A structure of a gate(112) and a planar capacitor(114) is formed on a silicon substrate(100). An interlayer dielectric(118) is formed on the silicon substrate including the structure of the gate and the planar capacitor. A metal contact is formed between the gates. A bitline is formed on the metal contact. An insulation layer(126) between interconnections is formed on the silicon substrate having the bitline. After a via hole is formed between the bitlines on the insulation layer between the interconnections, the via hole is filled with a metal layer to form a via contact(130). A metal interconnection(132) is formed on the via contact. The metal interconnection is connected to the ground.

column12: CABLE-STAYED BRIDGE LIGHTNING PROTECTION APPARATUS FOR DISTRIBUTING LIGHTNING CURRENT
column13: "A cable-stayed bridge lightning protection apparatus for distributing a lightning current", according to the present invention, comprises: a lightning rod (40) provided at the cable-stayed bridge; agrounding body (80) for facilitating an electrical connection of the lightning rod and the ground; a down-conductor (50) for connecting the lightning rod and the grounding body; supporting cables (30)for connecting a tower and a deck of the cable-stayed bridge; a protective lightning inducing wire (60) of the supporting cable, supported at the uppermost supporting cable among the plurality of supporting cables by one or more of a plurality of insulating supporters (90), and connected to the down-conductor (50) at the lower end of the lightning rod (40); and current distribution conductors (70) provided in parallel to the supporting cables, and connected to the down-conductor (50) and the grounding body (80) at both end portions of the supporting cable. The present invention relates to thecable-stayed bridge lightning protection apparatus for distributing the lightning current, the apparatus allowing the lightning current (a current flowing in because of the lightning) to be distributed and flow to the down-conductor, and the current distribution conductors, provided in parallel to each supporting cable, when lightning (hereinafter, referred to as downward lightning), which is downwardly discharged from the thundercloud to the ground or lightning (hereinafter, referred to as upward lightning) upwardly discharged from the ground to the thundercloud, according to the polarity ofa thundercloud, flows in through the lightning rod or the supporting cables provided at the cable-stayed bridge, such that the current, flowing to the supporting cables, particularly, to an assemblyof steel wires forming the supporting cable, is minimized, thereby preventing a decrease, in the mechanical strength of the supporting cables, caused by a fire or heat at the supporting cables becauseof the heat generated from the supporting cables, that is, Joule's heat caused by the lightning current and electrical resistance of the steel wire assembly, such that the stability of the cable-stayed bridge can be ensured. Furthermore, the cable-stayed bridge lightning protection apparatus for distributing the lightning current has a dipolar lightning rod for minimizing a deviation of dischargestart voltages according to the polarity of the thundercloud so as to minimize a deviation in the magnitudes of the currents flowing in the down-conductor and the current distribution conductor, thereby enabling the capacity of the down-conductor and the current distribution conductor to be easily selected when a lightning protection system of the cable-stayed bridge is designed. In addition, thelightning protection apparatus exhibits an effect of providing the lightning rods to each supporting cable (30) and respectively providing the down-conductors thereto in order to prevent the lightning flowing to the supporting cables (30), thereby having excellent complexity, constructability, and economic efficiency, which are provided to lightning protection devices for each supporting cable ofthe cable-stayed bridge by using one lightning rod.

column12: CONTACT PIN FOR TEST SOCKET AND TEST SOCKET COMPRISING THE SAME
column13: The present invention relates to a test socket disposed between a subject device and test equipment and a contact pin which is a component of the test socket. The test socket comprises: a housing formed of an insulating material; and a contact pin which is supported by the housing to be movable in a vertical direction and is configured to allow electricity to flow in the vertical direction.

column12: Clothes dryer and method of displaying drying time on the same
column13: A clothes dryer and a method of displaying a drying time on the clothes dryer by determining a predicted drying time considering an ambient temperature of the clothes dryer and displaying (82) the predicted drying time corresponding to the ambient temperature. Also, a clothes dryer which displays the predicted drying time by determining (84,86) a drying state of an object to be dried, and adjusting (88) the predicted drying time based upon the drying state of object to be dried.

column12: Device for cold and warm fomentations
column13: A device for cold and warm fomentations is disclosed. The device has a fomentation head and a heat exchange element control unit. The fomentation head includes a semiconductor heat exchange element. A coolant tank is mounted on the top surface of the heat exchange element. A heat conducting plate is fixed to the bottom surface of the heat exchange element. A far infrared radiation ceramic or metal-coated layer is positioned on the bottom surface of the heat conducting plate. The heat exchange element control unit includes a direct current electric source. A power polarity converting switch circuit is connected to the heat exchange element in parallel with the electric source. A program circuit is connected to the power polarity converting switch circuit at its output terminal. A rush current restricting element is connected to the heat exchange element. A power on-off relay switch is connected to the program circuit at its input terminal and to the power polarity converting switch circuit and the rush current restricting element. A first control circuit and a second control circuit are connected to the heat exchange element at their input terminals and to the power on-off relay switch at their output terminals.

column12: Active lightning arrester
column13: The present invention relates to an arrester, comprising: a rod member coupled to a ground means at one end in the longitudinal direction and charged with charges of the ground; a plurality of insulators provided to be spaced from each other in the longitudinal direction of the rod member; an charging plates provided between the neighboring insulators separately from the rod member so as to be electrically insulated and charged with a polarity opposite to that of the charges of the ground; a charging tube provided between the charging plates and the insulators, electrically connected to the charging plates, and charged with charges having a polarity opposite to that of the charges of the ground; a needle electrode member provided to the upper end of the rod member and having a needle-shaped part; and a discharge induction conductor electrode electrically connected to the charging plates between the insulators and the charging plates so as to induce discharge between the needle electrode member and the discharge induction conductor electrode and emit ion charges through the discharge, thereby forming a discharge path between a thundercloud and the needle electrode.

column12: Method of detecting defects in TFT-arrays and a TFT-array testing system incorporating the same
column13: A system and method for detecting defects in TFT-array panels is provided that improves defect detection accuracy by adjusting the thresholding parameters used to classify defective pixels in accordance with the standard deviation of the measured pixel voltages. The present invention is particularly suited for the testing of TFT-array panels that contain more pixels than can be measured by the sensor of the TFT-array tester in a single measurement. The system and method of the present invention calculates the standard deviation of the measured pixel voltages at each measurement point, and adjusts the thresholding parameters based on the calculated standard deviation. Accordingly, the system and method of the present invention helps to compensate for differences in the measured pixel voltages between measurement points due to environmental factors or other causes.

column12: Test socket
column13: The present invention relates to a test socket, and more specifically to a test socket which is placed between a device to be tested and a testing device, and electrically connects a terminal of the device to be tested to a pad of the testing device. As a conducting unit placed on each location corresponding to a terminal of the device to be tested and shown a conductivity in a thickness direction, the conducting unit comprises: a conducting portion where multiple conductive particles within an elastic insulating material are arranged and placed in a thickness direction; and an insulating support which supports each of the conducting portions and insulates. The conductive particles comprise at least one first conductivity particle. The first conductivity particle is formed as a plate containing an upper surface, a lower surface, and a circumferential surface connecting edges of the upper surface to the lower surface. The first conductivity particle has a through-hole penetrating centers of the upper and the lower surfaces, and a first slit penetrating an inner circumferential surface of the through-hole and the circumferential surface. A concave groove which curves inwardly at a predetermined depth is formed on the upper surface. The elastic insulating material is filled in the through-hole, the first slit and the concave groove, and integrally connects the inside to the outside of the first conductivity particle.

column12: Semiconductor integrated circuit device and on-die termination circuit
column13: The present invention discloses a semiconductor integrated circuit device and an on-die termination circuit. The circuit includes a level shifter for boosting an on-die termination control signal to a high voltage level; and a first NMOS transistor connected between a power voltage and a pad and terminating the pad to a first termination voltage level in response to the high voltage level. The on-die termination circuit has a reduced input capacitance.

column12: Control device for the remote diagnosis of the car
column13: PURPOSE: Provided is a remote diagnosis controller in a car which bases a controller area network(CAN) communication protocol to communicate a management server to devices in the car so that it helps to manage the car conveniently. CONSTITUTION: The remote diagnosis controller in the car comprises the parts of: a CANBUS interface part(20) which uses CANBUS to read the state of ECU and TCU and download data of ECU and TCU from main CPU; a peripheral drive part(30) which drives a blow motor to adjust the drive of a window, a door lock and a lamp and internal temperature of the car and an engine throttle; a signal pre-treatment part(40) which reads the state of the peripheral drive part to formalize the state as a signal proper to the main CPU; a drive circuit part(50) which adjusts the state of the blow motor; the main CPU(10) which firstly processes data obtained from CANBUS and the drive part by internal algorithm to generate; and a PCMCIA interface part(70) which converts output data in the main CPU to be proper to PCMCIA protocol and uses a wireless LAN card(60).

column12: LED Lighting Modules Using Carbon Thermal Conductive Material
column13: The present invention relates to an LED lighting module using a carbon thermal conductive material. Especially, the present invention relates to an LED lighting module using a carbon thermal conductive material which is comparatively light compared to aluminum, has thermal properties similar to aluminum, and does not need a separate post process by inserting a metal plate and injection-molding a heat sink. The LED lighting module includes a base plate, a heat sink and an LED module.

column12: Semiconductor device and method for manufacturing the same
column13: A semiconductor device is fabricated by forming a semiconductor substrate as a convex shape to increase a effective channel of a transistor and by stacking a first silicon germanium layer and a first silicon layer on the semiconductor substrate to form a first layer and stacking a second silicon germanium layer and a second silicon layer on the first layer to form a second layer such that the current reduced due to the increased effective channel is ensured, thereby being capable of high speed performance.

column12: LIGHTNING ARRESTER
column13: Provided is a lightning arrester capable of preventing damage caused by a lightning by discharging charges charged by approach of a thundercloud. The lightning arrester includes: a conductive rod installed at an upper part of an object to be protected from a lightning and connected to a ground part; a charge pipe having a cylindrical shape, formed of an insulating body to be insulated from the rod, and electrically charged with charges having a polarity opposite to ground charges; and a plurality of charge pins disposed on the charge pipe such that space charges in the air are charged to the pins by a thundercloud.

column12: Washing machine and method of controlling drying process thereof
column13: A washing machine and method of controlling a drying process thereof is provided. The washing machine includes a water temperature detecting unit and a controller. The water temperature detecting unit is disposed in a condensing duct to detect temperatures of condensed water. The controller determines whether an end of a drying process is reached based upon the water temperatures detected by the water temperature detecting unit, and terminates the drying process depending on a result of the determination. Accordingly, the drying process may be terminated without delay, irrespective of various factors, such as a weight of the laundry, moisture contained in the laundry, and the temperature of cold water supplied to an inside of the condensing duct, so that a drying performance is improved, excessive drying and damage to the laundry are prevented and energy is saved.

column12: Semiconductor device having control bitline to prevent floating body effect
column13: A vertical semiconductor device is provided. The semiconductor device includes a cell array including a control bit line connected to cells and electrically isolated from a bit line, and a floating body control circuit for applying a floating control voltage to the control bit line in a predetermined period.

column12: Method for manufacturing conductive particles
column13: The invention relates to a method for manufacturing conductive particles. The method for manufacturing the conductive particles distributed in a plurality in an elastic insulating material to form a conductive portion for electrical connection includes: (a) a step of preparing a substrate; (b) a step of providing, on the substrate, grooves for forming conductive particles having a shape corresponding to the desired conductive particles; (c) a step of filling a non-metal powder inside the grooves for forming the conductive particles; (d) a step of producing solidified conductive particles by heating the non-metal powder, wherein the non-metal powder is thermally decomposed before the heat treatment is completed so as to form pores inside and outside the solidified particles; (e) separating the solidified particles from the substrate; and (f) a step of forming a metal plating layer on the surfaces of the particles.

column12: BIPOLAR LIGHTNING ROD APPARATUS
column13: A bipolar lightning rod apparatus includes a fixation plate, a rod member configured to have one end connected to the fixation plate in a length direction thereof and charged with the electric charges of a ground, at least two insulators installed in the length direction, an electrification plate installed between adjacent insulators, electrically insulated from the rod member, and charged with electric charges having an opposite polarity to the electric charges of the ground, an electrification tube installed between the electrification plate and the insulators, electrically connected to the electrification plate, and charged with electric charges having an opposite polarity to the electric charges of the ground, and a rod cap connected to the top of the rod member and configured to induce the falling of a thunderbolt. The rod cap has an outside diameter greater than that of the insulators.

column12: LID DEVICE FOR TESTING ELECTRONIC DEVICE
column13: Provided is a lid apparatus for pressing a device under test toward a test socket for inspecting the device under test. The lid apparatus comprises: a pusher configured to press the device under test downward toward the test socket; and a stroke measuring unit in conjunction with the downward movement of the pusher to measure a stroke of the test socket in accordance with the downward movement of the pusher. Further, the lid apparatus has a display unit to display the stroke measured by the stroke measuring unit as a numerical value.

column12: SAWTOOTH WAVE GENERATING CIRCUIT AND SWITCH MODE POWER SUPPLY DEVICE HAVING THE SAME
column13: A sawtooth wave generating circuit that outputs a sawtooth wave signal after calibration and a switch mode power supply device including the sawtooth wave generating circuit is disclosed. The sawtooth wave generating circuit includes a capacitor, a calibration circuit, a charging circuit, discharging circuit and a control unit. The calibration circuit feedbacks a sawtooth wave signal, generates a plurality of voltage signals based on the sawtooth wave signal, and selects one of the voltage signals to generate a calibration output signal. Therefore, the sawtooth wave generating circuit generates a stable sawtooth wave signal regardless of operating conditions.

column13: A paging performance device for a receiving service in a wireless communication system and a method are provided to perform a paging process without using a network address for a terminal which returns the network address when switching to an idle mode, thereby offering a receiving service to the terminal which is not allocated with the network address. When a terminal(301) transfers to an idle mode, paging information of the terminal(301) which returns a network address is stored(321-333). If call reception occurs in the terminal(301), the paging information of the terminal(301) is confirmed by using an MAC(Medium Access Control) address of the terminal(301) to transmit a control signal so that the terminal(301) performs a paging process(335). If the terminal(301) enters a network, a call reception signal is transmitted to the terminal(301)(337).

CONSTITUTION: A system for controlling the hydraulic pressure and flow of an engine comprises a first solenoid valve(Vs1), an electronic control unit(110), and a second solenoid valve(Vs2). column12: HYDRAULIC EQUIPMENT FOR EXCAVATOR HAVING TONGS INSTALLING ARM
column13: According to the present invention, hydraulic equipment for an excavator comprising an arm installation tongs includes: a hydraulic cylinder which supplies a working fluid to a connection cylinder performing detachment of a quick coupler or a tongs cylinder driving the arm installation tongs; an oil tank which contains the working fluid discharged from the tongs cylinder or the connection cylinder; a tongs line which is installed between the tongs cylinder and a hydraulic pump or the oil tank, and supplies or discharges the working fluid; a main controller which is installed in the tongs line, and controls the tongs cylinder by determining supply direction of the working fluid; a connection line which is installed between the connection cylinder and the hydraulic pump or the oil tank, and supplies or discharges the working fluid; a solenoid valve which is installed in the connection line, and controls the connection cylinder by determining supply direction of the working fluid; and a sagging prevention part which is installed in the tongs line, and prevents the working fluid from sagging toward the bottom of an arm of the arm installation tongs by controlling the working fluid discharged from the tongs cylinder.

column12: Lightning arrester
column13: Disclosed is a lightning arrester. The lightning arrester safely discharges earth charge of a main electrode section and an auxiliary electrode section regardless of a variation of charge contained in air, so charge charged in a thundercloud is safely discharged into the earth even if the thundercloud is located far-remote from the earth. The lightning arrester has a fixing base fixedly installed on an object to be protected by grounding a lightning circuit connected to a ground electrode grounded to an earth, a fixing bar vertically installed at one side of an upper surface of the fixing base and made of conductive material, a main electrode section making contact with an upper portion of the fixing bar and made of conductive material, an upper polymer insulator including an elongated column member formed at a center thereof with a hollow section for receiving the fixing bar therein, and upper and lower disc-shaped plates integrally formed at an upper end of the elongated column member for ensuring an insulation distance, and an auxiliary electrode section aligned below the main electrode section without making contact with the main electrode section and made of conductive material. The elongated column member of the upper polymer insulator passes through a center of the auxiliary electrode section in order to fill space charge in the auxiliary electrode section.

column12: Dissipating charge transfer system air terminal
column13: PURPOSE: A lighting arrester system for distributing space charges is provided to prevent the generation of thunderbolt by discharging charges of ground above a support unit having a discharging unit including a plurality of discharging pin inserted to a longitudinal direction of a support bar. CONSTITUTION: A lighting arrester system for distributing space charges includes an electric potential buffering unit, a support unit(120), and a fixing member(110). The electric potential buffering unit includes an upper cap(140) for storing charges of ground, an isolation member(150) formed at a lower end part of the upper cap(140), and a lower cap(160) for electrifying opposite charges to the charges of the upper cap. The support unit(120) is used for fixing the electric potential buffering unit. The support unit(120) includes a discharge part. The discharge part is formed by a plurality of support bars for dispersing and discharging the shock current due to the thunderbolt and a plurality of discharge pins inserted into the support bars. The fixing member(110) is used for fixing the support unit(120). The fixing member is fixed to a protecting target by grounding a lighting arrest line grounded to a ground electrode.

column12: METHOD FOR CREATING DIGITAL TREE MAP BY EXTRACTING FROM OTHER DIGITAL TREE MAPS AND RECORDING MEDIA THEREFOR
column13: A method for creating digital tree map by extracting from other digital tree maps and recording media therefore are provided to process the information filled with the digital tree map according to 'the condition that user wants. The extraction object digital tree map and extraction condition are inputted by the input of the user through the user input means(S130). If the extraction condition is inputted, the branches to satisfy the extraction condition among the extraction object digital tree map are searched(S200). The small trees connecting the subset branches below connected with the searched kinds with 'more significant stage branches connected on the searched kinds are extracted (S300). The small trees extracted is indicated on the digital tree map(S400).

column12: LIGHTNING ARRESTER
column13: A lightning arrester is provided to improve pre-discharge performance between space charge and ground charge by inserting a dielectric between charge plates. A lightning arrester comprises a conductive rod(30), an insulator(34), a charge tube(45a), and a charge rod. The conductive rod is installed on an upper part of an object protected from lightning and connected to a ground device. The insulator is coupled to an end of the rod. The charge tube is formed in a cylindrical shape with a needle-shaped tip(45b) in a central direction and charged with space charge. The charge rod is mounted at a center of the charge tube and connected in the middle of the rod. The charge rod is connected to the rod linearly.

column12: A TRANSMITTER AND A RECEIVER ROBUST TO FREQUENCY OFFSET IN ORTHOGONAL FREQUENCY DIVISION MULTIPLEXING COMMUNICATION
column13: 본 발명에 따른 송신기는, 코딩되고 모듈레이션된 신호 벡터를 선택된 서브캐리어(subcarrier)에 맵핑하는 맵퍼, 맵핑된 신호 벡터를 서브캐리어에 실어 보내기 위해 역 푸리에 변환(Inverse Discrete Fourier Transform)하여 OFDM 심볼을 생성하는 IDFT부, 병렬로 생성되는 상기 OFDM 심볼을 직렬로 출력하는 P/S부, P/S부에서 출력된 OFDM 심볼을 시간 영역에서 반복하여 나이키스트 윈도우 함수를 곱하는 나이키스트 윈도잉부, 및 나이키스트 윈도우 함수가 곱해진 OFDM 심볼에 캐리어 주파수를 곱하여 패스밴드 신호를 생성한 뒤 채널에 전송하는 전송부를 포함하며, 나이키스트 윈도우 함수의 공칭폭은 푸리에 변환의 시간폭과 동일하고, 나이키스트 윈도우 함수는 시간 영역에서 나이키스트 조건을 만족한다. 이에 의하여, 복잡도를 줄이면서, 서브캐리어의 개수에 무관하게 동일한 방식으로 통신을 수행할 수 있게 된다. 특히, 인접 OFDM 심볼이 시간 도메인에서 100%의 효율을 달성할 수 있기 때문에, 5세대와 같은 차세대 통신 방식에 매우 적합하다.

column12: Lightning strike alarm system using bipolar conventional air terminal
column13: A lightning strike alarm system using a Bipolar Conventional Air Terminal (BCAT) is provided. The lightning strike alarm system using BCAT including a rod element to which a ground charge is electrified and an electrification plate-cone or an electrification plate-tube electrified by a thunderstorm cloud, includes a luminescence unit to be electrically connected to the rod element and the electrification plate-cone or the electrification plate-tube and emits light by electric energy electrified to the electrification plate-cone or the electrification plate-tube by the thunderstorm cloud. The lightning strike alarm system enables a user to find that an impulse current of the thunderstorm is normally and safely flown to the ground, and thus, the user may have psychological security.

column12: CHARGE PUMP APPARATUS AND CHARGE PUMPING METHOD
column13: A charge pumping method includes: generating a first boosted voltage by boosting an input voltage by a boosting mode of a first multiplier; changing the level of a voltage charged in at least one capacitor provided in the inside of a charge pump circuit, in preparation for a change in the boosting mode; and generating a second boosted voltage by boosting the input voltage by a boosting mode of a second multiplier.

column12: Test socket and conductive particle
column13: The present invention relates to an inspection socket and a conductive particle thereof, and more particularly, to an inspection socket, which is disposed between a device to be inspected and an inspection device to electrically connect a terminal of the device to be inspected and a pad of the inspection device, comprising: a plurality of conductive units provided at each position corresponding to a terminal of a device to be inspected, and having a plurality of conductive particles vertically disposed in an elastic insulating material; and an insulating support unit provided between the conductive units, and electrically insulating the conductive units from each other while supporting each of the conductive units. At least one of the conductive particles includes: a body unit made of a metal material, and forming an appearance of the conductive particles; and a plurality of silica particles having a part thereof fixed in the body unit, a part of the remainder to protrude from the body unit, and being in contact with the elastic insulating material forming the conductive units to be firmly coupled to the elastic insulating material.

column12: Level shifter and flat panel display comprising the same
column13: A level shifter and a flat panel display comprising the same, with reduced power consumption. The level shifter includes: a first transistor to apply a first voltage to an output terminal in correspondence with a first input signal; a second transistor to apply a second voltage to an output terminal in correspondence with voltage applied between gate and source electrodes thereof; a third transistor to lower the voltage applied between the gate and source electrodes of the second transistor according to the first input signal; and a capacitor to keep the voltage applied between the gate and source electrodes of the second transistor to turn on the second transistor in correspondence with the second input signal.

column12: HAND-HELD DEVICE INCLUDING A DISPLAY AND METHOD FOR NAVIGATING OBJECTS ON THE DISPLAY
column13: PURPOSE: A hand-held device including a display device and a method for navigating objects on the display device are provided to increase the using convenience by intuitionally controlling the object which is displayed on the display unit with a simple operation. CONSTITUTION: An inertia sensor(110) is built in a handheld device and outputs a sensor signal corresponding to the movement of a handheld device. A controller(130) interprets the motion direction of the handheld device according to the sensor signal and generates the command which moves the view frame of the handheld device to the motion direction about the object. A display unit(160) displays the area of the object corresponding to the moved view frame according to the command. The size of a sensor signal and view movement is compares with a scale factor as a medium.

column12: CONNECTOR FOR ELECTRICAL CONNECTION
column13: The present invention relates to a connector for electrical connection and, more particularly, to a connector for electrical connection that is arranged between a terminal of an inspection target device and a pad of an inspection device to provide the electrical connection between the terminal and the pad. The connector includes: a first connection unit which has an upper end capable of coming into contact with the terminal of the inspection target device and extends from the upper end to a lower end; a second connection unit which has a lower end capable of coming into contact with the pad of the inspection device, extends from the lower end to an upper end, and slides on the same plane as the first connection unit; and a spring which is integrally connected to the first connection unit and the second connection unit and moves the upper end of the first connection unit and the lower end of the second connection unit apart from each other, when the upper end of the first connection unit and the lower end of the second connection unit move to become closer to each other, in which the first connection unit and the second connection unit separated from each other can come into contact with each other at least in part when the first connection unit and the second connection unit relatively move to become close to each other.

column12: Apparatus for surface treatment of plastic molded article
column13: The present invention relates to an integrated printing and a surface treatment apparatus. The integrated printing comprises: a printing module comprising a first processing region and a printing unit provided to form a three-dimensional molded body in the first processing region by a printing method; and a surface treatment module positioned adjacent to the printing module, including a second processing region and a gas generator provided to provide gas for treating a surface of the three-dimensional molded body to the second processing region, and configured to be selectively moved to form an overlap region with respect to the first processing region by the second processing region.

column12: PCB-UNIFIED ZEROTH ORDER RESONANCE ANTENNA FOR MILLIMETER-WAVE BAND
column13: The present invention relates to a printed circuit board (PCB)-unified zeroth order resonance antenna for the millimeter-wave band. The PCB-unified zeroth order resonance antenna for the millimeter-wave band includes: an electricity supplying part which is formed on the upper surface of a PCB in multilayer structure, and receives a signal from the outside; a zeroth order resonance (ZOR) radiation part which is formed with an array of unit cells on the upper surface of the PCB, and radiates the signal received from the electricity supplying part; and a via which connects the ZOR radiation part and a ground formed in the PCB. The ZOR radiation part generates zeroth order and a first order mode in a target frequency band, has a butterfly-type radiation pattern, and horizontally radiates electric waves to the surface of the PCB. By the aforementioned present invention, the PCB-unified zeroth order resonance antenna is easily manufactured, is suitable for a millimeter-wave chip-to-chip wireless communications with few data transmission loss, and can improve reliability for product performance and productivity when being applied to a small electronic component.

column12: MATTE CLEAR COATING COMPOSITION FOR VEHICLE
column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a matte clear coating composition for a vehicle that enables uniform application by inhibiting agglomeration upon application while maintaining physical properties of a conventional matte clear coating, such as coating appearance, adherability, impact resistance, and water resistance, and that ensures economic efficiency by reducing the amount of a silica matting agent used.SOLUTION: The matte clear coating composition for a vehicle includes a polymer resin for coating and a matting agent, wherein the matte clear coating composition for a vehicle includes silica and talc as the matting agent, the content of the silica is 1-10 wt.% in the clear coating composition, the content of the talc is 1-15 wt.%, the diameter of the talc is 5-15 μm, the amount of oil absorption is 10-50, the polymer resin for coating is an acrylic resin, a polyester resin, or a urethane resin, and the composition further includes at least one additive selected from the group consisting of a curing agent, a pinhole inhibitor, a flow inhibitor, and a surface conditioner.

column12: Folded cascode operational amplifier having improved phase margin

column12: Wechselstrom-Leistungssteuervorrichtung
column13: An alternating current power control device comprising a phase comparison controller for comparing a phase of an input voltage with that of a first reference voltage, a single-winding transformer for varying the input voltage, a mutual induction reactor for lowering the input voltage by a desired level in response to an output voltage from the single-winding transformer, an output voltage comparator for comparing an output voltage with a second reference voltage, an output current comparator for comparing an output current with a reference current, an OR logic controller for performing an OR operation with respect to output signals from the phase comparison controller and output current comparator, and a switch array for selectively transferring the output voltage from the single-winding transformer to the mutual induction reactor in response to output signals from the output voltage comparator and OR logic controller. According to the present invention, the mutual induction reactor is implemented on the basis of the principle of a linear transformer and has a small capacity corresponding to about 1/10 of a load power. Therefore, a proper power necessary to the saving of energy can be supplied by using the mutual induction reactor. <IMAGE>

A CLOTHES HANGER CRACK
METHOD FOR PRODUCING PEARLESCENT PIGMENT
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a method for producing a pearlescent pigment having uniform particle size and thickness of a coating layer, exhibiting remarkable luster and color saturation and reactive in a short time at normal temperature.

SOLUTION: The method for producing a pearlescent pigment by a precipitation process comprises a step to mix mica with distilled water in a reaction vessel and stir the mixture to produce a slurry, a step to produce an aqueous solution of a titanium salt and an aqueous solution of ammonium bicarbonate (NH4HCO3) as a precipitant, a step to separately pour the titanium salt solution and the ammonium bicarbonate solution to the slurry under stirring and react the substances at normal temperature, and a step to subject the formed precipitate to solid-liquid centrifugal separation, wash the solid with distilled water and calcine the washed material after drying.

column13: A test socket structure in which a contact pin of a defective socket is replaced by block unit, and a pattern of a printed circuit board of a testing equipment is not abraded during testing of a semiconductor device. A fabricating method of a contact pin is disclosed by which the contact pin is hardly deformed and its spring elastic force can be maintained for a long time. Test socket including: a first housing (51) made of an insulating material having a predetermined thickness; a second housing (52) made of an insulating material, a side wall of which is adjacent to a side wall of the first housing; a first (53) and a second elastomers (54) respectively installed at an upper and a lower surfaces of the second housing; and a contact pin block (55) having a plurality of contact pins arranged at predetermined pitches and a fixing unit (55b) for fixing the plurality of contact pins so that they can be moved together, wherein the contact pin block is insertedly installed between the first and the second housings and is contacted with the first and the second elastomers in the vicinity of both end portions of the contact pin.

column12: VERTICAL ORGANIC LIGHT EMITTING TRANSISTOR AND ORGANIC LED ILLUMINATION APPARATUS HAVING THE SAME
column13: Disclosed are a vertical organic light emitting transistor capable of upwardly emitting light and a lamp device including the same. The disclosed lamp device includes a plurality of gate electrode lines which are arranged on a substrate in parallel with a preset space, a gate insulation layer which covers the gate electrode lines on the substrate, a plurality of first electrode lines which overlap with the gate electrode lines or are orthogonal to the gate electrode lines, a first charge transport layer which covers the first electrode lines on the gate insulation layer, a plurality of active layers which are arranged on the first charge transport layer in a matrix to face the first electrode line, a second charge transport layer which covers the active layer on the first charge transport layer, and a plurality of source electrode lines which are orthogonal to the first electrode lines on the second charge transport layer and cross the active layer.

column12: Remote controlling unmanned parking control system
column13: PURPOSE: A remote self service parking control system is provided, which monitors a surrounding environment of a vehicle remotely and performs a required control remotely after receiving a parking position after providing the monitored information to a user using a wireless internet environment. CONSTITUTION: A sensing control part(200) comprises a main control part(290) managing to control input/output signals and peripheral devices and to store information, and a radio telecommunication interface part(210) interfacing with an external radio terminal. An image processor part(330) acquires a surrounding environment of the vehicle with a camera, and a motor control part(230) controls to rotate the camera by 360 deg. and to stop the camera at a random position. A marker projection part(250) projects a marker to enable to read a random position in the image by being projected into the acquired image. A vehicle state recognition control part(270) recognizes and controls a present speed or a gear mode of the vehicle, and an ultrasonic sensor signal processor part(350) recognizes surrounding objects during the parking.

column12: TEST SOCKET
column13: PURPOSE: A test socket is provided to test ICs that operate at a high speed, extend durability of a test device, and automatically align an IC to be tested in a socket. CONSTITUTION: A test socket includes a socket housing(100) and a contact guide film(110). The socket housing is formed of an insulator and has an opening(101) formed in the center of the housing. An IC to be tested is loaded in the socket housing and unloaded from the housing through the opening of the socket housing. The contact guide film that is a hard insulating film is mounted in the socket housing. A plurality of holes are formed in the same pattern as the pattern of external leads of the IC to be tested in the center of the insulating film. A conductive rubber(112) is being inserted into each of the holes. The test socket further includes a housing cover that covers the socket housing while the IC is mounted in the socket housing.

column12: Mobile phone case
Virtual reality mindfulness meditation system and method of the same
column13: The present invention relates to a virtual reality mindfulness meditation system and a method, the system comprising: a virtual reality module which is worn on the head of a user and provides audio-visual data to the user; a server which transmits mindfulness meditation program information to the virtual reality module; and a manager terminal for managing the server. The method comprises: a guide step of transmitting a plurality of mindfulness meditation programs and guide information of the mindfulness meditation programs from the server to the virtual reality module and the plurality of transmitted mindfulness meditation programs and the guide information of the mindfulness meditation programs to the virtual reality module; a selection step of receiving selection of one meditation program from the user among the plurality of mindfulness meditation programs transmitted to the virtual reality module after the guide step; a meditation step of receiving the meditation program from the server for storing the meditation program information selected in the selection step and outputting the same to the virtual reality module. The present invention facilitates professional feedback from medical personnel.

column12: Modulation for broadcasting from multiple transmitters
column13: In a cellular network, randomness is introduced into a transmitted signal at each transmitter, and the resulting received signal, which is the sum of all received signals, fluctuates more in time than a signal transmitted without the introduced randomness. While the introduction of randomness can diminish reception of some parts of the signal at the receiver, the transmitted signal can be encoded using forward error correction coding techniques, which allows the receiver to recover all of the signal information despite some diminished reception. Such randomization provides time diversity so that receivers can have more consistent performance. For broadcasted data, where users with the worst channel condition dictates the overall performance, having consistent performance across users can improve the overall network performance.

column12: TIME DIVISION DRIVING METHOD AND SOURCE DRIVER FOR FLAT PANEL DISPLAY
LIMPHOME DRIVE METHOD OF HYBRID ELECTRIC VEHICLE
column13: PURPOSE: A limp home operation method of a hybrid vehicle is provided to restrictively operate a hybrid function when two out of three current sensors inside a motor controller of the hybrid vehicle are malfunctioning. CONSTITUTION: A limp home operation method of a hybrid vehicle comprises the following steps: detecting the malfunction of a current sensor inside a motor controller; comparing the motor speed with the predetermined speed when just one current sensor is operating; selecting a secondary limp home mode with the minimum motor control operation; measuring the current value of the two broken current sensors based on the normal current sensor, the motor speed and the consumed power amount; and performing the motor control based on the two current values(S61).

column12: AUTOMATIC CONTROLLER OF MOTOR OF AIR PURIFIER
SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR REMOTELY CONTROLLING DATA WIRELESSLY BY USING MOBILE TERMINAL
column13: PURPOSE: A system and method for remotely controlling data wirelessly by using a mobile terminal are provided to allow a callee to quickly know a caller by extracting and sending signature information. CONSTITUTION: In a state that the first mobile terminal(M1) and the second mobile terminal(M2) are normally available for call communication, a mobile communication exchange(16) attempts call connection between the first and second mobile terminals(M1,M2) and transfers voice communication and character information. The mobile communication exchange(16) receives a call connection attempt signal and mobile terminal code information from the first mobile terminal(M1) by the medium of a mobile communication base station(10A), a mobile communication repeater station(12A) and a mobile communication control station and determines whether there is signature information of a corresponding user that has been registered through a management server(MDMS) connected to the mobile communication exchange(16). When the originator mobile terminal(M1) is ringing, signature information of a callee is outputted, and when the receiver mobile terminal(M2) is ringing and a caller number is outputted, signature information of the caller is also outputted.

column12: Test socket
column13: The present invention relates to a testing socket, and more specifically, to a testing socket which is placed between a blood testing device and an inspection device and electrically connects a terminal of the blood testing device and a pad of the inspection device. The socket comprises: an upper probe which comprise an upper housing which has first through-holes extended to a thickness direction every location corresponding to terminals of the blood testing device, and a plurality of first contacting probes which are individually inserted into and fixed in the first through-holes of the upper housing, and can contact each of terminals of the blood testing device; a lower probe which comprises a lower housing having second through-holes extended to a thickness direction every location corresponding to pads of the inspection device, and a plurality of second contacting probes which are individually inserted into and fixed in the second through-holes of the lower housing, and can contact each of terminals of the blood testing device; and a plurality of connecting conductive wires which connect a first contacting probe protruding from the upper housing to a second contacting probe protruding from the lower housing. The first contacting probe and the second contacting probe have a protruding height, protruding towards facing each other, which is different from an edge side and a central side.

column12: STRUCTURE OF A VIBRATION-PROOF LIGHTENING ARRESTER FOR ABSORBING ANOMALOUS CURRENTS
column13: A supporting body of a vibration-proof lighting arrester is provided to prevent motion of a supporting part by absorbing vibration due to wind or earthquake. A supporting body(30) of a vibration-proof lighting arrester includes a vibration absorbing part(33) and a supporting part(31). The vibration absorbing part includes a housing(47), an elastic member, and an angle control part(51). The elastic member is arranged inside the housing. The elastic member includes a buffer spring. The angle control part is positioned on the elastic member. The angle control part includes an axial part and a mounting part. The axial part is connected to the housing. The mounting part is extended from the axial part. An opening part is formed on a top part of the mounting part. A lighting rod or a lighting arrester is mounted in the mounting part. The vibration absorbing part is arranged in the supporting part. The supporting part is electrically connected to the angle control part.
