column12: Electrical test assembly and Electrical test socket
column13: The present invention relates to an electrical test assembly, an electrical test socket, and a device to be tested and, more specifically, to an electrical test assembly containing a device to be tested and an electrical test socket for electrically connecting the device to be tested to a test apparatus. The device to be tested includes: an electrode area where a plurality of terminals are arranged on a lower surface; and a non-electrode area positioned around the electrode area and arranging a first position arrangement unit. The electrical test socket includes: a conductive function area arranging a plurality of conductive parts to show conductivity in a thickness direction; and an insulation area positioned around the conductive function area, wherein, in the insulation area, a second position arrangement unit inserted into the first position arrangement unit is arranged to protrude upwards from a surface of the insulation area for connecting the terminals of the device to be tested to positions corresponding to the conductive parts of the conductive function area respectively. The present invention can realize easy and firm electrical connection between the device under test and the electrical test socket.

column12: POGO PIN, THE FABRICATION METHOD THEREOF AND TEST SOCKET USING THE SAME
column13: Disclosed is a pogo pin including: a hollow body having a spring structure by spirally cutting at least a portion of an outer surface thereof; and a conductive material filling at least an inside of the body. According to the present invention, when testing a semiconductor package, error rate in contact between the package, the pogo pin and a test board can be remarkably reduced, and simultaneously can enhance rigidity and electrical conductivity of the pogo pin. Further, simple componentry of the pogo pin can facilitate its fabrication, reduce fabrication costs, and even foresee fabrication of a micro-pogo pin.

column12: System and method of monitoring, predicting and optimizing production yields in a liquid crystal display (LCD) manufacturing process
column13: A system and method of monitoring LCD production yields, predicting the effects of different testing methodologies on LCD production yields, and optimizing production yields is provided that compares the effect of different testing methodologies on the yields at various stages in the LCD testing and assembly process. The present invention can also be used to predict the effect of different testing methodologies on user-defined parameters, such as profit.

column12: CONNECTOR FOR ELECTRICAL CONNECTION
column13: Provided is a connector which is disposed between an inspection device and a device to be tested to electrically connect the inspection device and the device to be tested. The connector includes a plurality of elastic conductive parts and elastic insulating parts. The plurality of elastic conductive parts can be conductive in the vertical direction. The elastic insulation parts space and insulate the plurality of elastic conductive parts in the horizontal direction. The elastic insulation parts include a plurality of electromagnetic wave shielding portions, and the plurality of electromagnetic wave shielding portions include a plurality of carbon nanotubes which are distributed and arranged along the vertical direction and have magnetic properties.

column12: ANTICORROSION WAX COMPOSITION CONTAINING PLATE ZINC FLAKE
column13: An anticorrosion wax composition containing plate zinc flake includes plate zinc flake 5 to 15 wt %, anticorrosion additives 38 to 50 wt %, wax 15 to 20 wt %, oil 10 to 15 wt %, alkyd resin 5 to 10 wt %, and additives 0.5 to 2 wt %.

column12: BIFURCATED PROBE APPARATUS
column13: The present invention provides a bifurcated probe apparatus which includes a barrel which is formed with a hollow cylindrical shape and has both ends which are opened to have a first opening part and a second opening part, an intermediate member arranged to be slidable along the inner circumferential surface of the barrel, a first plunger arranged to partially protrude from the first opening part along the longitudinal direction of the barrel, a second plunger arranged to partially protrude from the second opening part along the longitudinal direction of the barrel, a first elastic member which is arranged between the first plunger and the intermediate member and elastically supports the first plunger, and a second elastic member which is arranged between the second plunger and the intermediate member and elastically supports the second plunger. Accordingly, the present invention can improve test reliability.

column12: Class AB amplifier having adjustable quiescent current and output current
column13: A class AB amplifier capable of easily controlling the amount of quiescent current and the amount of amplifier output current. The amplifier includes an input circuit that transform a voltage difference between input signals into a current; a current mirror including the (the Pull Up and Pull Down transistors of the) output circuit of the amplifier controls the quiescent current through the Pull Up and Pull Down transistors output circuit; and a control circuit in the current mirror (to which a first control voltage and a second control voltage are applied), adjusts the amount of quiescent current flowing through the output circuit in a first operating mode (by controlling a first bias current that is proportionate to the quiescent current in the current mirror), and controls the amount of the output current sourced or sinked (in response to the change in the voltages at the first and second output nodes of the input circuit) in a second operating mode. The first and second control voltages are DC voltages supplied from the outside of the class AB amplifier, and the amount of first bias current is determined by the first control voltage. The amounts of quiescent current and output current can be easily controlled.

column12: PROBE MEMBER FOR POGO PIN CONNECTOR, MANUFACTURING METHOD THEREFOR AND POGO PIN CONNECTOR COMPRISING SAME
column13: The present invention relates to a probe member for a pogo pin connector, a manufacturing method therefor and a pogo pin connector comprising same. The probe member for a pogo pin connector comprises:a contact part, wherein the contact part is formed from a material having a greater hardness compared to a first body part and a second body part, and the first body part and the second body part areformed from a material exhibiting an electrical conductivity of at least 50% IACS (International Annealed Copper Standard).

column12: HEATING CARBON FIBER AND APPARATUS USING THEREOF
column13: The present invention relates to a heating carbon fiber assembly for DC and an apparatus using the same. According to one embodiment of the present invention, the heating carbon fiber assembly for DC and an apparatus using the same include a basic hot wire made of carbon fiber and a coating layer which is formed between the basic hot wire and a structural fiber. According to one embodiment of the present invention, a plane carbon fiber assembly evaporates water by using heat generated from a plane carbon fiber.

column12: Probe member for pogo pin, method of manufacturing the same, and pogo pin comprising the same
column13: A probe member for a pogo pin, a method of manufacturing the probe member, and a pogo pin including the probe member are disclosed. The probe member for the pogo pin has a contact portion including a material having hardness greater than the hardness of a first body portion and a second body portion, and each of the first and second body portions includes a material having electrical conductivity equal to or greater than 50% IACS (International Annealed Copper Standard).

column12: Manufacturing method of conductive particle and conductive particle manufactured by the method
column13: The present invention relates a method of manufacturing conductive particles, and more particularly to, a method of manufacturing conductive particles, which are to be distributed in an elastic insulative material to form conductive portions for electrical connection, the method including the steps of: (a) preparing a substrate; (b) forming conductive particle-forming recesses in the substrate, the conductive particle-forming recesses having a shape corresponding to desired conductive particles; (c) filling the conductive particle-forming recesses with metal powder; (d) heating the metal powder to form solidified conductive particles; and (e) separating the solidified conductive particles from the substrate.

column12: LOTTERY SYSTEM AND METHOD USING A SETTLEMENT DATA INTERFACE
column13: PURPOSE: A lottery system through a payment data interface and a method thereof are provided to supply a corresponding prize winning money by drawing lottery tickets according to periodic orders of a user who paid a price as a unit of an order of price payments when a credit payment or a cash payment is executed, and informing a drawing result to a member store terminal in real time. CONSTITUTION: Card payment terminals(A1-An) generate card information and payment information through a credit card(CD) as a lottery ticket object in accordance with a received order of the number of corresponding authentication, and check/display a drawing of the credit card(CD) through a sale receipt. An electronic authentication server(ES) receives a credit inquiry request with respect to a price payment of the credit card(CD) from the card payment terminals(A1-An), executes an authentication process, counts an order of each authentication case, and draws a credit card of a specific order which reaches to a predetermined order unit. A financial payment server(CBS1) is mounted in a payment place of a credit card company and executes a price payment process with respect to a credit card authenticated by the electronic authentication server(ES). A member store payment drawing managing server(PSLMS) counts an order of each authentication case through a price payment request signal and card information from the card payment terminals(A1-An), draws a credit card of a specific order which reaches to a predetermined order unit, and transmits drawing information to the card payment terminals(A1-An) with price payment process information of the financial payment server(CBS1).

column12: PAVEMENT METHOD USING NATURAL GRAVEL MIXED WITH TRANSPARENT SYNTHETIC ADHESIVES AND FILLER
column13: PURPOSE: A pavement method using natural gravels is provided to improve the adhesive strength of chips, to shorten a period of construction and to cut down the construction expenses. CONSTITUTION: The pavement method using natural gravels comprises the steps of: spreading gravels(3) mixed with transparent synthetic adhesives(2) on a plane for construction(1) such as a floor or a wall; placing fillers(4) mixed with inorganic materials such as quartz or silica sand and synthetic adhesives among gravels(3); before the filler(4) is hardened, wiping off to make the gravels(3) exposed.

column12: TEST SOCKET
column13: A TEST SOCKET STRUCTURE IN WHICH A CONTACT PIN OF A DEFECTIVE SOCKET IS REPLACED BY BLOCK UNIT, AND A PATTERN OF A PRINTED CIRCUIT BOARD OF A TESTING EQUIPMENT IS NOT ABRADED DURING TESTING OF A SEMICONDUCTOR DEVICE. A FABRICATING METHOD OF A CONTACT PIN IS DISCLOSED BY WHICH THE CONTACT PIN IS HARDLY DEFORMED AND ITS SPRING ELASTIC FORCE CAN BE MAINTAINED FOR A LONG TIME. TEST SOCKET INCLUDING: A FIRST HOUSING (51) MADE OF AN INSULATING MATERIAL HAVING A PREDETERMINED THICKNESS; A SECOND HOUSING (52) MADE OF AN INSULATING MATERIAL, A SIDE WALL OF WHICH IS ADJACENT TO A SIDE WALL OF THE FIRST HOUSING; A FIRST (53) AND A SECOND ELASTOMERS (54) RESPECTIVELY INSTALLED AT AN UPPER AND A LOWER SURFACES OF THE SECOND HOUSING; AND A CONTACT PIN BLOCK (55) HAVING A PLURALITY OF CONTACT PINS ARRANGED AT PREDETERMINED PITCHES AND A FIXING UNIT (55B) FOR FIXING THE PLURALITY OF CONTACT PINS SO THAT THEY CAN BE MOVED TOGETHER, WHEREIN THE CONTACT PIN BLOCK IS INSERTEDLY INSTALLED BETWEEN THE FIRST AND THE SECOND HOUSINGS AND IS CONTACTED WITH THE FIRST AND THE SECOND ELASTOMERS IN THE VICINITY OF BOTH END PORTIONS OF THE CONTACT PIN.

column12: Test connector, manufacturing method of the test connector, and testing method of device-under-test using the test connector
column13: A test connector according to one embodiment comprises: a sheet on XYZ orthogonal coordinates, the sheet being made of an insulating material; and a plurality of conductive units, which are made of a conductive material, extend in the Z-axis direction, are spaced from each other in the X-axis direction, are arranged on the sheet, and have both ends in the Z-axis direction exposed to the surface of the sheet. The plurality of conductive units are formed by allowing a plurality of support units to be etched when intertwined with the plurality of support units, which extend in the X-axis direction and are separated from each other in the Z-axis direction.

column12: ALLOY MIXED WITH NBR, PVC, CPE AND METHOD OF IT
TESTING SOCKET AND CONDUCTIVE PARTICLES
column13: The present invention relates to a testing socket, more specifically to a testing socket which is placed between a device to be tested and a testing apparatus to electrically connect a terminal of theformer and a pad of the latter. The testing socket comprises: a plurality of conductive parts distanced from each other in the planar direction at each location corresponding to a terminal of a device to be tested, and having a plurality of conductive particles arrayed in the width-wise direction in flexible insulating material; and insulating support parts, placed between the plurality of conductive parts distanced from each other, for supporting each conductive part and insulating same in the planar direction, wherein each conductive particle comprises: a columnar trunk part; and two or more protrusions protruding from the top end of the trunk part, wherein between the adjacent protrusions is a groove which is recessed toward the trunk, and the ends of the protrusions have a rounded convex shape, and the center of the groove has a rounded concave shape.

column12: Method of manufacturing conductive particles and conductive particles manufactured by the method
METHOD OF SIMPLY MANUFACTURING JACKET OF LIQUID STORAGE VESSEL AND STRUCTURE THEREOF
column13: PURPOSE: A jacket of a liquid storage vessel is provided to bend the jacket and form welding holes in the jacket within one pressing process, thereby simplifying manufacturing processes of the jacket. CONSTITUTION: A jacket(20) integrally formed with the outer surface of a storage vessel is formed by one pressing process. End portions(21) are formed at the right, left, upper, and lower edges. A plurality of reinforcing bands(24) has passages(25,26) of different sizes. A plurality of welding holes(23) is punched in the reinforcing band at a constant interval. A chamber(22) is formed between the end portions and the reinforcing bands. The chamber is communicated with the passages. A heat medium is circulated in the chamber.

column12: SEMICONDUCTOR DEVICE AND METHOD FOR MANUFACTURING THE SAME
column13: PURPOSE: A semiconductor device and a manufacturing method thereof are provided to reduce a short channel effect by increasing the length of a channel between a plurality of plugs. CONSTITUTION: A gate pattern(210) with a bended shape is formed on a semiconductor substrate. A plurality of plugs is positioned on both sides of the gate pattern in zigzags. A spacer(220) is formed on the sidewall of the gate pattern. The left thickness and right thickness of the spacer are identical based on the gate pattern.

column12: CONDUCTIVE POWDER AND TEST CONNECTOR COMPRISING SAME
column13: The present disclosure according to one aspect relates to conductive powder comprising: core particles; and a polymer layer surrounding the surface of the core particles, wherein the polymer layer has a plurality of conductive particles bonded thereto, and the polymer contains one or more unsaturated hydrocarbons, aromatic hydrocarbons, or both. The present disclosure according to one aspect relates to a test connector comprising: a conductive part including the conductive powder; and a sheet of an insulating material. The conductive powder according to one aspect of the present disclosure may exhibit excellent deformation resistance, abrasion resistance, and resistance stability.

column12: OIL FILTER
LIDAR SYSTEM
column13: According to an embodiment of the present invention, a light detection and ranging system (LIDAR system) includes: a housing which includes at least four openings placed on the surface; a laser which is placed inside the housing and emits light; at least four optical fibers which receive the light emitted by the laser, delivers the light to areas corresponding to at least three openings, and radiates light in different directions to the outside of the housing through the openings; a detection unit which receives light flowing into the housing after reflection outside and converts the light into an electric signal; and a control unit which controls the laser and processes the signal obtained by the detection unit.

column12: TEST PATTERN
column13: A test pattern is provided to measure the passing gate effect and adjacent gate effect by applying the respective different bias in two gate pads. The active area(12) of the island type is arranged as zigzag inside the formed cell well(10) within the semiconductor substrate. The gate line(14) crosses the active area. The bit line(16) intersects with the gate line. The connection active area(13) connects the end part of the other active area with one end of the adjacent active area. The connection active area connects the end part of the other active area with the other side end part of the adjacent active area. The bit line contact(17) connects the connection active area to the bit line. The gate line is connected to the first gate pad(18a) and the second gate pad(18b) in common. The bit line pad(20) is commonly connected with the bit line.

column12: LOW POWER OPERATIONAL AMPLIFIER
column13: PURPOSE: An amplifier which operates at low power is provided to reduce the amount of power consumption by performing an amplifying operation with little current. CONSTITUTION: A first input unit(120) comprises input transistors which convert the difference between an input current and an output current into a corresponding amount of currents. A second input unit(140) controls the voltage of a node corresponded in response to the change in the amount of currents caused by the first input unit. An output unit(160) outputs an output current which is controlled through an output control method that is connected to the node of the second input unit. The output unit generates a quiescent current which flows from the output control method to a ground voltage. One end of the first input unit is connected to the output node. The other end of the first output unit comprises a first control circuit and a second control circuit which are connected to a corresponding input transistor among the input transistors.

column12: Clothes drying machine
column13: A clothes drying machine having a temperature sensor that may be easily repaired or replaced. The clothes drying machine includes a housing forming an external appearance of the clothes drying machine, a drying tub rotatably mounted in the housing, a hot air introducing duct to introduce hot air into the drying tub, a hot air discharging duct to discharge the hot air out of the drying tub, and a temperature sensor mounted at the front part of the hot air discharging duct to detect the temperature of the hot air passing through the hot air discharging duct. The temperature sensor is mounted at the front part of the hot air discharging duct so that an operator has easy access to the temperature sensor. Consequently, repair or replacement of the temperature sensor may be easily and conveniently performed.

column12: A PAVING METHOD HAVING A GRAVELS
/ / building the service system for real-time reverse auction/sale using on/off messaging program
column13: PURPOSE: A method for realizing a real-time reverse-auction/sale service system is provided to offer a product fit to user's request to a user by facilitating the goods PR(Public Relations) and the sale information exchange between the user and a seller through a direct connection using the on/offline messaging program. CONSTITUTION: A message service integrating an online and an offline component is constructed to a reverse-auction structure using a web server in order to maximize a real-time element. The user requests and receives a list and the information for a shop or a user group to a server. The information for the goods is offered to the requestor by registering the product information to the server. If the user request purchase, the user directly orders the goods in real-time through an instant messaging program. In case of the offline, the user receives the information through an SMS(Short Message Service) or an e-mail. The goods sale is promoted by exchanging the goods information through a users meeting and supporting friendship between users of congenial tastes.

column12: SOCKET CONNECTION TYPE LED SECURITY LAMP
column13: PURPOSE: A socket connection type led security lamp is provided to prevent a circuit from being damaged by efficiently cooling an LED lamp by using a thermoelectric device. CONSTITUTION: A socket(2) is included on a pillar(1) which is fixed on a surface. A base(11) is connected to the socket. A body(12) includes a space for accepting a light emitting device. A transparent cover is fixed with a clamp in a bottom opening portion of the body. A heat radiation fin(12a), which releases heat generated from an LED lamp in the light emitting device, is included on an outside of the body.

column12: Operational amplifier with overdriving circuit and method for same
column13: Disclosed is an operational amplifier including an overdriving circuit capable of reaching a target voltage within an operation time by outputting a higher voltage than the target voltage when an RC delay time is greater. The operational amplifier may including an overdriving circuit, in which first and second input terminals and an output terminal may be provided, an input voltage may be applied to the first input terminal, a second input terminal may be connected to the output terminal, and the input voltage applied to the first input terminal may be overdriven to have a certain level to be outputted to the output terminal, may include: first and second overdriving units performing an overdriving operation at a rising edge and a falling edge, respectively.

column12: TEST SOCKET
column13: The present invention relates to a test socket and, more specifically, to a test socket comprising: a housing which has an accommodation space accommodating a device-to-be-tested on which an electrical test is to be performed, and which has an open upper part; a cover capable of opening/closing the open upper part of the housing; a pusher device provided in the cover so as to downwardly press the device-to-be-tested placed in the housing; a temperature control means for injecting air or a refrigerant of a predetermined temperature into the accommodation space so as to regulate the temperature in the accommodation space; and a sealing means capable of sealing the accommodation space from the outside when the cover closes the housing, wherein the sealing means comprises: a first packer which is disposed on the housing upper surface facing the cover and which encompasses the accommodation space; a second packer spaced apart from the first packer, and disposed on the housing upper surface so as to encompass the first packer; and a vacuuming means for forming a vacuum state between the first packer and the second packer.

column12: TEST SOCKET APPARATUS
column13: The present invention relates to a test socket apparatus and, more specifically, a test socket apparatus comprising: a body part fixedly disposed at a lower side of a test substrate; a cover part which is disposed at an upper side of the test substrate and elastically supported by the body part and thus can move upward and downward; an adaptor in which a device to be tested is stably placed and which is disposed between the body part and the cover part and installed at an upper side of the test substrate; and a latch means which moves in association with the upward and downward movement of thecover part and is rotatably connected to each of the body part and the cover part so as to pressurize, toward the test substrate, the upper portion of the device to be tested stably placed in the adaptor, wherein the cover part operates the latch means while at least a part thereof passes through the test substrate, with the concomitant upward and downward movement thereof with respect to the body part disposed at a lower side of the test substrate.

column12: CAMERA LENS MODULE TESTING SOCKET
column13: The present invention relates to a camera lens module test socket which comprises: a base plate (10) installed on a printed circuit board connected with a test device; a lens module receiving part (20) installed on the base plate (10), and including an image sensor (25) sensing a test image obtained through a camera lens module (200); three pogo blocks (30a,30b,40) touching three surfaces of the camera lens module (200) received in the lens module receiving part (20); a cam plate (50) making first and second pogo blocks (30a,30b) among the three pogo blocks (30a,30b,40) touch both side terminals of the camera lens module (200), and making a central pogo block (40) touch a rear terminal of the camera lens module (200); and a pneumatic cylinder moving the cam plate (50) backward and forward to make the three pogo blocks (30a,30b,40) touch the three surfaces of the camera lens module (200). Therefore, the present invention is capable of improving a lifespan of a pogo pin through a linear touch between the camera lens module and the pogo blocks, improving a test speed by having a simple structure, reducing material costs and the weight by minimizing components, and saving production costs through the reduction of workers by minimizing assembly processes.

column12: DEVICE ARRAY FOR SENSING A GAS OR GAS MIXTURE AND FABRICATION METHOD OF THE SAME
INTEGRATED CONTROL APPARATUS AND METHOD OF ESC AND MDPS
column13: PURPOSE: A device and a method for synthetically controlling electronic stability control(ESC) and motor driven power steering(MDPS) are provided to improve handling performance by directly changing MDPS control characteristic according to slip angle. CONSTITUTION: A device for synthetically controlling ESC and MDPS(100) detects motor torque and steering torque from a torque sensor(125). A vehicle speed sensor detects vehicle speed. In case of controlling handling, ESC operation rate is received and assist rate is controlled based on the received motor torque, steering torque, vehicle speed, and ESC operation rate. According to the controlled assist rate, current is outputted to a motor and a handling function is implemented in the MDPS. In case of controlling asymmetrical surfaces, information about the detected motor torque and steering torque is delivered to the ESC. Superposed torque command receives from the ESC. The MDPS implements the received superposed torque command.

column12: Semiconductor device having delay drift compensation circuit that compensates for delay drift caused by temperature and voltage variations in clock tree
column13: A semiconductor device having a delay drift compensation circuit that compensates for a delay drift caused by temperature and voltage variations in a clock tree includes a clock driver having an output port, a first circuit having an input port, a first signal path between the output port of the clock driver and the input port of the first circuit and a first delay drift compensation circuit. The first delay drift compensation circuit, which is coupled with the first signal path, reduces a delay time of the first signal path when a power supply voltage increases, and increases the delay time of the first signal path when a temperature increases.

column12: SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR ROBOT POSITION CALIBRATION
column13: According to an embodiment of the present invention, a robot position correction system for correcting a position of a robot comprises: a correction plate having a plurality of correction grooves and an inclined surface formed at an edge of an inlet of the correction grooves; an optical unit including a laser beam generator attached to the robot movable with respect to the correction plate along one plane of the correction plate and for emitting laser beams toward the correction groove of the correction plate, and a light receiver for receiving reflected light of the laser beam reflected from the correction plate to measure the amount of light; a photographing unit for photographing the light receiver to generate an image; and a control unit including a signal processor which determines whether a position error has occurred based on the signal generated by the light receiver and calculates the position error amount by measuring the position of the reflected light received by the light receiver from the image generated by the photographing unit when the position error has occurred, and a robot position corrector which corrects the position of the robot based on the position error amount.

column12: LINEAR GUIDE WITH UPPER SEAL FIXED THERETO
column13: To provide a linear guide capable of fixing an upper seal installed in an end seal, without making the upper seal eccentric to a right or left side.SOLUTION: A linear guide comprises an end plate provided on the front and rear sides of a block arranged on a rail in a slidable manner, an end seal inserted into the end plate, and an upper seal installed in the end seal so as to be positioned on an upper side of the rail. The upper seal is formed with an end seal insertion recess part of which an end part is opened and into which the end seal is inserted. The end seal is formed with a stationary part projecting from a surface opposite to the block and inserted into the end seal insertion recess part.SELECTED DRAWING: Figure 12

column12: ROOM TEMPERATURE PROCESS OF PEARLY PIGMENTS BY PRECIPITATION METHOD
column13: A method for preparing a pearly glossy pigment at a room temperature is provided to improve the uniformity of particle size and thickness of a coated layer and to enhance gloss and saturation. A method for preparing a pearly glossy pigment comprises the steps of dissolving mica in distilled water at a reaction bath and stirring it to prepare a slurry; preparing a titanate aqueous solution and preparing an ammonium bicarbonate aqueous solution as a precipitant; injecting the titanate aqueous solution and the ammonium bicarbonate aqueous solution to the slurry with stirring; and separating the generated precipitate by centrifugation just after the termination of reaction, washing it with distilled water, drying it, and sintering it.

column12: TW I722733 B
CELL PHONE CASE FOR PROTECTING HINGE
column13: Provided is a cell phone case for protecting a hinge. The cell phone case includes a first cover unit which is provided with a first peripheral part to be coupled to a first body of a foldable mobile phone, a second cover unit which is provided with a second peripheral part to be coupled to a second body of the foldable mobile phone, faces the first cover unit, and independent from the first cover unit, a connection unit which includes a flexible material to enable bending deformation and elastic restoration, extends from a first cover unit-side edge of the second cover unit in a direction in which the first cover unit and the second cover unit face each other, and is provided with a hole at an end thereof, and a third cover unit which includes a rigid material to maintain the original form, and is provided with a magnetic member to be attached to and detached from the hinge of the foldable cell phone and a snap member to be coupled to the hole of the connection unit. The cell phone case may simplify the structure and stably protect the hinge of the foldable cell phone.

column12: Mask waste treatment device using sterilization unit
column13: The present invention relates to an apparatus for treating a mask waste using a sterilization unit, and more specifically, to an apparatus for treating a mask waste using a sterilization unit, comprising: a body provided with an insertion port into which a waste mask is inserted; a crushing part which crushes the mask inside the body to generate fragments; a sterilization unit that releases a bactericidal substance that sterilizes the fragments; and a recovery unit for recovering the fragments. Based on the structure, the whole size of the treatment device can be reduced into a small machine, the movement is more convenient, and the removal rate of harmful bacteria attached to the disposable mask can reach 99.99% by utilizing the bactericidal substances.

column12: APPARATUS FOR ASSORTING ORE
column13: Disclosed is an apparatus for assorting ore. According to one aspect of the present invention, an apparatus for assorting ore includes a vibration frame for performing a process of assorting a particle size of ore therein; an assorting screen inclined at the inside of the vibration frame to assort the ore and pulverized ore; and a dust absorbing unit for absorbing ore dust generated in the vibration frame.

column12: Test socket and conductive particle
column13: The present invention relates to a socket for inspection, and more particularly, to a socket for inspection which is disposed between a device to be inspected and an inspection apparatus and electrically connects a terminal of the device to be inspected and a pad of the inspection apparatus to each other. The socket includes a plurality of conductive portions spaced from each other in the surface direction at positions corresponding to the terminals of the device to be inspected and having a plurality of conductive particles aligned in the thickness direction in an elastic insulating material; and an insulating support portion disposed between the plurality of conductive portions spaced apart from each other to support the respective conductive portions and insulate the conductive portions in the surface direction, wherein the conductive particles include a columnar body portion, a first central protrusion protruding from the upper center of the body portion, and a pair of first side protrusions disposed on both sides of the first central protrusion and protruding from the upper end of the body portion, and a first groove portion recessed toward the body portion is provided between the first central protrusion and the first side protrusion.

column12: Alternating current power control device
column13: An alternating current power control device comprising a phase comparison controller for comparing a phase of an input voltage with that of a first reference voltage, a single-winding transformer for varying the input voltage, a mutual induction reactor for lowering the input voltage by a desired level in response to an output voltage from the single-winding transformer, an output voltage comparator for comparing an output voltage with a second reference voltage, an output current comparator for comparing an output current with a reference current, an OR logic controller for performing an OR operation with respect to output signals from the phase comparison controller and output current comparator, and a switch array for selectively transferring the output voltage from the single-winding transformer to the mutual induction reactor in response to output signals from the output voltage comparator and OR logic controller. According to the present invention, the mutual induction reactor is implemented on the basis of the principle of a linear transformer and has a small capacity corresponding to about 1/10 of a load power. Therefore, a proper power necessary to the saving of energy can be supplied by using the mutual induction reactor. <IMAGE>

column12: WAVEFORM GENERATION CIRCUIT
column13: Waveform generation circuits are provided. A waveform generation circuit includes a waveform generation block configured to generate a waveform signal corresponding to a driving control signal, and a control signal generation block configured to generate the driving control signal to compensate the waveform signal for an environmental factor affecting the waveform generation circuit.

column12: METHOD FOR MANUFACTURING OF SEMICONDUCTOR DEVICE
column13: A method for manufacturing a semiconductor device is provided to improve an operational characteristic of a transistor by widening a line width of a bonding part of a gate in a recess forming process. A first photoresist layer is formed on an active region. A first photoresist layer pattern having an inclined sidewall is formed by exposing and developing the first photoresist layer. A first recess having a line width larger than a line width of a gate region is formed by etching the active region. A second recess is formed in the gate region corresponding to a lower part of the first recess. A gate insulating layer(20), a gate polysilicon layer, a gate electrode layer, and a gate hard mask layer are formed on an entire surface including the first and second recesses. A gate(24) is formed by etching the gate hard mask layer, the gate electrode layer, and the gate polysilicon layer.

column12: CLOTHING DRYER
column13: A clothing dryer is provided to prevent foreign substance from being stacked in the interior of a housing due to introduced external air by installing a filter in a suction hole. A clothing dryer includes a housing(110), a rotary drum(120), and a suction part(150). The suction part includes a rotation member(152), a filter(155), a first suction duct(156), a second suction duct(157), a heater, and a blowing fan(180). The rotation member is disposed on the front side of a housing and a suction hole is formed in the rotation member. The filter is installed on the inner side of the rotation member to filter external air sucked through the suction hole. The first suction duct is disposed at a lower portion of the rotary drum to guide the air filtered through the filter. The second suction duct is bent from the first suction duct to the upper side to be communicated with the rear side of the rotary drum. The heater is installed in the first suction duct to heat the external heat. The blowing fan guides the external air into the interior of the rotary drum through the first suction duct and the second suction duct.

column12: IMAGE CONSULTATION DEVICE
column13: PURPOSE: An image consultation device is provided to spend advertisement cost in the way of reducing the cost by preset CPC(Cost Per Call) unit price in hospital account when a client performs consult request or consult reservation through a menu, thereby providing free video consultation to the client. column13: PURPOSE: A waste plastic pyrolyzing apparatus having an auxiliary pyrolyzing device using waste heat is provided to improve the productivity of pyrolytic oil, since waste plastic is dissolved using high combustion heat. CONSTITUTION: A waste plastic pyrolyzing apparatus comprises a combustion furnace(10), a pyrolyzing tank(20), and a secondary pyrolyzing device. A burner(160) for supplying the combustion heat is connected to a furnace. A chimney(11) of the furnace discharges the combustion heat. column12: METHOD FOR FORMING TRIPLE GATE OF HIGH VOLTAGE EEPROM DEVICE TO CONTROL THICKNESS OF OXIDE LAYER AND GUARANTEE UNIFORMITY, REPEATABILITY AND STABILITY OF PROCESS
column13: PURPOSE: A method for forming a triple gate of a high voltage EEPROM(electrically erasable and programmable read only memory) device is provided to control the thickness of an oxide layer and guarantee uniformity, repeatability and stability of a process by performing two thermal oxide processes and two precleaning processes. CONSTITUTION: A predetermined cell is formed in a silicon substrate(100). A high voltage gate oxide layer(114) and a high voltage HLD(high temperature low pressure deposition) oxide layer(116) are sequentially deposited on the substrate. A high voltage transistor region on the HLD oxide layer is covered with the first photoresist layer, and the region for forming an input/output transistor and a logic transistor is opened. By using the first photoresist layer as an etch mask, the high voltage gate oxide layer is removed and a predetermined depth of the HLD oxide layer is eliminated. The second photoresist layer is formed on the high voltage gate oxide layer except the portion for forming the logic transistor and on the HLD oxide layer from which the predetermined depth is eliminated. By using the second photoresist layer as an etch mask, the HLD oxide layer is removed to form a gate oxide layer(128) for the input/output transistor. A gate oxide process is performed on a region for forming the logic transistor to form a gate oxide layer for the logic transistor.

column12: Memory device and method for writing data in memory cell with boosted bitline voltage
column13: Provided are a method of writing data into a memory cell with a boosted write voltage and a memory device that performs the method. The method involves (a) transmitting data input in response to a write command to a bitline; (b) writing the input data on the bitline into a memory cell capacitor via a memory cell transistor; (c) generating a write boosting signal in response to the write command and a bitline precharge signal; (d) boosting a voltage of a capacitor connected between the write boosting signal and the bitline in response to the write boosting signal; (e) boosting a voltage of the bitline to a predetermined level; and (f) rewriting the input data into the memory cell capacitor with the boosted voltage of the bitline.

System and method for improving TFT-array manufacturing yields
column13: A system and method for detecting defects in TFT-array panels is provided that improves defect detection accuracy by adjusting the thresholding parameters used to classify defective pixels when the number of defects reported by a TFT-array testing system exceeds a predetermined critical number. In a preferred embodiment, the thresholding parameters are adjusted until the number of reported defects is less than or equal to the predetermined critical number. The predetermined critical number represents a threshold number for determining if the number of reported defects is abnormally high. Reducing the number of reported defects to a number equal to or less than the predetermined critical number will decrease the operation time of the TFT-array repair equipment, because of the reduced number of potential defects it will be required to handle, and will also result in the TFT-array testing system reporting a smaller number of potential defects, with the potential defects that are reported having a higher probability of being real defects.

column12: Source driver in liquid crystal display device, output buffer included in the source driver, and method of operating the output buffer
column13: Provided is an output buffer, which may be included in a source driver of a liquid crystal display (LCD) device. The output buffer may include a differential amplification unit and an output unit. The differential amplification unit may generate control currents by amplifying the difference between the voltages of an analog image signal and a signal output from the output buffer. The output unit outputs the amplified analog image signal in response to the control currents. The amount of bias current used to drive the differential amplification unit increases during a charge recycling period, and the amount of quiescent current flowing through the output unit decreases during the charge recycling period. The amount of the bias current used to drive the differential amplification unit decreases during a driving period, and the amount of the quiescent current flowing through the output unit increases during the driving period.

column13: 본 발명은 체크업 박스를 통하여 진단한 차량의 상태 정보를 무선 단말기를 통하여 오토 체크업센터로 전송하고, 차량의 상태 정보를 입력받은 체크업센터는 이에 대응하는 정보를 차량 협력업체에 전송하여 차량의 관리가 용이하고 긴급상황에 대처할 수 있도록 한다. 이러한, 본 발명은 차량의 원격관리 서비스 방법에 있어서, 차량의 진단/점검 장치로부터 차량에 관한 각종 체크업 신호를 송/수신하는 단계와, 수신된 체크업 신호 및 차량에 관한 각종 정보를 데이타 베이스화하는 단계와, 차량사용자, 협력업체 및 공공기관에 상기 정보를 전송하는 단계와 입력된 정보를 그 종류에 따라 일상적 관리 점검을 이루는 사용자DB 및 긴급DB로 나누고, 차량사용자, 협력업체 및 공공기관으로부터 입력되는 대응 정보를 차량의 진단/점검 장치로 전송하는 단계를 포함하여 이루어진다. 따라서, 본 발명은 자동차의 일상적 관리 및 운행 중 발생할 수 있는 긴급상황을 빠르고 편리하게 해결할 수 있도록 하는 효과를 제공한다.

column12: BIPOLAR CONVENTIONAL AIR TERMINAL

Accordingly, the present invention prevents a first cap from being separated from a combining insulation protrusion while the first cap rotates by generating vibration by an earthquake or a thunderstorm so as to prevent mutual coherence from being weakened.

column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a data receiver using a signal integration system so as to reduce high frequency noise generated in the case of detecting data at high speed, and a data reception method.

SOLUTION: This data receiver is equipped with an integrating and amplifying circuit and a sensing and amplifier circuit, and the integrating and amplifying circuit integrates and amplifies the difference between a pair of differential reference signals and input data, and outputs the first differential signals in a pair and the second differential signals in a pair, and the sensing and amplifier circuit senses and amplifies the difference between the first differential signals in a pair and the difference between the second differential signals in a pair thereby detecting the above input data. According to the data receiver and the data reception method using the signal integration system, high frequency noise generated in the case of detecting data at high speed can be reduced, and also according to a data receiver and a data reception method which detect data by integrating and amplifying signals being inputted through two reference signal lines and a data line, the data can be detected at high speed and accurately by a differential signal system insensitively to the change of pressure, voltage, and temperature.

column12: SURGE PROTECTION DEVICE FOR COMMUNICATION IN MULTIPLEX PROTECTION MODE
column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a surge protection device for communication in a multiplex protection mode, to which additional voltage needs not to be applied in order to determine whether a surge protection circuit is damaged or not.SOLUTION: The surge protection device for communication in a multiplex protection mode comprises: a surge protection circuit portion 30 that is provided between an input line 11 and an output line 21 and has at least two surge protection circuits 31 and 32 arranged in parallel; circuit switching portions 50 and 60 that selectively connect the input line 11 and the output line 21 to either one of the surge protection circuits 31 and 32; a condition measuring portion 70 that measures an input voltage flowing into an input end of the input line 11 and a second discharge voltage from the surge protection circuits 31 and 32 to a grounding end and compares the input voltage and the second discharge voltage respectively with a predetermined reference voltage; a control circuit portion that detects, using a result of the comparison with the input voltage and a result of the comparison with the second discharge voltage, whether the connected surge protection circuit are abnormal or not and switches the circuit to the other surge protection circuit at the circuit switching portions 50 and 60.

column12: HYDRAULIC BREAKER WITH IMPACT ABSORPTION STRUCTURE
column13: PURPOSE: A hydraulic breaker with an impact absorption structure is provided to absorb impact force generated in hitting and improve convenience and workability. CONSTITUTION: A hydraulic breaker with an impact absorption structure comprises a head cap(10), a cylinder main body(20), a front head(40), a hydraulic valve(60), an accumulator(70) and an impact absorbing device. The head cap is filled with nitrogen gas form the upper part. A piston(30) is installed on the cylinder main body to be reciprocated. In the front head, a piston mobile hole(41), a chisel mobile hole(42), and a piston catching part(43) are formed. In the piston mobile hole, the bottom side of a rod(31) of a piston is reciprocated. The chisel mobile hole is formed on the bottom side of the piston mobile hole. In the chisel mobile hole, a chisel(50) is reciprocated. The piston catching part is formed on the boundary portion of the piston mobile hole and the chisel mobile hole. The piston catching part is contacted with end projection(31a) formed on the rod. The hydraulic valve is coupled on the cylinder main body and controls the reciprocation of the piston. The impact absorbing device is equipped at the contact part of the piston and the front head.

CONSTITUTION: The first leads(36a,38a) of an upper semiconductor chip(30a) are electrically connected to the second leads(36b,38b) of a lower semiconductor chip(30b), respectively. A printed circuit pattern including conductive lines is formed on the lower portion of the upper semiconductor chip(30a) or on the upper portion of the lower semiconductor chip(30b) for electrically connecting between the first predetermined lead of the upper semiconductor chip(30a) and the second predetermined lead of the lower semiconductor chip(30b). Preferably, the printed circuit pattern is made of conductive ink.

column12: WATER TREATMENT DEVICE WITH IMPROVED EFFICIENCY
column13: The present invention provides a waste treatment device with improved efficiency which may remove flocculent floc and suspended particles included in raw water. The waste treatment device with improved efficiency comprises: a mixing tank for inputting coagulant into raw water to agitate and agglomerating foreign matters in the raw water to form and grow floc; a flotation tank for making the floc agglomerated from the mixing tank with a first fine bubble obtained by bubbling up saturated water to float; a suspended particle removing tank for making suspended particles included in processed water contact with a second fine bubble having a positive charge to float the suspended particles above water; a floc storing tank to collect the floc and the suspended particles floated above the water of the flotation tank and the suspended particle removing tank; a deodorizing tank for making third fine bubble having OH-radical ozone water with the processed water to deodorize stink; and a processed water tank to store the deodorized processed water. The floc storing tank is spaced apart from a bottom surface to divide the suspended particle removing tank and the deodorizing tank. The deodorizing tank heats and sterilizes particles of a third fine bubble through micro-wave and activates reaction with stink to accelerate oxidation decomposition of stink components by OH-radical.

column12: SOURCE DIRVER, COMMON VOLTAGE DRIVER, AND DRIVING METHOD FOR DISPLAY DEVICE USING TIME DIVISION DRIVING METHOD

A source driver includes first and second buffers(620,670), plural first switches(622), and a source driver(626). The first buffer buffers a voltage. The first switches are connected between source lines corresponding to an output terminal of the first buffer and source lines. The second buffer buffers an analog voltage corresponding to digital image data. Current mode output driver
column13: A current mode output driver and output current control method of controlling an output current using a gate voltage are provided. The current mode output driver, which outputs data read from a memory core to a transmission line, includes a gate voltage control circuit, a bias circuit, and a driver circuit. The gate voltage control circuit generates a predetermined gate voltage in response to a current control signal. The bias circuit outputs the gate voltage as a first enable signal in an active mode, and outputs a ground voltage as a second enable signal in a standby mode. The driver circuit drives a predetermined output current in response to the first enable signal, outputs the predetermined output voltage to the transmission line according to the data, and stops its operation in response to the second enable signal. The gate voltage control circuit changes the level of the gate voltage according to a value of the current control signal and output the changed result. Therefore, it is possible to easily increase resolution of an output current and reduce the occupied area of the current mode output driver, thereby facilitating a circuit design.

column12: Oscillator and method for operating the same
column13: An oscillator includes a first comparator circuit, a second comparator circuit, an oscillation signal generator circuit, and a frequency voltage generator circuit. The first comparator circuit generates a first pulse when a frequency voltage reaches a first reference voltage, and the second comparator circuit generates a second pulse when the frequency voltage reaches a second reference voltage. The oscillation signal generator circuit generates an oscillation signal by latching a first voltage in response to the first pulse and latching a second voltage in response to the second pulse. The frequency voltage generator circuit raises or lowers the frequency voltage in response to the oscillation signal. The driving capability of the first comparator circuit is reduced at the latching of the first voltage and is restored at the latching of the second voltage. The driving capability of the second comparator circuit is reduced at the latching of the second voltage and is restored at the latching of the first voltage.

Offset code of the comparator is determined from the code of an output voltage by enabling the comparator under the that voltages of the two input ports are equal. Stress condition of generating hot carrier in at least one transistor constituting the comparator. The step is implemented by increasing an operation voltage of the comparator. The comparator includes at least one cross-coupled PMOS transistor(35,36) and at least one cross-coupled NMOS transistor(33,34).

column12: Adaptive input voltage controlled voltage booster
column13: Provided is a voltage booster adaptively controlled by an input voltage. The voltage booster includes an Operational Transconductance Amplifier (OTA) having positive and negative input terminals and generating an output current in response to a voltage difference between the positive and negative input terminals. The positive input terminal of the OTA receives a voltage obtained by dividing a target output voltage of the voltage booster by n, and the negative input terminal of the OTA receives a voltage obtained by dividing an output voltage of the voltage booster by n. The output current of the OTA charges an input capacitor to generate a first input voltage. A buffer receives the first input voltage and outputs a second input voltage. The second input voltage is input to a voltage boosting unit to generate the output voltage having a voltage equal to n times the second input voltage, where n ≥ 1.

column12: Test socket
column13: A test socket structure in which a contact pin of a defective socket is replaced by block unit, and a pattern of a printed circuit board of a testing equipment is not abraded during testing of a semiconductor device. A fabricating method of a contact pin is disclosed by which the contact pin is hardly deformed and its spring elastic force can be maintained for a long time. Test socket including: a first housing made of an insulating material having a predetermined thickness; a second housing made of an insulating material, a side wall of which is adjacent to a side wall of the first housing; a first and a second elastomers respectively installed at an upper and a lower surfaces of the second housing; and a contact pin block having a plurality of contact pins arranged at predetermined pitches and a fixing unit for fixing the plurality of contact pins so that they can be moved together, wherein the contact pin block is insertedly installed between the first and the second housings and is contacted with the first and the second elastomers in the vicinity of both end portions of the contact pin.

column12: Chemical probe field effect transistor for measuring the surface potential of a gate electrode
column13: A chemical probe field effect transistor (10) for measuring surface potential as a function of temperature and used for chemical sensing. Source and drain regions (14, 16) in a semiconductor substrate (12) define a channel region (34). A gate insulating layer (18) covers the channel region, and a gate electrode layer (20) is disposed above the gate insulating layer to provide a gap (22) between the gate insulating layer and the gate electrode layer. This gap permits a fluid to contact an exposed surface (28) of the gate electrode layer. A heating layer (30) is disposed overlying the gate electrode layer to regulate its temperature. The surface potential of the gate electrode layer changes in response to the presence of certain chemicals in the contacting fluid.

column12: Bipolar Conventional Air Terminals
column13: The present invention relates to a bipolar arrester including: a rod member which serves as an inflow path of a lightning current; and a fixing plate to fixedly support the rod member. A vacuum space part is formed in the rod member, and a vibration cancelling part is provided in the vacuum space part and includes a permanent magnet making interaction with a current introduced from lightening. A rod cap has an anodized film formed by anodizing metal with respect to the surface of the rod cap. Accordingly, the rod member and the fixing plate may be prevented from being shaken due to vibrations as much as possible. Accordingly, outer portions of the rod member and the fixing plate may be prevented from being damaged or deformed, and a bolt screwed with the fixing plate may be prevented from being released due to the vibrations in advance. In addition, a lightening arrester is coupled to and installed on an upper portion of a support structure of a 5G antenna having strong directionality in transmitting and receiving a radio wave, thereby preventing a fault from being caused in transmitting and receiving the radio wave, as a directing angle of the antenna is changed due to the damage and deformation resulting from the vibrations and shaking caused by power discharge which occurs between a charging tube and a rod when the vibrations may be caused due to current shock of a large current or when fine thundercloud approaches.

column12: Anticorrosion wax composition containing plate zinc flake

column12: DICTIONARY SYSTEM
column13: A system for searching a dictionary is provided to enable a user to easily/quickly search a word and display a search result with convenient carrying while reading printed media by organically connecting the printed media and an electronic device, which includes a computer, providing a dictionary function. A character string obtainer(11) obtains a character string to be searched by scanning the character string among contents printed in the printed media. A dictionary searching/displaying device(12) searches the contents corresponding to the obtained character string from the dictionary and displays the search result. A wireless connector(13) connects the character string obtainer and the dictionary searching/displaying device. The wireless connector wirelessly transmits the character string scanned in the character string obtainer to the dictionary searching/displaying device.

column13: Provided is an output buffer, which may be included in a source driver of a liquid crystal display (LCD) device. The output buffer may include a differential amplification unit and an output unit. The differential amplification unit may generate control currents by amplifying the difference between the voltages of an analog image signal and a signal output from the output buffer. The output unit outputs the amplified analog image signal in response to the control currents. The amount of bias current used to drive the differential amplification unit increases during a charge recycling period, and the amount of quiescent current flowing through the output unit decreases during the charge recycling period. The amount of the bias current used to drive the differential amplification unit decreases during a driving period, and the amount of the quiescent current flowing through the output unit increases during the driving period.

column12: METHOD FOR REALIZING ELECTRONIC PROGRAM GUIDE OF DIGITAL BROADCASTING RECEIVER
column13: PURPOSE: A method for realizing an electronic program guide(EPG) of a digital broadcasting receiver is provided to update EPG information on the bottom by designating a specific data on a calendar. CONSTITUTION: According to the method, an electronic program guide(EPG) is enabled(ST41). A cursor moves to a calendar on the enabled electronic program guide screen(ST42). A date on the calendar is selected by the movement of the cursor(ST43), and electronic program guide data corresponding to the selected date is filtered by an event information table(EIT)(ST44). A reference time of the electronic program guide is read(ST45). And the screen is updated with the selected date and the prior electronic program guide and then is displayed(ST46).

column13: Disclosed is a fall-preventing device for a rotary quick coupler. The fall-preventing device for a rotary quick coupler comprises: a main body connected to arms of heavy equipment and having a connection plate; a rotary block having a rotation plate disposed opposite to the connection plate and an attachment detachably connected thereto; a hydraulic connection unit rotatably connecting the connection plate and the rotation plate and transmitting a hydraulic pressure required to drive the attachment and a hydraulic pressure required to connect or disconnect the attachment; a driving unit provided between the connection plate and the rotation plate to provide power for rotating the rotary block in a forward or reverse direction from the main body; and a protrusion unit preventing the rotary block from being separated from the main body by having the hydraulic connection unit seated on the driving unit when the hydraulic connection unit is separated from the connection plate and then the hydraulic connection unit and the rotary block are separated from the main body and fall. According to the present invention, the fall-preventing device can prevent the hydraulic connection unit and the rotary block from being separated from the main body, thus preventing accidents caused by falls.

column12: SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR PROVIDING INTEGRATED COMMUNICATION ID
column13: The present invention discloses a system and method for providing an integrated communication ID and it is an object of the present invention to allow a caller to connect to a receiver's a variety of communication equipments conveniently, with only an integrated communication ID of the receiver being perceived, by allocating a single, inherent communication ID to multiple users and managing multiple directory communication equipment data to enable call connection. In the application of the present invention, with only the integrated communication ID of the receiver being perceived, the caller can execute connection to the corresponding receiver's mobile communication terminal devices, wired terminal devices, facsimiles, homepages and the like by relaying, and an unspecific, third party can access conveniently to a variety of public open information using one integrated communication ID. By this, there is no need to memorize a wide variety of number including various telephone numbers, homepage URLs, mail IDs, messenger IDs and the like among the flood of information.

column12: Pusher apparatus
column13: The present invention relates to a pusher device, and more particularly, to a pusher device for pushing terminals of an inspection target device against an inspection device. The pusher device includes a housing including a pusher accommodating space, a valve accommodating space, an inflow path having, a discharge path, and a connection path; the valve structure being configured to selectively connect the connection path to one of the inflow path and the discharge path; and a pushing means being configured to be lowered by a pneumatic pressure and brought into contact with the inspection target device for pushing the inspection target device against the inspection device, wherein the valve structure and the pushing means are arranged in the housing.

column12: Low-resistance carbon grounding module and method for manufacturing the same
column13: The present invention provides a low-resistance carbon grounding module and a method for manufacturing the same, which can increase strength for durability against external environmental changes by varying the type and mixing ratio of raw materials for a carbon resistor without using any heat source. The low-resistance carbon grounding module comprises a carbon resistor extending in the longitudinal direction thereof and a conductive core bar installed in the center of the transverse section of the carbon resistor, wherein the carbon resistor comprises graphite, cement, and feldspar. Thus, it is possible to prevent the durability from being deteriorated due to external environmental changes, water, or electrical resistance, thus improving the quality and reliability of the product while minimizing the production of CO 2 .

column12: METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR TRANSMITTING MASK BITS
METHOD FOR MANUFACTURING TRANSISTOR OF SEMICONDUCTOR DEVICE
column13: A method for manufacturing a transistor in a semiconductor device is provided to prevent short channel effect and to reduce the length of a gate channel by shortening the length of a gate oxide layer. A gate oxide layer(18), a polysilicon layer(20), a metal film(22) and a hard mask layer(24) are sequentially deposited on a substrate(10) having a desired lower structure and patterned, thereby forming a gate pattern. Both ends of the gate oxide layer are obliquely etched. A first LDD(Lightly Doped Drain) region(28) is formed by tilt ion-implantation processing in the substrate of both sides of the gate pattern. A second LDD region(30) is then formed by tilt ion-implantation processing in the substrate of both sides of the gate pattern.

column12: HANDS FREE MIKE MOVING DEVICE
column13: A hands free mike moving device is provided to communicate on a phone with optimized quality and amount of a sound by moving a hands free mike back and forth by a medium of a driving motor. A hands free mike moving device includes a crash pad(1), a hands free unit(2), a seat location detector(3), a hands free mike moving unit(4), and a motor(5). The crash pad is located in front of a driver. The hands free unit is installed on the crash pad. The seat location detector is installed on a seat rail of a driver seat, detects the location of the driver seat, and is additionally connected to an input stage of the hands free unit. The motor is connected to an output stage of the hands free unit so that the motor is controlled according to a detection signal of the seat location detector.

column13: An apparatus for cooling a semiconductor device is provided to easily transfer the heat generated from a semiconductor device to a heat exchange part by making the heat exchange part come in contact with the upper surface of the semiconductor device even if the semiconductor device is tilted wherein the heat exchange part runs in parallel with the upper surface of the semiconductor device. A body part(10) can vertically transfer toward a semiconductor device placed on a test apparatus wherein the semiconductor device is electrically tested. A heat exchange part(30) comes in contact with the upper surface of the semiconductor device to absorb the heat generated from the semiconductor device, coupled to the body part. An elevation apparatus transfers the body part, coupled to the body part. The heat exchange part is coupled to the body part in a manner that the heat exchange part can rotate according to a tilt angle of one axial direction of the semiconductor device when the heat exchange part comes in contact with the semiconductor device. The rotation center of the heat exchange part can be positioned on the contact surface of the heat exchange part in contact with the semiconductor device.

column12: METHOD, APPARUTUS AND COMPUTER READABLE RECORDING MEDIUM FOR CREATING MIND-MAP WITH WEB-SCRAPING

column12: METHOD FOR ISSUING/COLLECTING/USING ACCUMULATED COUPONS USING SMS BETWEEN CUSTOMER AND INTERNET NETWORK SYSTEM
column13: PURPOSE: A method for issuing/collecting/using accumulated coupons using the SMS(Short Message Service) between a customer and an Internet network system is provided to remarkably enhance satisfaction of a customer and a seller by using a mobile phone number as a personal identification method, and increasing transparency as the accumulated coupon is issued through the SMS. CONSTITUTION: The customer requests issuance of the accumulated coupon by buying services and articles from the seller. The seller connects to the Internet system. The seller inputs the mobile phone number of the customer on the Internet system. The Internet system issues the accumulated coupon to a mobile phone through the SMS. The Internet system records accumulated coupon issuance information.

column12: LED TUNNEL LIGHTING
column13: The present invention relates to an LED tunnel lighting device. An SMPS box, installed in a plurality of LED modules and a case arranged on a cover, have waterproof property instead the waterproof and vibration absorption of a body of the LED tunnel lighting device. The LED tunnel lighting device implements the divergence of heat regardless of the number of LED modules and enables arrangement of LED modules based on the brightness of the light of the tunnel by the single body thereof since an aluminum plate, in which each LED module is installed and supported, forms air circulation hole for air circulation to the outside.

column13: To provide a linear guide with which lubricant never flows back in a lubricant channel of an end seal.SOLUTION: A linear guide comprises an end plate provided on the front and rear sides of a block arranged on a rail in a slidable manner, and an end seal inserted into the end plate. The end seal is formed with a lubricant channel which comprises a flow passage supplying lubricant between the rail and the block. The lubricant channel comprises a projection part formed so as to shield a part of the flow passage, and an elastic body insertion recess part formed on a side opposite to the projection part and into which a hollow elastic body is inserted. The elastic body contacts with the projection part, and closes the flow passage. When lubricant is injected into the lubricant channel, fixed pressure or more of lubricant injection force is applied, and then the elastic body is elastically deformed, so that the flow passage is opened.SELECTED DRAWING: Figure 12
