column12: SAFETY APPARATUS OF GRIPPER FOR A EXCAVATOR
column13: PURPOSE: A safety device for the gripper of an excavator is provided to stably and easily attach or detach a gripper to the arm of an excavator, and to prevent the movement of the gripper by adhering to one side of the arm. CONSTITUTION: A safety device(100) for the gripper of an excavator comprises a holding part(110), an elastic support part(120), a gripper tight fit part(130), and a gripper rotation restricting part(140). The holding part is joined to the gripper(30) through a base block(115) for firmly and easily joining to the gripper. The elastic support part is installed in the arm(10) of an excavator for elastically attaching to or detaching from the holding part. The gripper tight fit part is joined to the arm for tightly fitting the holding part to the elastic support part. The gripper rotation restricting part is formed in the arm and joined to the gripper tight fit part in order to completely restrict the rotation of the gripper.

column12: SPACING REGULATOR AND TILT TYPE ROTATIONAL QUICK COUPLER WITH IT
column13: An objective of the present invention is to provide a gap adjustment device and a tilt-type rotating quick coupler having the same, capable of extending a replacement cycle of a bearing. The gap adjustment device comprise: a main body installed on an arm of an excavator and provided with a connection rod and a connection plate; a power transfer unit which is rotatably installed on the connection plate, and transfers power by changing the propagation direction of the power; a tilt driving unit to supply power to the power transfer unit to rotate the power transfer unit in a tilting direction from the main body to one side or the other side; a rotating block rotatably installed on the power transfer unit and provided with a fixing hook to which an attachment is coupled; a rotation driving unit to supply power to the rotating block through the power transfer unit to rotate the rotating block from the power transfer unit; a wear prevention unit to prevent the power transfer unit and the rotating block from being worn; and a pressing member to press the wear prevention unit to tightly attach the wear prevention unit to the power transfer unit or the rotating block if the wear prevention unit is worn to widen the gap between the power transfer unit and the rotating block.

column12: APPARATUS FOR CONTROLLING AUTOMOTIVE HORN
column13: An apparatus for controlling an automotive horn is provided to prevent a contact operation failure of a horn due to foreign material. An automotive horn control device(300) includes a coil power supply unit(310) and a power supply control unit(320). The coil power feeder is connected to one end of a coil wound around a core. The coil power supply unit supplies the power. The power supply controller performs a switching operation when the power is applied. The power supply controller controls the current flow of the power supply controller. The power supply controller includes a light emitting unit(321), a light receiving unit(322), and a vibrator(325). The light emitting unit emits the light when the power is applied. The light receiving unit measures the light generated in the light emitting unit. The light receiving unit controls the current flowing on the coil by changing the resistance according to an amount of the light. The vibrator moves up and down by a spring according to the magnetization of the coil. The vibrator blocks the flow of the light generated in the light emitting unit.

column12: Pallet type parking facility using the weight center
column13: The present invention relates to a pallet-type parking facility using a center of gravity. The pallet-type parking facility using the center of the gravity of the present invention consists of a conveying device, which balances horizontally while a weight body moves horizontally in the opposite direction to the moving direction of a bogie so that an elevator does not become unbalanced when the bogie moves forward or backward in the elevator. Therefore, horizontal imbalance caused by a bias of the elevator is eliminated to prevent wire cut accidents and bogie fall accidents in advance, and height deviation between a floor of a multi-stories parking lot and the bogie is eliminated so that it is possible to induce easy vehicle entry into a parking space.

column12: Washing machine detecting condensed water temperature and drying control method of the same
column13: Disclosed herein are a washing machine with a drying unit (40) and a drying control method of the same that is capable of controlling a drying time based on a temperature of condensed water used during a drying operation to accomplish optimum drying efficiency. The drying control method includes detecting the temperature of condensed water supplied during drying the laundry, setting the drying time based on the detected temperature of the condensed water, and operating the drying unit according to the set drying time to perform a drying operation.

column12: Camera module test jig
column13: A camera module test jig comprises: a base plate provided with a camera module mounting unit; a cylinder support base provided between the base plate and a cylinder that drives a roller module to move forward and backward for supporting the cylinder; a jig cover, which covers the camera module mounting unit and closes the same via the roller module which partially moves forward in response to a single stroke of the cylinder; a base coupled to the jig cover through a hinge and comprising a tapered hinge unit; and a roller module which moves forward in response to a single stroke of the cylinder, while enabling the jig cover to cover the camera module mounting unit and makes it closed, wherein the tapered hinge unit may move forward with the remaining stroke of the cylinder for pushing down the base. This invention can achieve vertical connector on a pushdown clamshell type jig cover to make it subjected to a contact force perpendicularly, so as to avoid damages of the spring thimble. As a result, it is possible to reduce the impact applied to the spring thimble, prolong the service life of the spring thimble, thereby obtaining economic benefits of reduced maintenance fees and workforce management fees.

column12: PROBE MEMBER FOR POGO PIN THE METHOD OF MANUFACTURING THE SAME POGO PIN COMPRISING THE SAME
column13: The present invention relates to a probe member for a pogo pin, a manufacturing method thereof, and a pogo pin including the same. One embodiment of the present invention comprises: one or more contact parts having one end formed sharply and coming in contact with an object to be inspected; a first body part having one end coupled to the other end of the contact part and having a polygonal or circular pillar shape; and a second body part having one end coupled to the other end of the first body part and having a polygonal or circular pillar shape. The contact part is made of a material having a hardness higher than those of the first body part and the second body part. The first body part and the second body part are made of a material having electrical conductivity of 50% international annealed copper standard (IACS) or greater. At least a portion thereof is inserted into a pipe having an inner space formed therein. Thus, the probe member is used for a test socket.

column12: METHOD FOR MANUFACTURING TRANSISTOR OF SEMICONDUCTOR DEVICE
column13: A method for manufacturing a transistor in a semiconductor device is provided to control easily the Vt of the transistor and to maximize an ion implantation effect by forming a dual polysilicon structure in a substrate. A channel Vt controlling ion implantation and a field stop ion implantation are performed on a semiconductor substrate(110) with a lower structure. A gate region etching process is performed on the substrate. A gate oxide layer(160) is filled therein. Two trenches spaced apart from each other are formed at a center portion of the gate oxide layer. A polysilicon layer(170) and a gate metal are sequentially deposited on the resultant structure including the two trenches. A gate pattern is formed by performing an etching process on the resultant structure. A halo ion implantation is performed on a junction region of the resultant structure. A spacer made of an insulating layer is formed at both sidewalls of the gate pattern. Source/drain regions(210) are formed in the substrate by an ion implantation.

column12: NON-VOLATILE MEMORY CELL AND ARRAY CIRCUIT
column13: PURPOSE: A non-volatile memory cell and an array circuit are provided to store data according to the minute change of a threshold voltage due to an artificial channel stress. CONSTITUTION: A memory cell(110) includes two n-type metal oxide semiconductor(NMOS) transistors(MN10, MN20) in connection with a common node(LEN). The drain terminal(BL) of one NMOS transistor is in connection with the gate terminal of the other NMOS transistor. The gate terminal of one NMOS transistor is in connection with the gate terminal of the other NMOS transistor. A reading-writing circuit(120) includes two p-type MOS(PMOS) transistors(MP10, MP20) in connection with a common node(LEP). The drain terminal of one PMOS transistor is in connection with the gate terminal of the other PMOS transistor.

column12: Gap adjustment device for rotary quick coupler
column13: Provided is a gap-adjusting device for a rotary quick coupler. The gap-adjusting device for a rotary quick coupler comprises: a main body connected to arms of heavy equipment and having a connection plate; a rotary block having a rotation plate disposed opposite to the connection plate, rotatably connected to the connection plate by a hydraulic connection unit, and having an attachment detachably connected thereto; a driving unit provided between the connection plate and the rotation plate to provide power for rotating the rotary block in a forward or reverse direction from the main body; a pressure member installed in the driving unit to be able to move forward or backward from the connection plate toward the driving unit; and an operating member connected to the pressure member and exposed to the outside of the main body through the connecting plate to provide an operating force for moving the pressure member forward or backward. When a gap is made between the main body and the rotary block due to long-term operation, the gap-adjusting device according to the present invention can resolve the gap by a simple operation without disassembling the main body and the rotary block.

column12: System and method for detecting defects in a thin-film-transistor array
column13: A system and method for detecting a defect in a transistor array includes applying a test signal to the array, monitoring pixel voltage along a gate line of the array, and detecting a defect associated with the gate line based on a variation in the pixel voltage during the monitoring step. The defect may be a short between the gate line and a common line of the array. The gate line and common line may be associated with a same pixel element or different pixel elements. The system and method also detect a precise location of the defect based on a rate of change in the variation of the pixel voltage along the gate line. The rate of change may be measured in any one of a variety of ways. For example, the rate of change may be measured as a sudden increase or increase of the pixel voltage or as a change in slope of a pixel voltage profile. Alternatively, the location of the defect may be detected as corresponding to a minimum or maximum value in a pixel voltage profile. The transistor array may be a TFT array or another circuit which includes an array of transistors.

column12: FOOD COMPOSITION EFFECTIVE AGAINST DISEASES CAUSED BY THE DAMAGED NERVE CELLS
column13: A food composition effective for disease caused by neuronal damage containing wave hexagonal water extract of buckwheat and glucose is provided to recover deformed and damaged nerve cells of patients with disease caused by neuronal damage. A food composition effective for disease caused by neuronal damage contains wave hexagonal water extract of buckwheat and glucose. The wave hexagonal water extract of buckwheat is obtained by mixing wave hexagonal water(Reminda) and buckwheat, buckwheat leaf or a mixture of buckwheat and buckwheat leaf in a volume ratio of 15:1 to 5:1 and heating for 5 to 15hr. Acanthopanax senticosus can be added to the wave hexagonal water.

column12: Card storage mobile phone case
column13: The present disclosure relates to a card storage mobile phone case including: a case main body including a front surface, on which a mobile phone storing part, in which attachment/detachment of a mobile phone is performed in a form of surrounding a rear surface and side surfaces of the mobile phone, is formed, and a rear surface which is provided with a card mounting part having a card mounting surface, and including a hinge structure in a lower portion of the rear surface; a main body cover fitted and coupled to the rear surface of the case main body in a state of surrounding the rear surface of the case main body, and including a card string region in which a bottom part of a front surface the main body cover is spaced a predetermined distance apart from a card mounting surface of the card mounding part of the case main body so as to store a card, and an opening which is provided on a lower portion of the main body cover and through which the card is stored and taken out; and an opening/closing cover including a hinge coupling part coupled to the hinge structure with the main body cover therebetween, and configured to open/close the opening.

column12: Folded cascode operational amplifier having improved phase margin
column13: A folded cascode operational amplifier having an improved phase margin due to pole-zero cancellation by using a plurality of cascode-connected bias circuits and frequency compensation capacitors.

column12: Waveform generation circuit
column13: A waveform generation circuit includes: a waveform generation block configured to generate a waveform signal corresponding to a driving control signal; and a control signal generation block configured to generate a driving control signal for compensating the waveform signal for an environmental factor reflected into the waveform generation circuit.

column12: anisotropic conductive sheet
column13: The present invention relates to an anisotropic conductive sheet and conductive powder. More specifically, the anisotropic conductive sheet is arranged between a device to be tested and a test device to electrically connect a terminal of the device to be tested and a pad of the test device to each other, and comprises: a conduction passage forming unit which is arranged on each position corresponding to the terminal of the device to be tested, indicates conductivity in a thickness direction, and has conductive powder arranged in an elastic insulation material in the thickness direction; and an insulation unit to support and insulate the conduction passage forming units. The conductive powder is formed in a mesh structure of a three dimensional net shape, and a plurality of gas holes connecting the inside and the outside are disposed in the conductive powder. The elastic insulation material composing the conduction passage forming unit fills the gas holes of the conductive powder and is integratively connected to the outside of the conductive powder.

column12: Semi open cut type tunnel construction method at low overburden
column13: The present invention provides a shallow semi-excavation tunnel construction method with improved constructability and work safety. According to the present invention, the shallow semi-excavation tunnel construction method with improved constructability and work safety comprises: a first step of cutting the bottom surface (10B) of an upper excavation line (10) up to a stable ground layer, and forming a plurality of pairs of holes (20) facing each other with respect to the center line on both sides of the bottom surface (10B) of the upper excavation line (10) in the longitudinal direction of a tunnel formed by semi-excavation construction in a shallow section; a second step in which a support unit (32a) of a first steel rib member (30a) formed in a semi-arch shape is inserted into the hole (20, 20a) on one side formed on the bottom surface (10B) of the upper excavation line (10) to be partially supported on the hole (20); a third step in which a support unit (32b) of a second steel rib member (30b) formed in a semi-arch shape is inserted into the hole (20, 20b) on the other side formed on the bottom surface (10B) of the upper excavation line (10) to be partially supported on the hole (20); and a fourth step in which a first flange unit (34a) formed on the semi-arch end of the first steel rib member (30a) and a second flange unit (34b) formed on the semi-arch end of the second steel rib member (30b) are faced and coupled to each other by a fastening member.

column12: Pogo pin, the fabrication method thereof and test socket using the same
column13: Disclosed is a pogo pin including: a hollow body having a spring structure by spirally cutting at least a portion of an outer surface thereof; and a conductive material filling at least an inside of the body. According to the present invention, when testing a semiconductor package, error rate in contact between the package, the pogo pin and a test board can be remarkably reduced, and simultaneously can enhance rigidity and electrical conductivity of the pogo pin. Further, simple componentry of the pogo pin can facilitate its fabrication, reduce fabrication costs, and even foresee fabrication of a micro-pogo pin.

column12: A METHOD FOR SEARCHING/ACCESSING A CHANNEL AND A DIGITAL BROADCASTING RECEIVER
column13: PURPOSE: A channel searching/accessing method a digital broadcasting receiver is provided to supply convenience of searching/accessing to a destination channel by using the concept of anchor information is a plurality of channel exists. CONSTITUTION: Information about at least one anchor channel is stored(S901). A first key input about the channel conversion is received(S902). Information which is the nearest with a current channel form information about an anchor channel according to the first key input is collected(S905). Information about the collected anchor channel is outputted.

column12: Technique for reducing read channel optimization time
column13: A hard disk drive with a reduced read channel optimization test time and a reduced test time difference determines whether or not the time limit for testing the hard disk drive has elapsed whenever the test by the zones and heads is completed, so that the test time difference between the respective drives may be prevented. Further, the test progresses from the last zone to the first zone. Thus, although the test is halted in the course of performing the test, the zone with the high error rate can be tested. In addition, a determination is made as to whether or not the error rate is high or not at the steps of selecting the test track and determining the test off-track. If it is determined that the error rate is high, the total number of sectors to be read for the test will be adjusted, thereby reducing the test time delay due to the high error rate.

column12: SOLID TYPE-SNOW REMOVAL AGENT BASED ON ORGANIC ACID
column13: The present invention relates to a solid organic acid-based snow removal agent that solves problems of environmental damage such as water pollution caused by excessive use of chloride-based snow removal agents, has excellent quick-acting properties and durability to facilitate ensured snow removal and ice melting, and contains eco-friendly compositions to promote soil-improving and snow-melting effects. The present invention provides solid organic acid-based snow removal agent including magnesium chloride hexahydrate (MgCl_2.6H_2O), sodium chloride (NaCl), a corrosion inhibitory material, a hazardous decomposition material, and shell powder, wherein each of the magnesium chloride hexahydrate (MgCl_2.6H_2O), sodium chloride (NaCl), a corrosion inhibitory material, a hazardous decomposition material, and shell powder is in the form of granules.

Anisotropic sheet comprising conductive particles mixed different kind of particles
column13: An embodiment provides an anisotropic conductive sheet for electrically connecting a terminal of a device to be tested and a pad of a testing device, the sheet comprising a plurality of conductive portions which are formed in a thickness direction inside an insulating support portion and comprise multiple conductive particles, wherein the conductive particles are implemented by mixed particles including a highly-conductive metal and magnetic particles.

column12: Lightning arrester
column13: Provided is a lightning arrester capable of previously discharging charges charged depending on an approach of lightning before the lightning occurs, thereby preventing the lightning. The lightning arrester includes: a conductive rod installed at an upper part of an object to be protected from lightning and connected to a ground part; an insulator coupled with one end of the rod; a charge pipe having a cylindrical shape with pin-shaped projections extending inward therefrom and in which space charges are charged; and a charge rod inserted into the charge pipe and connected in the middle of the rod.

column12: AUTOMATIC TAILGATE LOCKING DEVICE
column13: PURPOSE: A automatic opening and shutting device of a side door of a trunk is provided to automatically open and shut a side door by using an air compressor, so the safety of workers and reduction of working time is achieved. CONSTITUTION: A power permitting device of a selecting switch part(2) permits the power when a side door(10) is opened and shut in order to supply the air contained in an air reservoir(9) by an air compressor(8). A front/rear connector of a front/rear side selecting valve(3) selects the front and the rear of the side door by connecting selectively the first(18) and the second pipe(19). A rear door connecting device of a rear operating valve(4) selects a rear door(16) connecting the third pipe(24) by the selecting switch part. A left/right connecting device of a left/right selecting valve(5) selects and opens/shuts the left and the right of the front/rear side door. A driving device of an actuator member(6) is operated by the air pressure through the left/right side pipe, and opens and shuts the side door and a rear door by winding or unwinding a wire(31).

column12: TENT RACK FOR RECREATION VEHICLE
SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR E-LEARNING AND EVALUATION USING RADIANT OR TREE STRUCTURE MAPPING
column13: PURPOSE: A system for the cyber education configuring an answer as a radial or tree structured shape and an evaluation method thereof are provided to effectively evaluate the understanding of the user's learning by presenting a problem having the radial and tree structure to a user. CONSTITUTION: The method comprises the steps of receiving a plurality of user's answers for each problem(S2005), extracting a plurality of subordinate problems matching to a selection problem of the plural answers from a radial or tree structured problem table, and judging that respective subordinate selection problems are matched to the respective subordinate problems. If the judgment is matched, a point corresponding to the problem is stored in the radial or tree structured answer table(S2019). The point is given to the user as the point for the radial or tree structured problem by summing up the respective points of the plural problems.

column12: ADVERTIZING DEVICE TO USE THE LCD OF TELEPHONE
PAINTING LAYER STRUCTURE FOR PREVENTING CHIPPING AND METHOD FOR MANUFACTURING THE SAME
Test socket
column13: The present invention relates to a socket for inspection, and more particularly, to a socket for inspection comprising an anisotropically conductive sheet in which a plurality of conductive portions extending in the thickness direction are arranged in an insulated state from each other by an insulating portion. The anisotropically conductive sheet includes: an insulating portion having through holes formed at positions corresponding to a terminal of a device to be tested, and insulating conductive portions disposed in the through holes from each other; an intermediate sheet body comprising a support sheet provided in the middle of a surface and a rear surface of the anisotropically conductive sheet, and an electrode portion supported by the support sheet and inserted into the through hole to form a conductive path; and an elastic portion supporting the electrode portion inserted into the through hole in the insulating portion, wherein an insulating sheet is attached on an upper surface of the anisotropically conductive sheet.

column12: Lightning arrester
column13: Provided is a lighting arrester capable of preventing damage caused by a lightning by discharging charges charged by approach of a thundercloud. The lightning arrester includes: a conductive rod installed at an upper part of an object to be protected from a lightning and connected to a ground part; a charge pipe having a cylindrical shape, formed of an insulating body to be insulated from the rod, and electrically charged with charges having a polarity opposite to ground charges; and a plurality of charge pins disposed on the charge pipe such that space charges in the air are charged to the pins by a thundercloud.

column12: CONNECTOR FOR ELECTRICAL CONNECTION
column13: Provided is a connector for electrical connection, which is arranged between an inspection device and a device under test. The connector includes a signal conductive unit, a ground conductive unit, and a metal frame unit. The signal conductive unit includes a transmission unit and an insulation unit. The transmission unit includes a plurality of first conductive particles that are electrically connected in a vertical direction. The insulation unit is integrally formed with the transmission unit so as to surround the transmission unit in a horizontal direction perpendicular to the vertical direction, and has a thickness in a horizontal direction greater than the maximum width of the transmission unit in the horizontal direction. The ground conductive unit is spaced apart from the signal conductive unit in the horizontal direction. The metal frame unit maintains the signal conductive unit and the ground conductive unit in the vertical direction, spaces the signal conductive unit and the ground conductive unit to be apart from each other in the horizontal direction, and is electrically connected to the ground conductive unit.

column12: EAR RING
column13: 본 고안은 귀를 뚫지 않고 착용하는 귀걸이에 관한 것으로서, 보다 구체적으로는, 쉽게 끌러지면서도 착용시에는 알맞는 밀착력으로 착용할 수 있는 귀걸이에 관한 것이다. 상기 목적을 달성하기 위한 본 고안의 귀걸이는, 서로 결합되면 완전한 하나의 귀걸이를 구성하게 되는 2개의 호형 귀걸이체(1,1a)에, 예컨대 왼쪽 귀걸이체(1)의 한쪽 단부에는 안쪽으로 들어 갈수록 폭이 넓어지도록 끼움 홈부(2)를 테이퍼 가공하여 양측의 두께부분(11,11a)에 구멍(4)을 뚫고, 또한 이와 대응되는 오른쪽 귀걸이체(1a)의 한쪽 단부에는 안쪽으로 갈수록 두께가 두꺼워지도록 끼움 돌기부(3)를 테이퍼 가공하여 그 중앙부분에 핀(5)을 꽂을 수 있는 구멍(4)을 뚫음과 동시에 이 구멍에 인접하여 반구형으로 움푹 들어간 베어링 홈(7)을 엠보싱한 후, 이 끼움 돌기부(3)의 양측 베어링 홈(7)에 각각 미세한 볼 베어링(6)을 위치시켜, 상기 끼움 홈부(2)에 끼움 돌기부(3)와 함께 헐거운 끼워맞춤을 하고, 이 상태에서 상기 구멍(4)들을 관통하는 핀(5)을 꽂아 그 양단을 리벳팅하여 구성된다.

column12: LIGHTNING ARRESTER SYSTEM EMPLOYING THE DOUBLE-TRIANGLE METHOD
column13: A lightening arrest system adopting a double triangle method is provided to reduce inflow probability of direct strokes by preventing electric filed from being concentrated on an edge of a building when a thundercloud approaches. A plurality of arresters(2) are installed in a building. A ground unit(3) for the equipotential of a mesh type is laid in the bottom of the building. A conductor(4) of low surge impedance connects the arrest and the ground unit for the equipotential. A surge protector(8) prevents the indirect strokes to the electronic device installed at the building. A ground module is connected to at least one of an apex or an intersecting point of the ground unit for the equipotential and discharges the surge current passing through the ground unit for the equipotential to the ground. A plurality of arrests are dipole electric static induction arresters.

column12: Class AB amplifier having adjustable quiescent current and output current
column13: A class AB amplifier capable of easily controlling the amount of quiescent current and the amount of amplifier output current. The amplifier includes an input circuit that transform a voltage difference between input signals into a current; a current mirror including the (the Pull Up and Pull Down transistors of the) output circuit of the amplifier controls the quiescent current through the Pull Up and Pull Down transistors output circuit; and a control circuit in the current mirror (to which a first control voltage and a second control voltage are applied), adjusts the amount of quiescent current flowing through the output circuit in a first operating mode (by controlling a first bias current that is proportionate to the quiescent current in the current mirror), and controls the amount of the output current sourced or sinked (in response to the change in the voltages at the first and second output nodes of the input circuit) in a second operating mode. The first and second control voltages are DC voltages supplied from the outside of the class AB amplifier, and the amount of first bias current is determined by the first control voltage. The amounts of quiescent current and output current can be easily controlled.

column12: TEST CONNECTOR AND MANUFACTURING METHOD OF THE TEST CONNECTOR
column13: According to an embodiment of the present invention, provided is a connector for inspection which is disposed between a device under test and test equipment to electrically connect the device under test with the test equipment. The connector for inspection comprises: a sheet formed by mixing silicone rubber and an iron oxide; and a conductive portion extending in a vertical direction in the sheet to enable conductivity in the vertical direction.

column12: Test contactor
column13: The present invention relates to a test contactor with enhanced durability. More specifically, the test contactor is disposed between a tested device and a tester to electrically connect a terminal of the tested device and a pad of the tester. The test contactor comprises: a housing having an upper hole formed at a position corresponding to the terminal of the tested device, having a lower hole formed at a position corresponding to the pad of the tester, and having a reception space formed between the upper and lower holes; an upper pin partially protruding through the upper hole, coming in contact with the terminal of the tested device, and moved in a vertical direction; a lower pin partially protruding through the lower hole, coming in contact with the pad of the tester, and disposed on the direct lower side of the upper pin; a contact means extended in the lateral direction of the upper pin to be connected to the lower pin and including an elastic part elastically biasing the upper pin in a direction distant from the lower pin; and an elastic sheet body disposed between the upper and lower pins and elastically supporting the upper pin pressed by the tested device to move to a lower side. The contact means and the elastic sheet body are disposed in the reception space of the housing.

column12: VERTICAL SEMICONDUCTOR DEVICE AND MANUFACTURING METHOD OF THE SAME
column13: PURPOSE: A vertical type semiconductor device and a method of manufacturing thereof are provided to be applied to a circuit structure needing different performance characteristics by forming the thickness of the gate oxidation film of two transistors to be different. CONSTITUTION: In a vertical type semiconductor device and a method of manufacturing thereof, a common source region(108) is arranged in an active region(110) and the silicon substrate in the lower part of an element isolation film. A gate(G) is formed to be overlapped with the common source area. Gate oxidation films(116a,116b) are respectively formed between the gate and the active region in both sides of the gate. A drain region(126) is formed on the active area of both side of the gate. A LDD(Lightly Doped Drain) domain(114) is formed between the gate oxidation film and the common source area.

column12: METHOD FOR GENERATING LINEAR TEST PATTERN IN PAGE PRINTER
column13: The linearity test pattern generating circuit includes an up-down counter and a counter. A buffer circuit (120) connecting between the up-down counter and the counter supplies the buffed output of the up-down counter to the counter. An inverter circuit (121) supplies the inverted output of the up-down counter to the counter. A counter control means controls the adding counter operation of the up-down counter by inverting the output logic according to the carry signal of the up-down counter. And a print data position control means switches the operation of the buffer and the inverter circuits to control the outputs of them.

column12: DATA PROCESSING METHOD AND DEVICE FOR ENTROPY ENHANCEMENT
column13: Disclosed is a data processing method for entropy enhancement. According to the present invention, a data processing method for entropy enhancement includes the steps of: generating a plurality of blocks of non-uniform length by dynamically dividing data to be transmitted; generating a verification code by performing an XOR operation on the plurality of blocks; and generating encrypted data by concatenating the reinforcement data including the plurality of blocks and the verification code, and transmitting the encrypted data. Therefore, data can be protected from various predictive attacks.

column13: 초고강도 강판용 가열장치 및 이를 이용한 초고강도 강판의 성형방법에 대한 발명이 개시된다. 본 발명의 초고강도 강판용 가열장치는: 초고강도 강판을 향하여 레이저를 조사하며 초고강도 강판을 국부 가열시키는 빔가열부 및 빔가열부에서 발생된 레이저가 초고강도 강판의 설정구역에 조사되도록 레이저의 이동을 안내하며 초고강도 강판에 마주하는 상태로 설치되는 가이드부를 포함하는 것을 특징으로 한다.

column12: Clothing dryer
column13: A clothing dryer including a rotating drum, a shelf installed inside the rotating drum, and a support member, which is rotatably installed at a rear end of the shelf such that the shelf is supported by a rear surface of the rotating drum. The rear end of the shelf is installed on a rear surface of the rotating drum through the support member, so that the shelf is more stably installed inside the rotating drum.

column12: BIPOLAR LIGHTNING ARRESTOR
column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a bipolar lightning arrestor capable of increasing discharge efficiency for a lightning current of the falling of a thunderbolt and also capable of preventing the coupling and fixation power of the bipolar lightning arrestor from becoming weak due to vibration attributable to external environment factors, such as an earthquake or a typhoon.SOLUTION: A bipolar lightning arrestor includes: a fixation plate; a rod member configured to have one end connected to the fixation plate in a longitudinal direction thereof and charged with the electric charges of a ground; at least two or more insulators installed along a longitudinal direction of the rod member; an electrification plate installed between adjacent insulators, electrically insulated from the rod member, and charged with electric charges having an opposite polarity to the electric charges of a ground; an electrification tube installed between the electrification plate and the insulators, electrically connected to the electrification plate, and charged with electric charges having an opposite polarity to the electric charges of a ground; and a rod cap connected to the top end of the rod member and configured to induce the falling of a thunderbolt. The rod cap is configured to have an outer diameter relatively greater than that of the insulators so that discharge efficiency can be increased by greatly increasing an area into which the falling of a thunderbolt is induced.

column12: SUPERCOOLING SYSTEM
column13: The present invention relates to a supercooling system and a method for displaying a supercooled state which can accurately display a supercooled state of a stored object in spite of the external influence. The supercooling system includes a cooling apparatus including a storing unit storing a stored object, a cooling means cooling the storing unit, and a main control unit receiving external commercial power and controlling the cooling means to maintain the temperature in the storing unit at a temperature below at least the maximum ice crystal formation zone, and a supercooling apparatus (200) including an independent storage room having a storing space therein to store an object and mounted and cooled in the storing unit, a temperature sensing unit (220) sensing the temperature of the independent storage room, a temperature control means mounted in the independent storage room and controlling the internal temperature, a display unit (240) displaying the state of the current control, and a sub-control unit (280) controlling the temperature control means based on the sensed temperature from the temperature sensing unit (220) to store the object received in the independent storage room in a supercooled state, and displaying the state of the stored object on the display unit (240) with the proceeding of the cooling of the stored object or the storing space.

column12: Circuit and method for driving a liquid crystal display device using low power
column13: Provided are a circuit and method for driving a liquid crystal display device using low power. The circuit includes a display data latch, a gamma decoder, and a driver cell circuit. The display data latch latches display from a memory. The gamma decoder receives a plurality of gray scale voltages, and selects and outputs one of the plurality of gray scale voltages in response to the display data. The driver cell circuit receives an output voltage of the gamma decoder and generates an output voltage applied to the liquid crystal display device. The driver cell circuit controls a slew rate in response to comparison result of current data and previous data of the display data. The driver cell circuit includes a previous data latch, a bias control voltage generator, and a driver amplifier. The previous data latch receives a portion or the whole of the display data and outputs the portion or the whole of the display data as the previous data. The bias control voltage generator compares the current data and the previous data of the display and generates a control signal. The driver amplifier receives the output voltage of the gamma decoder, generates the output voltage applied to the liquid crystal display device, and controls the slew rate in response to the control signal.

column12: Terminais de ar de raio de dissipação de descarga bipolares
column13: "TERMINAIS DE AR DE RAIO DE DISSIPAçãO DE DESCARGA BIPOLARES". A presente invenção refere-se a Terminais de Ar de Raio de Dissipação de Descarga Bipolares, e um objetivo da presente invenção é dispersar e descarregar uma carga carregada de terra após a aproximação de uma nuvem de tempestade em um espaço de acordo com um princípio de dipólo elétrico, bipolar e camada dupla elétrica. O objetivo acima da presente invenção é conseguido provendo os terminais de ar de raio de dissipação de descarga bipolares que compreendem: um membro de base fixo e instalado em uma região superior de um objeto protegido, que inclui uma projeção de acoplamento sobre cuja superfície periférica interna de ranhuras de rosca de acoplamento são formadas, a projeção de acoplamento projetada e formada em um lado de uma superfície superior do membro de base, e uma peça de aterramento formada em um lado oposto à projeção de acoplamento de modo a aterrar um eletrodo de terra e um fio de raio aterrado; um membro de descarga acoplado liberável no membro de base, para focalizar uma carga de terra após uma aproximação de nuvem de tempestade na superfície superior do membro de base; e uma unidade de modificação de potencial presa liberável no membro de descarga de modo que a unidade de modificação de potencial é carregada com diferentes cargas por princípio elétrico dipólo, bipolar e camada dupla elétrica de acordo com a aproximação da nuvem de tempestade para dispersar e descarregar a carga de terra em um espaço separado do membro de descarga.

column12: CAMERA LENS MODULE TEST SOCKET
column13: The present invention relates to a camera lens module test socket configured of: a base plate installed on a printed circuit board connected to an inspection device; a lens module seating portion installed on the base plate and having an image sensor installed thereon for detecting a test image acquired through a camera lens module; 3 pogo blocks making a connection at 3 surfaces of the camera lens module seated in the lens module seating portion; a cam plate connecting a first and a second pogo block at both sides from among the 3 pogo blocks to both side surface terminals of the camera lens module, and connecting the center pogo block to a rear surface terminal of the camera lens module; and a pneumatic cylinder for moving the cam plate forward and backward so as to connect the three pogo blocks at the 3 surfaces of the camera lens module, etc., wherein the lifespan of pogo pins can be improved through a linear connection between the camera lens module and the pogo blocks, inspection speed can be improved by a simple structure, the minimization of components can reduce weight and costs, and production costs can be reduced through the reduction of production manpower due to the minimization of assembly processes.

column12: modulo de aterramento de carbono de baixa resistencia e metodo para fabricacao do mesmo
column13: MàDULO DE ATERRAMENTO DE CARBONO DE BAIXA RESISTÊNCIA E MÉTODO PARA FABRICAÇçO DO MESMO. A presente invenção refere-se aum módulo de aterramento de carbono de baixa resistência e um método para fabricação do mesmo, o qual pode aumentar a resistência para durabilidade contra mudanças ambientais externas através da variação do tipo e razão de mistura de matérias-primas para um resistor de carbono sem usar qualquer fonte de calor. O módulo de aterramento de carbono de baixa resistência compreende um resitor de carbono se estendendo na sua direção longitudinal e uma barra de núcleo condutora instalada no centro da seção transversal do resitor de carbono, onde o resitor de carbono compreende grafite, cimento e feldspato. Desta maneira, é possível prevenir a durabilidade de ser deteriorada devido a mudanças ambientais externas, água ou resistência elétrica, deta maneira aperfeiçoamento a qualidade e a confiabilidade do produto enquanto minimizando a produção de CO2.

column12: ONE-TOUCH FOLDING MAKESHIFT BATHTUB

The disclosed one-touch folding makeshift bathtub comprises: a bathtub sheet portion made of a soft waterproof fabric and configured in the shape of a quadrangular bathtub having an open upper portion, thereby providing a space therein for containing bath water; and a water-pressure support frame portion installed to surround the periphery of the bathtub sheet portion and configured to support water pressure of bath water contained in the bathtub sheet portion, the water-pressure support frame portion comprising a front plate portion forced against a front sheet of the bathtub sheet portion, a rear plate portion forced against a rear sheet of the bathtub sheet portion, and a pair of side plate portions for connecting both sides of the front plate portion and the rear plate portion, the side plate portions having front and rear ends rotatably configured on the front and rear plate portions, respectively, each side plate portion comprising multiple side plates such that same can be folded or unfolded in a zigzag with regard to each other. If the front plate portion moves away from the rear plate portion, the multiple side plates are unfolded, and the bath sheet portion is unfolded, thereby making the bath sheet portion ready to use such that bath water can be contained therein. If the front and rear plate portions are moved toward each other, the front plate portion, the multiple side plates, and the rear plate portion are folded in a zigzag, and the bath sheet portion is folded and is ready to be stored.

column12: Bipolar discharge-dissipation lightning air terminals
column13: The present invention relates to a Bipolar Discharge-Dissipation Lightning Air-Terminals, and an object of the present invention is to disperse and discharge an earth charge following a thundercloud approach in a space according to electric dipole, bipolar and electric double layer principle. The above object of the present invention is achieved by providing the bipolar discharge-dissipation lightning air-terminals comprising: a base member fixed and installed in a top region of a protected object, including a coupling projection on whose inner periphery surface coupling screw grooves are formed, the coupling projection protruded and formed at a side of an upper surface of the base member, and a grounding piece formed at a side opposite to the coupling projection in order to earth a ground electrode and a grounded lightning wire; a discharge member coupled releasably to the base member, for focusing an earth charge following a thundercloud approach on the upper surface of the base member; and a potential modifying unit attached releasably on the discharge member so that the potential modifying unit is charged with different charges by electric dipole, bipolar and electric double layer principle according to the thundercloud approach to disperse and discharge the earth charge in a space separated from the discharge member.

column12: digital to analog converter, delay-locked loop, memory device and counting method
column13: A digital to analog converter (DAC) can comprise: an escalator code generator; and an escalator-code-to-analog converter (ECAC). The generator can (1) represent base 10 numbers with a mixed code having a coin code portion and a cash code portion, which will eliminate multi-bit changes in the cash code upon changes in count direction; and (2) represent a count in a first direction as the sum of the coin code and the cash code. The generator can alter the coin code when the count changes direction while the cash code remains the same until a count capacity of the coin code is exceeded, at which point the cash code can be altered. Cycling between adjacent base 10 numbers is absorbed by the coin code while keeping the cash code the same, which reduces noise introduced into an output of the ECAC due to such cycling.

column12: A method for preparing extract for the prevention and treatment of hyperlipidemia and obesity from the extract of aster spathulifolius aerial part and composition containing the same
column13: The present invention relates to a method for preparing an extract of the aerial part of Aster spathulifolius effective in preventing and treating hyperlipidemia and obesity and a composition comprising the extract. Since most of salt which is originally abundant in Aster spathulifolius, phenolic compounds which are unstable and susceptible to oxidation, and mucous substances are simply removed by the preparation method in accordance with the present invention, the present invention can significantly increase the content of terpenes, or the active ingredient, and reduce production cost. The composition of the present invention can be used as functional food for aiding the prevention and treatment of hyperlipidemia- and obesity-related arteriosclerosis, cardiovascular disease, cerebral thrombosis, liver disease, thrombosis, diabetes, etc.

column12: A METHOD FOR PREPARING EXTRACT FOR THE PREVENTION AND TREATMENT OF HYPERLIPIDEMIA AND OBESITY FROM THE EXTRACT OF ASTER SPATHULIFOLIUS AERIAL PART AND COMPOSITION CONTAINING THE SAME
SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR CLASSIFYING DEFECTS IN AND IDENTIFYING PROCESS PROBLEMS FOR AN ELECTRICAL CIRCUIT
column13: A method for performing circuit defect analysis and process problem identification includes applying a test signal to a circuit, obtaining a signal generated in response to the test signal, comparing the response signal to reference information, classifying a defect in the circuit based on a result of the comparing step, and identifying a problem in a manufacturing process which caused the defect based on the classification. The reference information may include one or more signal profiles corresponding to predefined types of defects that can occur during the manufacturing process. Defect classification is preferably performed by determining whether the response signal falls within one or more of the signal profiles. If the response signal falls within two or more signal profiles, then probabilities may be determined for each profile. The defect may then be classified as corresponding to the defect type whose signal profile has the highest probability. A processing system performs defect classification and process problem identification using a similar approach.

column12: Test socket for use in testing tested device
column13: Provided is a test socket electrically connecting a device to be tested, having a plurality of terminals, to an test board of the test device. The test socket comprises a plurality of pins, a pin support, an elastic conductive sheet, a housing, a pusher, and a latch device. The pins are connected to the test board. The pin support is placed on the test board and maintains the plurality of pins inthe vertical alignment. The elastic conductive sheet is detachably mounted on an upper portion of the pin support and the device to be tested is mounted on the elastic conductive sheet. The elastic conductive sheet includes a plurality of elastic conductive portions which are in contact with the plurality of terminals and the plurality of pins in the vertical direction. The housing is coupled to the pin support and accommodates the elastic conductive sheet. The pusher is movably coupled to the housing in the vertical direction. The latch device is operatively connected to the housing and the pusher and fixes the device to be tested to the elastic conductive sheet to be releasable in conjunction with the movement of the pusher.

column12: GAS TRANSPORT TUBE AND PLASMA PROCESSING APPARATUS
column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To suppress occurrence of discharge in a gas transport tube provided between electrodes, without increasing the length of the gas transport tube.SOLUTION: A gas transport tube 60 transports process gas, introduced from the side of a ground member 61 facing an upper electrode 42 applied with a DC voltage, to gas diffusion chambers 54, 55. A tubular member 160 of the gas transport tube 60 has an inlet 161, and an outlet 162. A passage formation member 170 forms a first gas passage 171, multiple second gas passages 172, multiple third gas passages 173, and a fourth gas passage 174 in the tubular member 160. The first gas passage 171 elongates in the direction of the outlet 162. The multiple second gas passages 172 branch from the terminal of the first gas passage 171. The multiple third gas passages 173 meander between the inlet 161 and outlet 162. The fourth gas passage 174 merges the terminals of the multiple third gas passages 173 with the outlet 162.SELECTED DRAWING: Figure 2
